Name: Bivalirudin Trifluoroacetate
Information: Bivalirudin Trifluoroacetate is a synthetic 20 residue peptide (thrombin inhibitor) which reversibly inhibits thrombin.

Name: Eptifibatide Acetate
Information: Eptifibatide Acetate is a cyclic heptapeptide constructed from 6 amino acids and a mercaptopropionyl residue. A disulfide bridge forms between mercaptopropionyl and cysteine. Eptifibatide prevents platelet aggregation. One study shows the inhibition of platelet glycoprotein IIb/IIIa in acute coronary syndromes.

Name: Leuprorelin Acetate
Information: Leuprorelin Acetate is an agonist at pituitary GnRH receptors.

Name: Lypressin Acetate
Information: Lypressin Acetate is a hormone used to prevent or control the frequent urination, increased thirst, and loss of water associated with diabetes insipidus (water diabetes).

Name: Octreotide Acetate
Information: Octreotide Acetate is the acetate salt of a cyclic octapeptide. It is a long-acting octapeptide with pharmacologic properties mimicking those of the natural hormone somatostatin.

Name: Alarelin Acetate
Information: Alarelin Acetate is a synthetic LH-RH agonist that is found in higher amounts than that of LH-RH in rat hypophyseal stimulation of gonadotropin secretion in vivo and in vitro and in ovulation inductions.

Name: Atosiban Acetate
Information: Atosiban Acetate is a competitive oxytocin and vasopressin antagonist by exhibiting high affinity for both receptors. It is used to treat preterm labors.

Name: Gonadorelin Acetate
Information: Gonadorelin Acetate is another name for gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH). It is a synthetic decapeptide prepared using solid phase peptide synthesis.

Name: Oxytocin (Syntocinon)
Information: Oxytocin(Syntocinon) is a nine amino acid peptide that is synthesized in hypothalamic neurons and transported down axons of the posterior pituitary for secretion into blood.

Name: Salmon Calcitonin Acetate
Information: Salmon Calcitonin Acetate, which is more potent and longer lasting than human CT, has been used widely for the treatment of osteoporosis, paget's disease, hypercalcemic shock and chronic pain in terminal cancer patients.

Name: Terlipressin Acetate
Information: Terlipressin Acetate is an analogue of vasopressin used as a vasoactive drug in the management of hypotension. It has been found to be effective when norepinephrine does not help.

Name: GHRP-2
Information: GHRP-2 is a true hGH secretagogue. It is a synthetic agonist of ghrelin.

Name: Glucagon HCl
Information: Glucagon HCl stimulates glycogenolysis in the liver, used as the hydrochloride salt as an antihypoglycemic and as an adjunct in gastrointestinal radiography.

Name: Nafarelin Acetate
Information: Nafarelin Acetate is a Gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) agonist; synthetic decapeptide analog of GnRH (luteinizing hormone-releasing hormone, gonadorelin); structurally related to goserelin, leuprolide, and triptorelin.

Name: Pramlintide Acetate
Information: Pramlintide is an analogue of amylin, a small peptide hormone that is released into the bloodstream by the β cells of the pancreas along with insulin after a meal.

Name: Desmopressin Acetate
Information: Desmopressin is a synthetic octapeptide, and an analogue of human hormone arginine vasopressin with antidiuretic and coagulant activities. It is a selective agonist for the vasopressin V2 receptor (V2R).

Name: Angiotensin II human Acetate
Information: Angiotensin II human is converted by Angiotensin I through removal of two C-terminal residues by the enzyme angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE). Angiotensin II is mediated by AT1 and AT2 receptors, which are seven transmembrane glycoproteins with 30% sequence similarity.

Name: Carperitide Acetate
Information: a peptide hormone that promotes the loss of fluid and electrolytes and the reduction of vascular tone.

Name: ABT-737
Information: ABT-737 is a BH3 mimetic inhibitor of Bcl-xL, Bcl-2 and Bcl-w with EC50 of 78.7 nM, 30.3 nM and 197.8 nM in cell-free assays, respectively no inhibition observed against Mcl-1, Bcl-B or Bfl-1. Phase 2.

Name: Linifanib (ABT-869)
Information: Linifanib (ABT-869) is a novel, potent ATP-competitive VEGFR/PDGFR inhibitor for KDR, CSF-1R, Flt-1/3 and PDGFRβ with IC50 of 4 nM, 3 nM, 3 nM/4 nM and 66 nM respectively, mostly effective in mutant kinase-dependent cancer cells (i.e. FLT3). Phase 3.

Name: Veliparib (ABT-888)
Information: Veliparib (ABT-888) is a potent inhibitor of PARP1 and PARP2 with Ki of 5.2 nM and 2.9 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. It is inactive to SIRT2. Phase 3.

Name: Axitinib
Information: Axitinib is a multi-target inhibitor of VEGFR1, VEGFR2, VEGFR3, PDGFRβ and c-Kit with IC50 of 0.1 nM, 0.2 nM, 0.1-0.3 nM, 1.6 nM and 1.7 nM in Porcine aorta endothelial cells, respectively.

Name: Saracatinib (AZD0530)
Information: Saracatinib (AZD0530) is a potent Src inhibitor with IC50 of 2.7 nM in cell-free assays, and potent to c-Yes, Fyn, Lyn, Blk, Fgr and Lck less active for Abl and EGFR (L858R and L861Q). Phase 2/3.

Name: Roxadustat (FG-4592)
Information: Roxadustat (FG-4592) is an HIF-α prolyl hydroxylase inhibitor in a cell-free assay, stabilizes HIF-2 and induces EPO production. Phase 3.

Name: Selumetinib (AZD6244)
Information: Selumetinib (AZD6244) is a potent, highly selective MEK inhibitor with IC50 of 14 nM for MEK1 and Kd value of 530 nM for MEK2. It also inhibits ERK1/2 phosphorylation with IC50 of 10 nM, no inhibition to p38α, MKK6, EGFR, ErbB2, ERK2, B-Raf, etc. Phase 3.

Name: Nintedanib (BIBF 1120)
Information: Nintedanib (BIBF 1120) is a potent triple angiokinase inhibitor for VEGFR1/2/3, FGFR1/2/3 and PDGFRα/β with IC50 of 34 nM/13 nM/13 nM, 69 nM/37 nM/108 nM and 59 nM/65 nM in cell-free assays. Phase 3.

Name: Afatinib (BIBW2992)
Information: Afatinib (BIBW2992) inhibits EGFR/ErbB irreversibly in vitro with IC50 of 0.5, 0.4, 10, 14, 1 nM for EGFRwt, EGFR L858R , EGFR L858R/T790M ErbB2 (HER2) and ErbB4 (HER4), respectively.

Name: BMS-536924
Information: BMS-536924 is an ATP-competitive IGF-1R/IR inhibitor with IC50 of 100 nM/73 nM, modest activity for Mek, Fak, and Lck with very little activity for Akt1, MAPK1/2.

Name: Bortezomib (PS-341)
Information: Bortezomib (PS-341) is a potent 20S proteasome inhibitor with Ki of 0.6 nM. It exhibits favorable selectivity towards tumor cells over normal cells.

Name: Bosutinib (SKI-606)
Information: Bosutinib (SKI-606) is a novel, dual Src/Abl inhibitor with IC50 of 1.2 nM and 1 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Cediranib (AZD2171)
Information: Cediranib (AZD2171) is a highly potent VEGFR(KDR) inhibitor with IC50 of <1 nM, also inhibits Flt1/4 with IC50 of 5 nM/≤3 nM, similar activity against c-Kit and PDGFRβ, 36-, 110-fold and >1000-fold selective more for VEGFR than PDGFR-α, CSF-1R and Flt3 in HUVEC cells. Phase 3.

Name: Dovitinib (TKI-258, CHIR-258)
Information: Dovitinib (TKI258, CHIR258) is a multitargeted RTK inhibitor, mostly for class III (FLT3/c-Kit) with IC50 of 1 nM/2 nM, also potent to class IV (FGFR1/3) and class V (VEGFR1-4) RTKs with IC50 of 8-13 nM, less potent to InsR, EGFR, c-Met, EphA2, Tie2, IGF-1R and HER2 in cell-free assays. Phase 4.

Name: Canertinib (CI-1033)
Information: Canertinib (CI-1033) is a pan-ErbB inhibitor for EGFR and ErbB2 with IC50 of 1.5 nM and 9.0 nM, no activity to PDGFR, FGFR, InsR, PKC, or CDK1/2/4. Phase 3.

Name: PD184352 (CI-1040)
Information: PD184352 (CI-1040) is an ATP non-competitive MEK1/2 inhibitor with IC50 of 17 nM in cell-based assays, 100-fold more selective for MEK1/2 than MEK5. Phase 2.

Name: Dasatinib
Information: Dasatinib is a novel, potent and multi-targeted inhibitor that targets Abl, Src and c-Kit, with IC50 of <1 nM, 0.8 nM and 79 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Ridaforolimus (Deforolimus, MK-8669)
Information: Ridaforolimus (Deforolimus, MK-8669) is a selective mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 0.2 nM in HT-1080 cell line while not classified as a prodrug, mTOR inhibition and FKBP12 binding is similar to rapamycin. Phase 3.

Name: Erlotinib HCl (OSI-744)
Information: Erlotinib HCl (OSI-744) is an EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 2 nM in cell-free assays, >1000-fold more sensitive for EGFR than human c-Src or v-Abl.

Name: Gefitinib (ZD1839)
Information: Gefitinib (ZD-1839) is an EGFR inhibitor for Tyr1173, Tyr992, Tyr1173 and Tyr992 in the NR6wtEGFR and NR6W cells with IC50 of 37 nM, 37nM, 26 nM and 57 nM, respectively.

Name: Imatinib Mesylate (STI571)
Information: Imatinib Mesylate (STI571) is an orally bioavailability mesylate salt of Imatinib, which is a multi-target inhibitor of v-Abl, c-Kit and PDGFR with IC50 of 0.6 μM, 0.1 μM and 0.1 μM in cell-free or cell-based assays, respectively.

Name: Lapatinib (GW-572016) Ditosylate
Information: Lapatinib (GW-572016) Ditosylate is a potent EGFR and ErbB2 inhibitor with IC50 of 10.8 and 9.2 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Lenalidomide (CC-5013)
Information: Lenalidomide (CC-5013) is a TNF-α secretion inhibitor with IC50 of 13 nM in PBMCs.

Name: Panobinostat (LBH589)
Information: Panobinostat (LBH589) is a novel broad-spectrum HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM in a cell-free assay. Phase 3.

Name: Motesanib Diphosphate (AMG-706)
Information: Motesanib Diphosphate (AMG-706) is a potent ATP-competitive inhibitor of VEGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 2 nM/3 nM/6 nM, respectively similar activity against Kit, ~10-fold more selective for VEGFR than PDGFR and Ret. Phase 3.

Name: Nilotinib (AMN-107)
Information: Nilotinib (AMN-107) is a selective Bcr-Abl inhibitor with IC50 less than 30 nM in Murine myeloid progenitor cells.

Name: Pazopanib HCl (GW786034 HCl)
Information: Pazopanib HCl (GW786034 HCl) is a novel multi-target inhibitor of VEGFR1, VEGFR2, VEGFR3, PDGFR, FGFR, c-Kit and c-Fms with IC50 of 10 nM, 30 nM, 47 nM, 84 nM, 74 nM, 140 nM and 146 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: PD0325901
Information: PD0325901 is a selective and non ATP-competitive MEK inhibitor with IC50 of 0.33 nM in cell-free assays, roughly 500-fold more potent than CI-1040 on phosphorylation of ERK1 and ERK2. Phase 2.

Name: Perifosine (KRX-0401)
Information: Perifosine (KRX-0401) is a novel Akt inhibitor with IC50 of 4.7 μM in MM.1S cells, targets pleckstrin homology domain of Akt. Phase 3.

Name: PI-103
Information: PI-103 is a multi-targeted PI3K inhibitor for p110α/β/δ/γ with IC50 of 2 nM/3 nM/3 nM/15 nM in cell-free assays, less potent to mTOR/DNA-PK with IC50 of 30 nM/23 nM.

Name: Rapamycin (Sirolimus)
Information: Rapamycin (Sirolimus) is a specific mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of ~0.1 nM HEK293 cells.

Name: Sorafenib Tosylate
Information: Sorafenib Tosylate is a multikinase inhibitor of Raf-1, B-Raf and VEGFR-2 with IC50 of 6 nM, 22 nM and 90 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: STF-62247
Information: STF-62247 is a molecule targeting VHL-deficient renal cell carcinoma that induces autophagy. STF-62247 shows selective toxicity and growth inhibition of renal cells lacking VHL 25-fold greater sensitivity observed for cells with VHL deficiency compared to wild-type (VHL+).

Name: Sunitinib Malate
Information: Sunitinib Malate is a multi-targeted RTK inhibitor targeting VEGFR2 (Flk-1) and PDGFRβ with IC50 of 80 nM and 2 nM in cell-free assays, and also inhibits c-Kit.

Name: Tandutinib (MLN518)
Information: Tandutinib (MLN518, CT53518) is a potent FLT3 antagonist with IC50 of 0.22 μM, also inhibits PDGFR and c-Kit, 15 to 20-fold higher potency for FLT3 versus CSF-1R and >100-fold selectivity for the same target versus FGFR, EGFR and KDR. Phase 2.

Name: Temsirolimus (CCI-779, NSC 683864)
Information: Temsirolimus (CCI-779, NSC 683864) is a specific mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 1.76 μM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Vandetanib (ZD6474)
Information: Vandetanib (ZD6474) is a potent inhibitor of VEGFR2 with IC50 of 40 nM in a cell-free assay. It also inhibits VEGFR3 and EGFR with IC50 of 110 nM and 500 nM, respectively. Not sensitive to PDGFRβ, Flt1, Tie-2 and FGFR1 with IC50 of 1.1-3.6 μM. No activity against MEK, CDK2, c-Kit, erbB2, FAK, PDK1, Akt and IGF-1R with IC50 above 10 μM.

Name: Vorinostat (SAHA, MK0683)
Information: Vorinostat (suberoylanilide hydroxamic acid, SAHA) is an HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of ~10 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Tozasertib (VX-680, MK-0457)
Information: Tozasertib (VX-680, MK-0457) is a pan-Aurora inhibitor, mostly against Aurora A with Kiapp of 0.6 nM in a cell-free assay, less potent towards Aurora B/Aurora C and 100-fold more selective for Aurora A than 55 other kinases. Phase 2.

Name: Y-27632 2HCl
Information: Y-27632 2HCl is a selective ROCK1 (p160ROCK) inhibitor with Ki of 140 nM in a cell-free assay, exhibits >200-fold selectivity over other kinases, including PKC, cAMP-dependent protein kinase, MLCK and PAK.

Name: Elesclomol (STA-4783)
Information: Elesclomol (STA-4783) is a novel potent oxidative stress inducer that elicits pro-apoptosis events among tumor cells. Phase 3.

Name: Entinostat (MS-275)
Information: Entinostat (MS-275) strongly inhibits HDAC1 and HDAC3 with IC50 of 0.51 μM and 1.7 μM in cell-free assays, compared with HDACs 4, 6, 8, and 10. Phase 3.

Name: Enzastaurin (LY317615)
Information: Enzastaurin (LY317615) is a potent PKCβ selective inhibitor with IC50 of 6 nM in cell-free assays, 6- to 20-fold selectivity against PKCα, PKCγ and PKCε. Phase 3.

Name: AC480 (BMS-599626)
Information: AC480 (BMS-599626) is a selective and efficacious inhibitor of HER1 and HER2 with IC50 of 20 nM and 30 nM, ~8-fold less potent to HER4, >100-fold to VEGFR2, c-Kit, Lck, MET etc. Phase 1.

Name: Obatoclax Mesylate (GX15-070)
Information: Obatoclax Mesylate (GX15-070) is an antagonist of Bcl-2 with Ki of 0.22 μM in a cell-free assay, can assist in overcoming MCL-1 mediated resistance to apoptosis. Phase 3.

Name: Olaparib (AZD2281, Ku-0059436)
Information: Olaparib (AZD2281, KU0059436) is a selective inhibitor of PARP1/2 with IC50 of 5 nM/1 nM in cell-free assays, 300-times less effective against tankyrase-1.

Name: Nutlin-3
Information: Nutlin-3 is a potent and selective Mdm2 (RING finger-dependent ubiquitin protein ligase for itself and p53) antagonist with IC50 of 90 nM in a cell-free assay stabilizes p73 in p53-deficient cells.

Name: Masitinib (AB1010)
Information: Masitinib is a novel inhibitor for Kit and PDGFRα/β with IC50 of 200 nM and 540 nM/800 nM, weak inhibition to ABL and c-Fms. Phase 3.

Name: Pictilisib (GDC-0941)
Information: Pictilisib (GDC-0941) is a potent inhibitor of PI3Kα/δ with IC50 of 3 nM in cell-free assays, with modest selectivity against p110β (11-fold) and p110γ (25-fold). Phase 2.

Name: SB431542
Information: SB431542 is a potent and selective inhibitor of ALK5 with IC50 of 94 nM in a cell-free assay, 100-fold more selective for ALK5 than p38 MAPK and other kinases.

Name: Crizotinib (PF-02341066)
Information: Crizotinib (PF-02341066) is a potent inhibitor of c-Met and ALK with IC50 of 11 nM and 24 nM in cell-based assays, respectively.

Name: Luminespib (AUY-922, NVP-AUY922)
Information: Luminespib (AUY-922, NVP-AUY922) is a highly potent HSP90 inhibitor for HSP90α/β with IC50 of 13 nM /21 nM in cell-free assays, weaker potency against the HSP90 family members GRP94 and TRAP-1, exhibits the tightest binding of any small-molecule HSP90 ligand. Phase 2.

Name: PHA-665752
Information: PHA-665752 is a potent, selective and ATP-competitive c-Met inhibitor with IC50 of 9 nM in cell-free assays, >50-fold selectivity for c-Met than RTKs or STKs.

Name: HA14-1
Information: HA14-1 is a non-peptidic ligand of a Bcl-2 surface pocket with IC50 of ~9 μM.

Name: ZSTK474
Information: ZSTK474 inhibits class I PI3K isoforms with IC50 of 37 nM in a cell-free assay, mostly PI3Kδ. Phase1/2.

Name: SB203580
Information: SB203580 is a p38 MAPK inhibitor with IC50 of 0.3-0.5 μM in THP-1 cells, 10-fold less sensitive to SAPK3(106T) and SAPK4(106T) and blocks PKB phosphorylation with IC50 of 3-5 μM.

Name: MK-2206 2HCl
Information: MK-2206 2HCl is a highly selective inhibitor of Akt1/2/3 with IC50 of 8 nM/12 nM/65 nM in cell-free assays, respectively no inhibitory activities against 250 other protein kinases observed. Phase 2.

Name: SU11274
Information: SU11274 is a selective Met inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM in cell-free assays, no effects on PGDFRβ, EGFR or Tie2.

Name: Vismodegib (GDC-0449)
Information: Vismodegib (GDC-0449) is a potent, novel and specific hedgehog inhibitor with IC50 of 3 nM and also inhibits P-gp with IC50 of 3.0 μM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Brivanib (BMS-540215)
Information: Brivanib is an ATP-competitive inhibitor against VEGFR2 with IC50 of 25 nM, moderate potency against VEGFR-1 and FGFR-1, but >240-fold against PDGFR-β. Phase 3.

Name: Belinostat (PXD101)
Information: Belinostat (PXD101) is a novel HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 27 nM in a cell-free assay, with activity demonstrated in cisplatin-resistant tumors.

Name: Iniparib (BSI-201)
Information: Iniparib (BSI-201) is a PARP1 inhibitor with demonstrated effectiveness in triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC). Phase 3.

Name: Refametinib (RDEA119, Bay 86-9766)
Information: Refametinib (RDEA119, Bay 86-9766) is a potent, ATP non-competitive and highly selective inhibitor of MEK1 and MEK2 with IC50 of 19 nM and 47 nM, respectively.

Name: Abexinostat (PCI-24781)
Information: Abexinostat (PCI-24781) is a novel pan-HDAC inhibitor mostly targeting HDAC1 with Ki of 7 nM, modest potent to HDACs 2, 3, 6, and 10 and greater than 40-fold selectivity against HDAC8. Phase 1/2.

Name: Linsitinib (OSI-906)
Information: Linsitinib (OSI-906) is a selective inhibitor of IGF-1R with IC50 of 35 nM in cell-free assays modestly potent to InsR with IC50 of 75 nM, and no activity towards Abl, ALK, BTK, EGFR, FGFR1/2, PKA etc. Phase 3.

Name: KU-55933 (ATM Kinase Inhibitor)
Information: KU-55933 (ATM Kinase Inhibitor) is a potent and specific ATM inhibitor with IC50/Ki of 12.9 nM/2.2 nM in cell-free assays, and is highly selective for ATM as compared to DNA-PK, PI3K/PI4K, ATR and mTOR.

Name: PF-04217903
Information: PF-04217903 is a selective ATP-competitive c-Met inhibitor with IC50 of 4.8 nM in A549 cell line, susceptible to oncogenic mutations (no activity to Y1230C mutant). Phase 1.

Name: Quisinostat (JNJ-26481585) 2HCl
Information: Quisinostat (JNJ-26481585) 2HCl is a novel second-generation HDAC inhibitor with highest potency for HDAC1 with IC50 of 0.11 nM in a cell-free assay, modest potent to HDACs 2, 4, 10, and 11 greater than 30-fold selectivity against HDACs 3, 5, 8, and 9 and lowest potency to HDACs 6 and 7. Phase 2.

Name: BTZ043 Racemate
Information: BTZ043 racemate is a decaprenylphosphoryl-β-D-ribose 2'-epimerase (DprE1) inhibitor acting as a new antimycobacterial agent that kill Mycobacterium tuberculosis.

Name: Rucaparib (AG-014699,PF-01367338) phosphate
Information: Rucaparib (AG-014699, PF-01367338) is an inhibitor of PARP with Ki of 1.4 nM for PARP1 in a cell-free assay, also showing binding affinity to eight other PARP domains. Phase 3.

Name: MLN8054
Information: MLN8054 is a potent and selective inhibitor of Aurora A with IC50 of 4 nM in Sf9 insect cell. It is more than 40-fold selective for Aurora A than Aurora B. Phase 1.

Name: Vatalanib (PTK787) 2HCl
Information: Vatalanib (PTK787) 2HCl is an inhibitor of VEGFR2/KDR with IC50 of 37 nM in a cell-free assay, less potent against VEGFR1/Flt-1, 18-fold against VEGFR3/Flt-4. Phase 3.

Name: U0126-EtOH
Information: U0126-EtOH is a highly selective inhibitor of MEK1/2 with IC50 of 0.07 μM/0.06 μM in cell-free assays, 100-fold higher affinity for ΔN3-S218E/S222D MEK than PD98059.

Name: ZM 447439
Information: ZM 447439 is a selective and ATP-competitive inhibitor for Aurora A and Aurora B with IC50 of 110 nM and 130 nM, respectively. It is more than 8-fold selective for Aurora A/B than MEK1, Src, Lck and has little effect against CDK1/2/4, Plk1, Chk1, etc.

Name: LY294002
Information: LY294002 is the first synthetic molecule known to inhibit PI3Kα/δ/β with IC50 of 0.5 μM/0.57 μM/0.97 μM in cell-free assays, respectively more stable in solution than Wortmannin, and also blocks autophagosome formation.

Name: OSU-03012 (AR-12)
Information: OSU-03012 (AR-12) is a potent inhibitor of recombinant PDK-1(phosphoinositide-dependent kinase 1) with IC50 of 5 μM in a cell-free assay and 2-fold increase in potency over OSU-02067.

Name: Danusertib (PHA-739358)
Information: Danusertib (PHA-739358) is an Aurora kinase inhibitor for Aurora A/B/C with IC50 of 13 nM/79 nM/61 nM in cell-free assays, modestly potent to Abl, TrkA, c-RET and FGFR1, and less potent to Lck, VEGFR2/3, c-Kit, CDK2, etc. Phase 2.

Name: TAE684 (NVP-TAE684)
Information: TAE684 (NVP-TAE684) is a potent and selective ALK inhibitor with IC50 of 3 nM in a cell-free assay, 100-fold more sensitive for ALK than InsR.

Name: BI 2536
Information: BI2536 is a potent Plk1 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.83 nM in a cell-free assay. It shows 4- and 11-fold greater selectivity against Plk2 and Plk3. Phase 2.

Name: Varespladib (LY315920)
Information: Varespladib (LY315920) is a potent and selective human non-pancreatic secretory phospholipase A2 (hnsPLA) inhibitor with IC50 of 7 nM. Phase 3.

Name: Foretinib (GSK1363089)
Information: Foretinib (GSK1363089) is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of HGFR and VEGFR, mostly for Met and KDR with IC50 of 0.4 nM and 0.9 nM in cell-free assays. Less potent against Ron, Flt-1/3/4, Kit, PDGFRα/β and Tie-2, and little activity to FGFR1 and EGFR. Phase 2.

Name: SGX-523
Information: SGX-523 is a selective Met inhibitor with IC50 of 4 nM, no activity to BRAFV599E, c-Raf, Abl and p38α. Phase 1.

Name: GSK690693
Information: GSK690693 is a pan-Akt inhibitor targeting Akt1/2/3 with IC50 of 2 nM/13 nM/9 nM in cell-free assays, also sensitive to the AGC kinase family: PKA, PrkX and PKC isozymes. Phase 1.

Name: JNJ-38877605
Information: JNJ-38877605 is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of c-Met with IC50 of 4 nM, 600-fold selective for c-Met than 200 other tyrosine and serine-threonine kinases. Phase 1.

Name: Odanacatib (MK-0822)
Information: Odanacatib (MK 0822) is a potent, selective, and neutral inhibitor of cathepsin K (human/rabbit) with IC50 of 0.2 nM/1 nM, and demonstrated high selectivity versus off-target cathepsin B, L, S. Phase 3.

Name: Palbociclib (PD-0332991) HCl
Information: Palbociclib (PD-0332991) HCl is a highly selective inhibitor of CDK4/6 with IC50 of 11 nM/16 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. It shows no activity against CDK1/2/5, EGFR, FGFR, PDGFR, InsR, etc. Phase 3.

Name: Triciribine
Information: Triciribine is a DNA synthesis inhibitor, also inhibits Akt in PC3 cell line and HIV-1 in CEM-SS, H9, H9IIIB, U1 cells with IC50 of 130 nM and 20 nM, respectively does not inhibit PI3K/PDK1 5000-fold less active in cells lacking adenosine kinase. Phase 1/2.

Name: Cabozantinib (XL184, BMS-907351)
Information: Cabozantinib (XL184, BMS-907351) is a potent VEGFR2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.035 nM and also inhibits c-Met, Ret, Kit, Flt-1/3/4, Tie2, and AXL with IC50 of 1.3 nM, 4 nM, 4.6 nM, 12 nM/11.3 nM/6 nM, 14.3 nM and 7 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Everolimus (RAD001)
Information: Everolimus (RAD001) is an mTOR inhibitor of FKBP12 with IC50 of 1.6-2.4 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Mocetinostat (MGCD0103)
Information: Mocetinostat (MGCD0103) is a potent HDAC inhibitor with most potency for HDAC1 with IC50 of 0.15 μM in a cell-free assay, 2- to 10- fold selectivity against HDAC2, 3, and 11, and no activity to HDAC4, 5, 6, 7, and 8. Phase 2.

Name: BMS-754807
Information: BMS-754807 is a potent and reversible inhibitor of IGF-1R/InsR with IC50 of 1.8 nM/1.7 nM in cell-free assays, less potent to Met, Aurora A/B, TrkA/B and Ron, and shows little activity to Flt3, Lck, MK2, PKA, PKC etc. Phase 2.

Name: SRT1720 HCl
Information: SRT1720 HCl is a selective SIRT1 activator with EC50 of 0.16 μM in a cell-free assay, but is >230-fold less potent for SIRT2 and SIRT3.

Name: YM155 (Sepantronium Bromide)
Information: YM155 (Sepantronium Bromide) is a potent survivin suppressant by inhibiting Survivin promoter activity with IC50 of 0.54 nM in HeLa-SURP-luc and CHO-SV40-luc cells does not significantly inhibit SV40 promoter activity, but is observed to slightly inhibit the interaction of Survivin with XIAP. Phase 2.

Name: INO-1001 (3-Aminobenzamide)
Information: INO-1001 is a potent inhibitor of PARP with IC50 of <50 nM in CHO cells and a mediator of oxidant-induced myocyte dysfunction during reperfusion. Phase 2.

Name: Alisertib (MLN8237)
Information: Alisertib (MLN8237) is a selective Aurora A inhibitor with IC50 of 1.2 nM in a cell-free assay. It has >200-fold higher selectivity for Aurora A than Aurora B. Phase 3.

Name: AT9283
Information: AT9283 is a potent JAK2/3 inhibitor with IC50 of 1.2 nM/1.1 nM in cell-free assays also potent to Aurora A/B, Abl(T315I). Phase 2.

Name: Pemetrexed
Information: Pemetrexed is a novel antifolate and antimetabolite for TS, DHFR and GARFT with Ki of 1.3 nM, 7.2 nM and 65 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Malotilate
Information: Malotilate, diisopropyl 1,3-dithiol-2-ylidenemalonate, is a drug used for the treatment of liver cirrhosis.

Name: Brivanib Alaninate (BMS-582664)
Information: Brivanib alaninate (BMS-582664) is the prodrug of BMS-540215, an ATP-competitive inhibitor against VEGFR2 with IC50 of 25 nM.

Name: ADL5859 HCl
Information: ADL5859 HCl is a δ-opioid receptor agonist with Ki of 0.8 nM, selectivity against opioid receptor κ, μ, and weak inhibitory activity at the hERG channel. Phase 2.

Name: Andarine
Information: Andarine is a selective non-steroidal androgen receptor (AR) agonist with Ki of 4 nM, tissue-selective for anabolic organs. Phase 3.

Name: Tanespimycin (17-AAG)
Information: Tanespimycin (17-AAG) is a potent HSP90 inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM in a cell-free assay, having a 100-fold higher binding affinity for HSP90 derived from tumour cells than HSP90 from normal cells. Phase 2.

Name: Alvespimycin (17-DMAG) HCl
Information: Alvespimycin (17-DMAG) HCl is a potent HSP90 inhibitor with IC50 of 62 nM in a cell-free assay. Phase 2.

Name: AG-490 (Tyrphostin B42)
Information: AG-490 (Tyrphostin B42) is an inhibitor of EGFR with IC50 of 0.1 μM in cell-free assays, 135-fold more selective for EGFR versus ErbB2, also inhibits JAK2 with no activity to Lck, Lyn, Btk, Syk and Src.

Name: Ivacaftor (VX-770)
Information: Ivacaftor (VX-770) is a selective potentiator of CFTR targeting G551D-CFTR and F508del-CFTR with EC50 of 100 nM and 25 nM in fisher rat thyroid cells, respectively.

Name: SNS-032 (BMS-387032)
Information: SNS-032 (BMS-387032) has firstly been described as a selective inhibitor of CDK2 with IC50 of 48 nM in cell-free assays and is 10- and 20-fold selective over CDK1/CDK4. It is also found to be sensitive to CDK7/9 with IC50 of 62 nM/4 nM, with little effect on CDK6. Phase 1.

Name: Barasertib (AZD1152-HQPA)
Information: Barasertib (AZD1152-HQPA) is a highly selective Aurora B inhibitor with IC50 of 0.37 nM in a cell-free assay, ~3700 fold more selective for Aurora B over Aurora A. Phase 1.

Name: Docetaxel
Information: Docetaxel, an analog of paclitaxel, is an inhibitor of depolymerisation of microtubules by binding to stabilized microtubules.

Name: Gemcitabine HCl
Information: Gemcitabine HCl is a DNA synthesis inhibitor with IC50 of 50 nM, 40 nM, 18 nM and 12 nM in PANC1, MIAPaCa2, BxPC3 and Capan2 cells, respectively.

Name: Paclitaxel
Information: Paclitaxel is a microtubule polymer stabilizer with IC50 of 0.1 pM in human endothelial cells.

Name: Ibutamoren mesylate (MK-0667, L163191)
Information: Ibutamoren mesylate (MK-0667, L163191) is a potent, orally active growth hormone (GH) secretagogue.

Name: PLX-4720
Information: PLX4720 is a potent and selective inhibitor of B-RafV600E with IC50 of 13 nM in a cell-free assay, equally potent to c-Raf-1(Y340D and Y341D mutations), 10-fold selectivity for B-RafV600E than wild-type B-Raf.

Name: Roscovitine (Seliciclib,CYC202)
Information: Roscovitine (Seliciclib, CYC202) is a potent and selective CDK inhibitor for Cdc2, CDK2 and CDK5 with IC50 of 0.65 μM, 0.7 μM and 0.16 μM in cell-free assays. It shows little effect on CDK4/6. Phase 2.

Name: SNS-314
Information: SNS-314 is a potent and selective inhibitor of Aurora A, Aurora B and Aurora C with IC50 of 9 nM, 31 nM, and 3 nM, respectively. It is less potent to Trk A/B, Flt4, Fms, Axl, c-Raf and DDR2. Phase 1.

Name: Capecitabine
Information: Capecitabine is a tumor-selective fluoropyrimidine carbamate, which achieves higher intratumoral 5-FU level with lower toxicity than 5-FU.

Name: Delanzomib (CEP-18770)
Information: Delanzomib (CEP-18770) is an orally active inhibitor of the chymotrypsin-like activity of proteasome with IC50 of 3.8 nM, with only marginal inhibition of the tryptic and peptidylglutamyl activities of the proteosome. Phase 1/2.

Name: MK-8245
Information: MK-8245 is an liver-targeting inhibitor of stearoyl-CoA desaturase (SCD) with IC50 of 1 nM for human SCD1 and 3 nM for both rat SCD1 and mouse SCD1, with anti-diabetic and anti-dyslipidemic efficacy. Phase 2.

Name: Ganetespib (STA-9090)
Information: Ganetespib (STA-9090) is an HSP90 inhibitor with IC50 of 4 nM in OSA 8 cells, induces apoptosis of OSA cells while normal osteoblasts are not affected active metabolite of STA-1474. Phase 3.

Name: PA-824
Information: PA-824 is an anti-tuberculosis drug for tuberculosis with MIC less than 2.8 μM.Phase 2.

Name: Onalespib (AT13387)
Information: Onalespib (AT13387) is a selective potent Hsp90 inhibitor with IC50 of 18 nM in A375 cells, displays a long duration of anti-tumor activity. Phase 2.

Name: Lenvatinib (E7080)
Information: Lenvatinib (E7080) is a multi-target inhibitor, mostly for VEGFR2(KDR)/VEGFR3(Flt-4) with IC50 of 4 nM/5.2 nM, less potent against VEGFR1/Flt-1, ~10-fold more selective for VEGFR2/3 against FGFR1, PDGFRα/β in cell-free assays. Phase 3.

Name: ABT-751 (E7010)
Information: ABT-751 (E7010) binds to the colchicine site on β-tubulin and inhibits polymerization of microtubules, not a substrate for the MDR transporter and is active against cell lines resistant to vincristine, doxorubicin, and cisplatin. Phase 1/2.

Name: CP-724714
Information: CP-724714 is a potent, selective inhibitor of HER2/ErbB2 with IC50 of 10 nM, >640-fold selectivity against EGFR, InsR, IRG-1R, PDGFR, VEGFR2, Abl, Src, c-Met etc in cell-free assays. Phase 2.

Name: Valproic acid sodium salt (Sodium valproate)
Information: Valproic acid sodium salt (Sodium valproate) is a HDAC inhibitor by selectively inducing proteasomal degradation of HDAC2, used in the treatment of epilepsy, bipolar disorder and prevention of migraine headaches.

Name: TGX-221
Information: TGX-221 is a p110β-specific inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM in a cell-free assay, 1000-fold more selective for p110β than p110α.

Name: CYC116
Information: CYC116 is a potent inhibitor of Aurora A/B with Ki of 8.0 nM/9.2 nM, is less potent to VEGFR2 (Ki of 44 nM), with 50-fold greater potency than CDKs, not active against PKA, Akt/PKB, PKC, no effect on GSK-3α/β, CK2, Plk1 and SAPK2A. Phase 1.

Name: JNJ-26854165 (Serdemetan)
Information: JNJ-26854165 (Serdemetan) acts as a HDM2 ubiquitin ligase antagonist and also induces early apoptosis in p53 wild-type cells, inhibits cellular proliferation followed by delayed apoptosis in the absence of functional p53. Phase 1.

Name: Ostarine (GTx-024, MK-2866 )
Information: MK-2866 (GTx-024) is a selective androgen receptor modulator (SARM) with Ki of 3.8 nM, and is tissue-selective for anabolic organs. Phase 3.

Name: BIIB021
Information: BIIB021 is an orally available, fully synthetic small-molecule inhibitor of HSP90 with Ki and EC50 of 1.7 nM and 38 nM, respectively. Phase 2.

Name: Plinabulin (NPI-2358)
Information: Plinabulin (NPI-2358) is a vascular disrupting agent (VDA) against tubulin-depolymerizing with IC50 of 9.8~18 nM in tumor cells. Phase 1/2.

Name: Regorafenib (BAY 73-4506)
Information: Regorafenib (BAY 73-4506) is a multi-target inhibitor for VEGFR1, VEGFR2, VEGFR3, PDGFRβ, Kit, RET and Raf-1 with IC50 of 13 nM/4.2 nM/46 nM, 22 nM, 7 nM, 1.5 nM and 2.5 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: XAV-939
Information: XAV-939 selectively inhibits Wnt/β-catenin-mediated transcription through tankyrase1/2 inhibition with IC50 of 11 nM/4 nM in cell-free assays, regulates axin levels and does not affect CRE, NF-κB or TGF-β.

Name: ENMD-2076
Information: ENMD-2076 has selective activity against Aurora A and Flt3 with IC50 of 14 nM and 1.86 nM, 25-fold selective for Aurora A than over Aurora B and less potent to VEGFR2/KDR and VEGFR3, FGFR1 and FGFR2 and PDGFRα. Phase 2.

Name: Danoprevir (ITMN-191)
Information: Danoprevir(ITMN-191) is a peptidomimetic inhibitor of the NS3/4A protease of hepatitis C virus (HCV) with IC50 of 0.2-3.5 nM, inhibition effect for HCV genotypes 1A/1B/4/5/6 is ~10-fold higher than 2B/3A. Phase 2.

Name: Ritonavir
Information: Ritonavir is a Cytochrome P450 3A and Protease Inhibitor Also inhibits Cytochrome P450 2D6, P-Glycoprotein and induces Cytochrome P450 2C19, Cytochrome P450 1A2, Cytochrome P450 2C9, Cytochrome P450 2B6 and UDP Glucuronosyltransferases.

Name: Anastrozole
Information: Anastrozole is a third-generation nonsteroidal selective aromatase inhibitor. It may offer greater selectivity compared with other aromatase inhibitors, being without any intrinsic endocrine effects and with no apparent effect on the synthesis of adrenal steroids.

Name: Aprepitant
Information: Aprepitant is a potent and selective neurokinin-1 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.1 nM.

Name: Bicalutamide
Information: Bicalutamide is an androgen receptor (AR) antagonist with IC50 of 0.16 μM in LNCaP/AR(cs)cell line.

Name: Fulvestrant
Information: Fulvestrant is an estrogen receptor (ER) antagonist with IC50 of 0.94 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Raltitrexed
Information: Raltitrexed is a thymidylate synthase inhibitor with an IC50 of 9 nM for the inhibition of L1210 cell growth.

Name: Thalidomide
Information: Thalidomide was introduced as a sedative drug, immunomodulatory agent and also is investigated for treating symptoms of many cancers. Thalidomide inhibits an E3 ubiquitin ligase, which is a CRBN-DDB1-Cul4A complex.

Name: CUDC-101
Information: CUDC-101 is a potent multi-targeted inhibitor against HDAC, EGFR and HER2 with IC50 of 4.4 nM, 2.4 nM, and 15.7 nM, and inhibits class I/II HDACs, but not class III, Sir-type HDACs. Phase 1.

Name: TAK-700 (Orteronel)
Information: TAK-700 (Orteronel) is a potent and highly selective human 17,20-lyase inhibitor with IC50 of 38 nM, exhibits >1000-fold selectivity over other CYPs (e.g. 11-hydroxylase and CYP3A4). Phase 3.

Name: Exemestane
Information: Exemestane is an aromatase inhibitor, inhibits human placental and rat ovarian aromatase with IC50 of 30 nM and 40 nM, respectively.

Name: Finasteride
Information: Finasteride is a potent, reversible inhibitor of the rat type 1 5 alpha-reductase with Ki of 10.2 nM, used in the treatment of benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and male pattern baldness (MPB).

Name: Cladribine
Information: Cladribine is an adenosine deaminase inhibitor for U266, RPMI8226, and MM1.S cells with IC50 of approximately 2.43 μM, 0.75 μM, and 0.18 μM, respectively.

Name: Decitabine
Information: Decitabine is a DNA methyltransferase inhibitor, incorporating into DNA and resulting in hypomethylation of DNA and intra-S-phase arrest of DNA replication. It is used to treat myelodysplastic syndrome (MDS).

Name: Dimesna
Information: Dimesna is an uroprotective agent used to decrease urotoxicity.

Name: Dutasteride
Information: Dutasteride is a dual 5-α reductase inhibitor that inhibits conversion of testosterone to dihydrotestosterone (DHT).

Name: Melatonin
Information: Melatonin is a MT receptor agonist, used as a dietary supplement.

Name: PIK-75 HCl
Information: PIK-75 HCl is a p110α inhibitor with IC50 of 5.8 nM (200-fold more potently than p110β), isoform-specific mutants at Ser773, and also potently inhibits DNA-PK with IC50 of 2 nM in cell-free assays.

Name: Bisoprolol fumarate
Information: Bisoprolol fumarate is a selective type β1 adrenergic receptor blocker.

Name: Tivozanib (AV-951)
Information: Tivozanib (AV-951) is a potent and selective VEGFR inhibitor for VEGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 30 nM/6.5 nM/15 nM, and also inhibits PDGFR and c-Kit, low activity observed against FGFR-1, Flt3, c-Met, EGFR and IGF-1R. Phase 3.

Name: Doxorubicin (Adriamycin) HCl
Information: Doxorubicin (Adriamycin) HCl is an antibiotic agent that inhibits DNA topoisomerase II and induces DNA damage and apoptosis in tumor cells.

Name: Fluorouracil (5-Fluoracil, 5-FU)
Information: Fluorouracil (5-Fluoracil, 5-FU) is a DNA/RNA synthesis inhibitor, which interrupts nucleotide synthetic by inhibiting thymidylate synthase (TS) in tumor cells.

Name: Methotrexate
Information: Methotrexate (MTX), analog of folic acid, is a nonspecific inhibitor of the dihydrofolate reductase(DHFR) of bacteria and cancerous cells as well as normal cells. It forms an inactive ternary complex with DHFR and NADPH.

Name: Imiquimod
Information: Imiquimod is a novel synthetic agent with immune response modifying activity.

Name: Bendamustine HCl
Information: Bendamustine HCL is a DNA-damaging agent with IC50 of 50 μM in cell-free assay.

Name: Nelarabine
Information: Nelarabine is a purine nucleoside analog and DNA synthesis inhibitor with IC50 from 0.067-2.15 μM in tumor cells.

Name: Bleomycin sulfate
Information: Bleomycin Sulfate is a glycopeptide antibiotic and an anticancer agent for squamous cell carcinomas (SCC) with IC50 of 4 nM in UT-SCC-19A cells.

Name: Carboplatin
Information: Carboplatin is a DNA synthesis inhibitor by binding to DNA and interfering with the cell's repair mechanism in A2780, SKOV-3, IGROV-1, and HX62 cells.

Name: Clofarabine
Information: Clofarabine inhibits the enzymatic activities of ribonucleotide reductase (IC50 = 65 nM) and DNA polymerase.

Name: OSI-930
Information: OSI-930 is a potent inhibitor of Kit, KDR and CSF-1R with IC50 of 80 nM, 9 nM and 15 nM, respectively also potent to Flt-1, c-Raf and Lck and low activity against PDGFRα/β, Flt-3 and Abl. Phase 1.

Name: Dacarbazine
Information: Dacarbazine is a triazene derivative with antineoplastic activity. Dacarbazine alkylates and cross-links DNA during all phases of the cell cycle, resulting in disruption of DNA function, cell cycle arrest, and apoptosis used in the treatment of various cancers.

Name: Dexrazoxane HCl (ICRF-187, ADR-529)
Information: Dexrazoxane HCl (ICRF-187, ADR-529) is an intracellular iron chelator, which decreases the formation of superoxide radicals, used as a cardioprotective agent also an inhibitor of topoisomerase II

Name: Epirubicin HCl
Information: Epirubicin HCl, a semisynthetic L-arabino derivative of doxorubicin, is an antineoplastic agent by inhibiting Topoisomerase.

Name: Oxaliplatin
Information: Oxaliplatin inhibits DNA synthesis by conforming DNA adducts in RT4, TCCSUP, A2780, HT-29, U-373MG, U-87MG, SK-MEL-2, and HT-144 cells.

Name: Etoposide
Information: Etoposide is a semisynthetic derivative of podophyllotoxin, which inhibits DNA synthesis via topoisomerase II inhibition activity.

Name: KU-0063794
Information: KU-0063794 is a potent and highly specific dual-mTOR inhibitor of mTORC1 and mTORC2 with IC50 of ~10 nM in cell-free assays no effect on PI3Ks.

Name: Raloxifene HCl
Information: Raloxifene is an estrogen antagonist, which inhibits human cytosolic aldehyde oxidase-catalyzed phthalazine oxidation activity with IC50 of 5.7 nM.

Name: Fludarabine Phosphate
Information: Fludarabine Phosphate is an analogue of adenosine and deoxyadenosine, which is able to compete with dATP for incorporation into DNA and inhibit DNA synthesis.

Name: Flavopiridol (Alvocidib)
Information: Flavopiridol (Alvocidib) competes with ATP to inhibit CDKs including CDK1, CDK2, CDK4, CDK6, and CDK9 with IC50 values in the 20-100 nM range. It is more selective for CDK1, 2, 4, 6, 9 versus CDK7. Flavopiridol is initially found to inhibit EGFR and PKA. Phase 1/2.

Name: Topotecan HCl
Information: Topotecan HCl is a topoisomerase I inhibitor for MCF-7 Luc cells and DU-145 Luc cells with IC50 of 13 nM and 2 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: 2-Methoxyestradiol (2-MeOE2)
Information: 2-Methoxyestradiol (2-MeOE2) depolymerizes microtubules and blocks HIF-1α nuclear accumulation and HIF-transcriptional activity. Phase 2.

Name: Letrozole
Information: Letrozole is a third generation inhibitor of aromatase with IC50 of 0.07-20 nM in cell-free assays.It has no effect on the plasma levels of 17α-OH progesterone, thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH), luteinizing hormone (LH), follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH), or androstenedione and does not affect normal urine electrolyte excretion or thyroid function in clinical studies.

Name: Leucovorin Calcium Pentahydrate
Information: Leucovorin is a derivative of folic acid, which can be used to increase levels of folic acid under conditions favoring folic acid inhibition.

Name: Temozolomide
Information: Temozolomide is a monofunctional SN-1 alkylating agent that can modify nitrogen atoms in the DNA ring and the extracyclic oxygen group, chemically converted to MTIC and degrades to methyldiazonium cation, which transfers methyl groups to DNA at physiologic pH. A DNA damage inducer in L-1210 and L-1210/BCNU cells.

Name: Tamoxifen
Information: Tamoxifen is an antagonist of the estrogen receptor in breast tissue.

Name: Vincristine sulfate
Information: Vincristine sulfate is an inhibitor of polymerization of microtubules by binding to tubulin with IC50 of 32 μM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Agomelatine
Information: Agomelatine is classified as a norepinephrine-dopamine disinhibitor (NDDI) due to its antagonism of the 5-HT2C receptor.

Name: Amuvatinib (MP-470)
Information: Amuvatinib (MP-470) is a potent and multi-targeted inhibitor of c-Kit, PDGFRα and Flt3 with IC50 of 10 nM, 40 nM and 81 nM, respectively. Phase 2.

Name: Latrepirdine 2HCl
Information: Latrepirdine is an orally active,and neuroactive antagonist of multiple drug targets, including histamine receptors, GluR, and 5-HT receptors, used as an antihistamine drug.

Name: Leflunomide
Information: Leflunomide is a pyrimidine synthesis inhibitor belonging to the DMARD, used as an immunosuppressant agent.

Name: JNJ-7706621
Information: JNJ-7706621 is pan-CDK inhibitor with the highest potency on CDK1/2 with IC50 of 9 nM/4 nM and showing >6-fold selectivity for CDK1/2 than CDK3/4/6 in cell-free assays. It also potently inhibits Aurora A/B and has no activity on Plk1 and Wee1.

Name: Enzalutamide (MDV3100)
Information: Enzalutamide (MDV3100) is an androgen-receptor (AR) antagonist with IC50 of 36 nM in LNCaP cells.

Name: Dienogest
Information: Dienogest is an orally active synthetic progesterone, used for contraception and the treatment of endometriosis.

Name: Entecavir Hydrate
Information: Entecavir, a new deoxyguanine nucleoside analogue, is a selective inhibitor of the replication of the hepatitis B virus (HBV).

Name: Nepafenac
Information: Nepafenac is a prodrug of amfenac that acts as an inhibitor of COX-1 and COX-2 activity, used in the treatment of pain and inflammation associated with cataract surgery.

Name: Rufinamide
Information: Rufinamide is a voltage-gated sodium channel blocker, used an anticonvulsant medication.

Name: Posaconazole
Information: Posaconazole is an inhibitor primarily of CYP3A4, but it does not inhibit the activity of other CYP enzymes Also an inhibitor of sterol C14ɑ demethylase inhibitor with IC50 of 0.25 μM. Posaconazole has a median terminal elimination half-life of 15-35 hours.

Name: Prasugrel
Information: Prasugrel is a thienopyridine ADP receptor (P2Y12) antagonist, used for the reduction of thrombotic cardiovascular events.

Name: Ramelteon
Information: Ramelteon is a novel melatonin receptor agonist for human MT1 and MT2 receptors and chick forebrain melatonin receptors with Ki of 14 pM, 112 pM and 23.1 pM, respectively.

Name: Cinacalcet HCl
Information: Cinacalcet HCl represents a new class of compounds for the treatment of hyperparathyroidism.

Name: Celecoxib
Information: Celecoxib is a selective COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 40 nM in Sf9 cells.

Name: Avagacestat (BMS-708163)
Information: Avagacestat (BMS-708163) is a potent, selective, orally bioavailable γ-secretase inhibitor of Aβ40 and Aβ42 with IC50 of 0.3 nM and 0.27 nM, demonstrating a 193-fold selectivity against Notch. Phase 2.

Name: CHIR-99021 (CT99021)
Information: CHIR-99021 (CT99021) is a GSK-3α and GSK-3β inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM and 6.7 nM, respectively. CHIR99201 does not exhibit cross-reactivity against cyclin-dependent kinases (CDKs) and shows a 350-fold selectivity toward GSK-3β compared to CDKs.

Name: PD173074
Information: PD173074 is a potent FGFR1 inhibitor with IC50 of ~25 nM and also inhibits VEGFR2 with IC50 of 100-200 nM in cell-free assays, ~1000-fold selective for FGFR1 than PDGFR and c-Src.

Name: Vemurafenib (PLX4032, RG7204)
Information: Vemurafenib (PLX4032, RG7204) is a novel and potent inhibitor of B-RafV600E with IC50 of 31 nM in cell-free assay. 10-fold selective for B-RafV600E over wild-type B-Raf in enzymatic assays and the cellular selectivity can exceed 100-fold.

Name: Acarbose
Information: Acarbose is an inhibitor of intestinal alpha-glucosidase, used to treat type 2 diabetes mellitus.

Name: BX-795
Information: BX795 is a potent and specific PDK1 inhibitor with IC50 of 6 nM, 140- and 1600-fold more selective for PDK1 than PKA and PKC in cell-free assays, respectively. Meanwhile, in comparison to GSK3β more than 100-fold selectivity observed for PDK1.

Name: BX-912
Information: BX912 is a potent and specific PDK1 inhibitor with IC50 of 12 nM, 9- and 105- fold greater selectivity for PDK1 than PKA and PKC in cell-free assays, respectively. In comparison to GSK3β, selectivity for PDK1 is 600-fold.

Name: Adapalene
Information: Adapalene is a dual RAR and RXR agonist, used in the treatment of acne.

Name: Altretamine
Information: Altretamine is an anti-neoplastic agent.

Name: Amisulpride
Information: Amisulpride is an atypical antipsychotic used to treat psychosis in schizophrenia and episodes of mania in bipolar disorder.

Name: Aniracetam
Information: Aniracetam is a nootropics and neuroprotective drug.

Name: Artemisinin
Information: Artemisinin is a sesquiterpene endoperoxide which is a potent antimalarial agent.

Name: Asenapine maleate
Information: Asenapine maleate is a high-affinity antagonist of serotonin, norepinephrine, dopamine and histamine receptors, used for the treatment of schizophrenia and acute mania associated with?bipolar disorder.

Name: Benazepril HCl
Information: Benazepril HCl is a novel angiotensin I converting enzyme inhibitor, used primarily in treatment of hypertension.

Name: Budesonide
Information: Budesonide is a glucocorticoid steroid for the treatment of asthma, non-infectious rhinitis.

Name: Bumetanide
Information: Bumetanide (Bumex) is a loop diuretic of the sulfamyl category to treat heart failure.

Name: Camptothecin
Information: Camptothecin is a specific inhibitor of DNA topoisomerase I (Topo I) with IC50 of 0.68 μM in a cell-free assay. Phase 2.

Name: Carmofur
Information: Carmofur is a highly potent acid ceramidase inhibitor, used in the treatment of breast and colorectal cancer.

Name: Celastrol
Information: Celastrol is a potent proteasome inhibitor for the chymotrypsin-like activity of a purified 20S proteasome with IC50 of 2.5 μM.

Name: Cetirizine DiHCl
Information: Cetirizine DiHCl is an antihistamine.

Name: Cilnidipine
Information: Cilnidipine is a unique L-type and N-type calcium channel blocker, used for high blood pressure treatment.

Name: Cilostazol
Information: Cilostazol is a potent cyclic nucleotide phosphodiesterase type 3 (PDE3) inhibitor with IC50 of 0.2 μM and inhibitor of adenosine uptake.

Name: Epothilone A
Information: Epothilone A is a paclitaxel-like microtubule-stabilizing agent with EC0.01 of 2 μM.

Name: Floxuridine
Information: Floxuridine is an antineoplastic antimetabolite, used in the treatment of colon carcinoma and colorectal cancer that has metastasized to the liver.

Name: Tegafur (FT-207, NSC 148958)
Information: Tegafur (FT-207, NSC 148958) is a substance being used in the treatment of some types of cancer.

Name: Ifosfamide
Information: Ifosfamide is a nitrogen mustard alkylating agent used in the treatment of cancer.

Name: Megestrol Acetate
Information: Megestrol acetate is a synthetic progestogen, used to treat breast cancer and loss of appetite.

Name: Mercaptopurine (6-MP)
Information: Mercaptopurine is a widely used antileukemic agent and immunosuppressive drug that inhibits de novo purine synthesis through incorporation of thiopurine methyltransferase metabolites into DNA and RNA.

Name: Pamidronate Disodium
Information: Pamidronate Disodium is a nitrogen containing bisphosphonate, used to prevent osteoporosis.

Name: Streptozotocin (STZ)
Information: Streptozotocin is a glucosamine-nitrosourea derivative, which is a methylating, carcinogenic, antibiotic and diabetes inducing agent.

Name: Ki16425
Information: Ki16425 is a competitive, potent and reversible antagonist to LPA1, LPA2 and LPA3 with Ki of 0.34 μM, 6.5 μM and 0.93 μM in RH7777 cell lines, respectively, shows no activity at LPA4, LPA5, LPA6.

Name: Costunolide
Information: Costunolide, a natural sesquiterpene compound with multiple biological activities inhibits FPTase with IC50 of 20 μM, also inhibits telomerase with IC50 of 65-90 μM.

Name: Dexamethasone (DHAP)
Information: Dexamethasone (DHAP) is a potent synthetic member of the glucocorticoid class of steroid drugs, and an interleukin receptor modulator that has anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressant effects.

Name: Doxazosin Mesylate
Information: Doxazosin, a quinazoline-derivative, selectively antagonizes postsynaptic α1-adrenergic receptors, used in the treatment of high blood pressure and urinary retention associated with benign prostatic hyperplasia.

Name: Edaravone
Information: Edaravone is a novel potent free radical scavenger that has been clinically used to reduce the neuronal damage following ischemic stroke.

Name: Etodolac
Information: Etodolac is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) and a COX inhibitor, used for the treatment of inflammation and pain.

Name: Etomidate
Information: Etomidate is a GABAA receptor agonist, used as a short-acting anaesthetic agent or sedative.

Name: Felbamate
Information: Felbamate (Felbatol) is an anticonvulsant drug used in the treatment of epilepsy NMDAR antagonist.

Name: Fluconazole
Information: Fluconazole is a fungal lanosterol 14 alpha-demethylase inhibitor, which thereby prevents the formation of ergosterol,used in the treatment and prevention of superficial and systemic fungal infections.

Name: Flumazenil
Information: Flumazenil is a competitive GABAA receptor antagonist, used in the treatment of benzodiazepine overdoses.

Name: Fluoxetine HCl
Information: Fluoxetine is a selective serotonin-reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) at the neuronal membrane, used in the treatment of depression.

Name: Flupirtine maleate
Information: Flupirtine maleate is the salt form of Flupirtine, which is a centrally acting non-opioid analgesia, is a selective neuronal potassium channel opener that also has NMDA receptor antagonist properties.

Name: Fluvoxamine maleate
Information: Fluvoxamine Maleate is a selective serotonin (5-HT) reuptake inhibitor (SSRI), used in the treatment of obsessive-compulsive disorder.

Name: Gabapentin HCl
Information: Gabapentin HCl is a GABA analogue, used to treat seizures and neuropathic pain.

Name: Galanthamine HBr
Information: Galanthamine is an AChE inhibitor with IC50 of 0.35 μM, exhibits 50-fold selectivity against butyryl-cholinesterase.

Name: Gatifloxacin
Information: Gatifloxacin is an antibiotic of the fourth-generation fluoroquinolone family, and inhibits the bacterial enzymes DNA gyrase and topoisomerase IV.

Name: Genistein
Information: Genistein, a phytoestrogen found in soy products, is a highly specific inhibitor of protein tyrosine kinase (PTK) which blocks the mitogenic effect mediated by EGF on NIH-3T3 cells with IC50 of 12μM or by insulin with IC50 of 19 μM.

Name: Ginkgolide B
Information: Ginkgolide B is a PAFR antagonist with IC50 of 3.6 μM.

Name: Glimepiride
Information: Glimepiride is a potent Kir6.2/SUR inhibitor with IC50 of 3.0 nM, 5.4 nM, and 7.3 nM for SUR1, SUR2A and SUR2B, used in the treatment of type 2 diabetes mellitus.

Name: Granisetron HCl
Information: Granisetron is a serotonin 5-HT3 receptor antagonist,used to treat chemotherapy-induced nausea and vomiting.

Name: Heparin sodium
Information: Heparin sodium, a sulfated polysaccharide belonging to the family of glycosaminoglycans, has numerous important biological activities associated with its interaction with diverse proteins, used as an anticoagulant.

Name: Ivermectin
Information: Ivermectin is a glutamate-gated chloride channel (GluCls) activator, used as a broad-spectrum antiparasitic drug.

Name: TG100-115
Information: TG100-115 is a PI3Kγ/δ inhibitor with IC50 of 83 nM/235 nM, with little effect on PI3Kα/β. Phase 1/2.

Name: Ketoconazole
Information: Ketoconazole inhibits cyclosporine oxidase and testosterone 6 beta-hydroxylase with IC50 of 0.19 mM and 0.22 mM, respectively.

Name: Lansoprazole
Information: Lansoprazole is a proton-pump inhibitor (PPI) which prevents the stomach from producing gastric acid.

Name: Levetiracetam
Information: Levetiracetam is an anticonvulsant medication used to treat epilepsy.

Name: Lidocaine
Information: Lidocaine is a selective inverse peripheral histamine H1-receptor agonist with an IC50 of >32 μM.

Name: Loratadine
Information: Loratadine is a histamine H1 receptor antagonist, used to treat allergies. Also acts as a selective inhibitor of B(0)AT2 with IC50 of 4 μM.

Name: Losartan Potassium (DuP 753)
Information: Losartan is an angiotensin II receptor antagonist, competes with the binding of angiotensin II to AT1 receptors with IC50 of 20 nM.

Name: GSK1059615
Information: GSK1059615 is a dual inhibitor of PI3Kα/β/δ/γ (reversible) and mTOR with IC50 of 0.4 nM/0.6 nM/2 nM/5 nM and 12 nM, respectively. Phase 1.

Name: Glesatinib?(MGCD265)
Information: Glesatinib?(MGCD265) is a potent, multi-target and ATP-competitive inhibitor of c-Met and VEGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 1 nM, 3 nM/3 nM/4 nM, respectively also inhibits Ron and Tie2. Phase 1/2.

Name: Rigosertib (ON-01910)
Information: Rigosertib (ON-01910) is a non-ATP-competitive inhibitor of PLK1 with IC50 of 9 nM in a cell-free assay. It shows 30-fold greater selectivity against Plk2 and no activity to Plk3. Phase 3.

Name: Patupilone (EPO906, Epothilone B)
Information: Patupilone (EPO906, Epothilone B) is a paclitaxel-like microtubule-stabilizing agent with EC0.01 of 1.8 μM. Phase 2.

Name: BMS-707035
Information: BMS-707035 is a specific HIV-I integrase (IN) inhibitor with IC50 of 15 nM. Phase 2.

Name: Amonafide
Information: Amonafide produces protein-associated DNA-strand breaks through a topoisomerase II-mediated reaction, but does not produce topoisomerase I-mediated DNA cleavage. Phase 3.

Name: Acitretin
Information: Acitretin is a second generation retinoid used for psoriasis.

Name: Bafetinib (INNO-406)
Information: Bafetinib (INNO-406) is a potent and selective dual Bcr-Abl/Lyn inhibitor with IC50 of 5.8 nM/19 nM in cell-free assays, does not inhibit the phosphorylation of the T315I mutant and is less potent to PDGFR and c-Kit. Phase 2.

Name: Biapenem
Information: Biapenem is a carbapenem antibiotic with activity against both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacterial strains.

Name: Cefoselis Sulfate
Information: Cefoselis is a widely used beta-lactam antibiotic.

Name: Daptomycin
Information: Daptomycin is a novel antibiotic with rapid in vitro bactericidal activity against gram-positive organisms.

Name: Doripenem Hydrate
Information: Doripenem Hydrate is an ultra-broad-spectrum injectable antibiotic, used to treat complicated intra-abdominal infections and complicated urinary tract infections.

Name: Dorzolamide HCl
Information: Dorzolamide HCl is a water-soluble, potent inhibitor of human carbonic anhydrase II and IV with Ki of 1.9 nM and 31 nM, respectively, used as anti-glaucoma agent.

Name: Gestodene
Information: Gestodene is a progestogen hormonal contraceptive.

Name: Drospirenone
Information: Drospirenone is a synthetic progestin that is an analog to spironolactone.

Name: Ruxolitinib (INCB018424)
Information: Ruxolitinib (INCB018424) is the first potent, selective, JAK1/2 inhibitor to enter the clinic with IC50 of 3.3 nM/2.8 nM in cell-free assays, >130-fold selectivity for JAK1/2 versus JAK3.

Name: Isotretinoin
Information: It was developed to be used as a chemotherapy medication for the treatment of brain cancer, pancreatic cancer and more.

Name: Lopinavir
Information: Lopinavir is a potent HIV protease inhibitor with Ki of 1.3 pM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Meropenem
Information: Meropenem is an ultra-broad spectrum injectable antibiotic.

Name: Mianserin HCl
Information: Mianserin is an potent antagonist of H1 histamine receptor and 5-HT serotonin receptors, used for the treatment of depression.

Name: Mizoribine
Information: Mizoribine is an imidazole nucleoside, selectively inhibits inosine monophosphate synthetase and guanosine monophosphate synthetase.

Name: Mosapride Citrate
Information: Mosapride Citrate is a gastroprokinetic agent that acts as a selective 5HT4 agonist.

Name: Nafamostat Mesylate
Information: Nafamostat mesilate is a synthetic serine protease inhibitor, used as an anticoagulant during hemodialysis.

Name: Naftopidil DiHCl
Information: Naftopidil DiHCl is a selective 5-HT1A and α1-adrenergic receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.1 μM and 0.2 μM, respectively.

Name: Omeprazole
Information: Omeprazole is a proton pump inhibitor, used to treat dyspepsia, peptic ulcer disease, gastroesophageal reflux disease, laryngopharyngeal reflux, and Zollinger–Ellison syndrome.

Name: Ondansetron HCl
Information: Ondansetron is a serotonin 5-HT3 receptor antagonist, used to prevent nausea and vomiting caused by cancer chemotherapy, and radiation therapy.

Name: Oxcarbazepine
Information: Oxcarbazepine inhibits the binding of [3H]BTX to sodium channels with IC50 of 160 μM and also inhibits the influx of 22Na+ into rat brain synaptosomes with IC50 about 100 μM.

Name: Pelitinib (EKB-569)
Information: Pelitinib (EKB-569) is a potent irreversible EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 38.5 nM. Phase2.

Name: Pirarubicin
Information: Pirarubicin is an anthracycline antibiotic, and also a DNA/RNA synthesis inhibitor by intercalating into DNA and interacts with topoisomerase II, used as an antineoplastic agent.

Name: Pizotifen Malate
Information: Pizotifen Malate is a benzocycloheptane based agent used for recurrent migraine headaches.

Name: Polymyxin B sulphate
Information: Polymyxin B is an antibiotic primarily used for resistant gram-negative infections.

Name: Resveratrol
Information: Resveratrol has a wide spectrum of targets including cyclooxygenases(i.e. COX, IC50=1.1 μM), lipooxygenases（LOX, IC50=2.7 μM）, kinases, sirtuins and other proteins. It has anti-cancer, anti-inflammatory, blood-sugar-lowering and other beneficial cardiovascular effects.

Name: Rocuronium Bromide
Information: Rocuronium Bromide is a competitive AchR antagonist, used in modern anaesthesia.

Name: Stavudine (d4T)
Information: Stavudine (d4T) is a nucleoside analog reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NARTI) active against HIV.

Name: Teicoplanin
Information: Teicoplanin is a glycopeptide antibiotic, used to treat serious infections caused by Gram-positive bacteria.

Name: Tenofovir Disoproxil Fumarate
Information: Tenofovir Disoproxil Fumarate belongs to a class of antiretroviral drugs, it inhibits the activity of HIV reverse transcriptase by competing with the natural substrate deoxyadenosine 5’-triphosphate and, after incorporation into DNA, by DNA chain termination.

Name: Tenofovir
Information: Tenofovir blocks reverse transcriptase and hepatitis B virus infections.

Name: Tigecycline
Information: Tigecycline is bacteriostatic and is a protein synthesis inhibitor by binding to the 30S ribosomal subunit of bacteria and thereby blocking entry of Aminoacyl-tRNA into the A site of the ribosome during prokaryotic translation.

Name: Trilostane
Information: Trilostane is an inhibitor of 3β-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase used in the treatment of Cushing’s syndrome.

Name: Vecuronium Bromide
Information: Vecuronium is a non-depolarizing neuromuscular blocking agent, used for skeletal muscle relaxation during surgery.

Name: Bimatoprost
Information: Bimatoprost is a prostaglandin analog used topically (as eye drops) to control the progression of glaucoma and in the management of ocular hypertension.

Name: Linezolid
Information: Linezolid is a synthetic antibiotic used for the treatment of serious infections.

Name: Alfuzosin HCl
Information: Alfuzosin HCl is an alpha1 receptor antagonist used to treat benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH).

Name: Clopidogrel
Information: Clopidogrel is an oral, thienopyridine class antiplatelet agent.

Name: Prazosin HCl
Information: Prazosin HCl is a competitive alpha-1 adrenoceptor antagonist, used to treat high blood pressure or benign prostatic hyperplasia.

Name: Ranolazine 2HCl
Information: Ranolazine 2HCl is a calcium uptake inhibitor via the sodium/calcium channal, used to treat chronic angina.

Name: Repaglinide
Information: Repaglinide is a potassium channel blocker, which lowers blood glucose by stimulating the release of insulin from the pancreas, used the treatment of type II diabetes.

Name: Risedronate Sodium
Information: Risedronate Sodium, a nitrogen-containing bisphosphonate, inhibits osteoclast-mediated bone resorption and modulates bone metabolism, used in the treatment of osteoporosis.

Name: Rolipram
Information: The PDE4 selective inhibitor, rolipram, inhibited immunopurified PDE4B and PDE4D activities similarly, with IC50 values of approx. 130 nM and 240 nM respectively an anti-inflammatory agent.

Name: Sildenafil Citrate
Information: Sildenafil Citrate, a selective inhibitor of cyclic guanosine monophosphate (cGMP)-specific phosphodiesterase type 5 (PDE5), is a well-tolerated and highly effective treatment for erectile dysfunction.

Name: Sumatriptan Succinate
Information: Sumatriptan Succinate is a triptan sulfa drug containing a sulfonamide group for the treatment of migraine headaches.

Name: Tamsulosin
Information: Tamsulosin is a selective α1 receptor antagonist that has preferential selectivity for the α1A receptor in the prostate versus the α1B receptor in the blood vessels.

Name: Tianeptine sodium
Information: Tianeptine sodium is a selective serotonin reuptake enhancer (SSRE), used for treating major depressive episodes.

Name: Tizanidine HCl
Information: Tizanidine HCl is an α2-adrenergic receptor agonist and inhibits neurotransmitter release from CNS noradrenergic neurons.

Name: Topiramate
Information: Topiramate is a mutil-targeted inhibitor, including voltage-gated sodium channel and calcium channel, AMPA/kainate receptor and carbonic anhydrase, used to treat epilepsy.

Name: Tranilast
Information: Tranilast?is an antiallergic drug by inhibiting lipid mediator and cytokine release from inflammatory cells, used for the treatment of allergic disorders such as asthma, allergic rhinitis and atopic dermatitis.

Name: Varenicline Tartrate
Information: Varenicline Tartrate is a nicotinic AChR partial agonist, used to treat nicotine addiction.

Name: Venlafaxine HCl
Information: Venlafaxine HCl is an arylalkanolamine serotonin-norepinephrine reuptake inhibitor (SNRI), used to treat major depressive disorder (MDD), generalised anxiety disorder (GAD), panic disorder and social phobia.

Name: Voriconazole
Information: Voriconazole is a new triazole derivative similar to fluconazole and itraconazole that acts by inhibiting fungal cytochrome P-450-dependent, 14-alpha-sterol demethylase-mediated synthesis of ergosterol.

Name: Zileuton
Information: Zileuton is an orally active inhibitor of 5-lipoxygenase, and thus inhibits leukotrienes (LTB4, LTC4, LTD4, and LTE4) formation, used to decrease the symptoms of asthma.

Name: Ziprasidone HCl
Information: Ziprasidone HCl is a novel and potent dopamine and serotonin (5-HT) receptor antagonist, used in the treatment of schizophrenia and bipolar disorder.

Name: Zonisamide
Information: Zonisamide is a voltage-dependent sodium channel and T-type calcium channel blocker, used as an antiepileptic drug.

Name: Ispinesib (SB-715992)
Information: Ispinesib (SB-715992) is a potent, specific and reversible inhibitor of kinesin spindle protein (KSP) with Ki app of 1.7 nM in a cell-free assay, no inhibition to CENP-E, RabK6, MCAK, MKLP1, KHC or Kif1A. Phase 2.

Name: Tipifarnib
Information: Tipifarnib (R115777) is a potent and specific farnesyltransferase (FTase) inhibitor with IC50 of 0.6 nM, its anti-proliferative effects are most prominent in H-ras or N-ras mutant cells. Phase 3.

Name: PHA-680632
Information: PHA-680632 is potent inhibitor of Aurora A, Aurora B and Aurora C with IC50 of 27 nM, 135 nM and 120 nM, respectively. It has 10- to 200-fold higher IC50 for FGFR1, FLT3, LCK, PLK1, STLK2, and VEGFR2/3.

Name: Cilomilast
Information: Cilomilast is a potent PDE4 inhibitor with IC50 of about 110 nM, has anti-inflammatory activity and low central nervous system activity. Phase 3.

Name: Zibotentan (ZD4054)
Information: Zibotentan (ZD4054) is a specific Endothelin (ET)A antagonist with IC50 of 21 nM, exhibiting no activity at ETB. Phase 3.

Name: Atazanavir Sulfate
Information: Atazanavir Sulfate is a HIV protease inhibitor with Ki of 2.66 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: VX-745
Information: VX-745 is a potent and selective inhibitor of p38α with IC50 of 10 nM, 22-fold greater selectivity versus p38β and no inhibition to p38γ.

Name: SP600125
Information: SP600125 is a broad-spectrum JNK inhibitor for JNK1, JNK2 and JNK3 with IC50 of 40 nM, 40 nM and 90 nM in cell-free assays, respectively 10-fold greater selectivity against MKK4, 25-fold greater selectivity against MKK3, MKK6, PKB, and PKCα, and 100-fold selectivity against ERK2, p38, Chk1, EGFR etc.

Name: AZD6482
Information: AZD6482 is a PI3Kβ inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM, 8-, 87- and 109-fold more selective to PI3Kβ than PI3Kδ, PI3Kα and PI3Kγ in cell-free assays. Phase 1.

Name: Marbofloxacin
Information: Marbofloxacin is a potent antibiotic inhibiting bacterial DNA replication.

Name: http://selleckchem.com/products/.html
Information: Moxifloxacin is a fourth-generation synthetic fluoroquinolone antibacterial agent.

Name: Calcitriol
Information: Calcitriol is a nonselective vitamin D receptor activator/agonist(VDRA), exhibiting a 10-fold higher vitamin D receptor (VDR) binding affinity(IC50=0.4 nM) than the selective VDRA paricalcitol.

Name: Doxercalciferol
Information: Doxercalciferol is a synthetic vitamin D2 analog, suppressing parathyroid synthesis and secretion, used to treat secondary hyperparathyroidism and metabolic bone disease.

Name: Alfacalcidol
Information: Alfacalcidol is a non-selective VDR activator medication.

Name: Orantinib (TSU-68, SU6668)
Information: Orantinib (TSU-68, SU6668) has greatest potency against PDGFR autophosphorylation with Ki of 8 nM in a cell-free assay, but also strongly inhibits Flk-1 and FGFR1 trans-phosphorylation, little activity against IGF-1R, Met, Src, Lck, Zap70, Abl and CDK2 does not inhibit EGFR. Phase 3.

Name: Safinamide Mesylate
Information: Safinamide Mesylate is mesylate salt of Safinamide, selectively and reversibly inhibits MAO-B with IC50 of 98 nM, exhibits 5918-fold selectivity against MAO-A. Phase 3.

Name: Pimasertib (AS-703026)
Information: Pimasertib (AS-703026) is a highly selective, potent, ATP non-competitive allosteric inhibitor of MEK1/2 with IC50 of 5 nM-2 μM in MM cell lines. Phase 2.

Name: Lomibuvir (VX-222, VCH-222)
Information: Lomibuvir (VX-222, VCH-222) is a novel, potent and selective inhibitor of HCV polymerase with IC50 of 0.94-1.2 μM, 15.3-fold less effective for mutant M423T, and 108-fold less effective for mutant I482L. Phase 2.

Name: Zosuquidar (LY335979) 3HCl
Information: Zosuquidar (LY335979) 3HCl is a potent modulator of P-glycoprotein-mediated multi-drug resistance with Ki of 60 nM in a cell-free assay. Phase 3.

Name: Daclatasvir (BMS-790052)
Information: Daclatasvir (BMS-790052) is a highly selective inhibitor of HCV NS5A with EC50 of 9-50 pM, for a broad range of HCV replicon genotypes and the JFH-1 genotype 2a infectious virus in cell culture. Phase 3.

Name: Iloperidone
Information: Iloperidone is a dopamine (D2)/serotonin (5-HT2) receptor antagonist, used for the treatment of schizophrenia.

Name: HMN-214
Information: HMN-214 is a prodrug of HMN-176, which alters the cellular spatial orientation of Plk1.

Name: AEE788 (NVP-AEE788)
Information: AEE788 (NVP-AEE788) is a potent inhibitor of EGFR and HER2/ErbB2 with IC50 of 2 nM and 6 nM, less potent to VEGFR2/KDR, c-Abl, c-Src, and Flt-1, does not inhibit Ins-R, IGF-1R, PKCα and CDK1. Phase 1/2.

Name: PHA-793887
Information: PHA-793887 is a novel and potent inhibitor of CDK2, CDK5 and CDK7 with IC50 of 8 nM, 5 nM and 10 nM. It is greater than 6-fold more selective for CDK2, 5, and 7 than CDK1, 4, and 9. Phase 1.

Name: Naratriptan HCl
Information: Naratriptan HCl is a triptan agent that is used for the treatment of migraine headaches.

Name: Ponatinib (AP24534)
Information: Ponatinib (AP24534) is a novel, potent multi-target inhibitor of Abl, PDGFRα, VEGFR2, FGFR1 and Src with IC50 of 0.37 nM, 1.1 nM, 1.5 nM, 2.2 nM and 5.4 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Fludarabine
Information: Fludarabine is a STAT1 activation inhibitor which causes a specific depletion of STAT1 protein (and mRNA) but not of other STATs. Also a DNA synthesis inhibitor in vascular smooth muscle cells.

Name: Ralimetinib (LY2228820)
Information: Ralimetinib (LY2228820) is a novel and potent inhibitor of p38 MAPK with IC50 of 7 nM in a cell-free assay, does not alter p38 MAPK activation. Phase 1/2.

Name: Pralatrexate
Information: Pralatrexate is an antifolate, and structurally a folate analog. Its IC50 is < 300 nM in some cell lines.

Name: Cefaclor
Information: Cefaclor is a cephalosporin antibiotic.

Name: Betamethasone
Information: Betamethasone is a glucocorticoid steroid with anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressive properties.

Name: Mycophenolate Mofetil
Information: Mycophenolate Mofetil is a non-competitive, selective and reversible inhibitor of inosine monophosphate dehydrogenase I/II with IC50 of 39 nM and 27 nM, respectively.

Name: Cephalexin
Information: Cephalexin is an antibiotic that can treat a number of bacterial infections.

Name: Dyphylline
Information: Dyphylline is a xanthine derivative with bronchodilator and vasodilator effects.

Name: Aztreonam
Information: Aztreonam is a synthetic monocyclic beta-lactam antibiotic, used to treat Gram-negative aerobic bacteria infection.

Name: Perindopril Erbumine
Information: Perindopril Erbumine is a potent ACE inhibitor with IC50 of 1.05 nM.

Name: Irbesartan
Information: Irbesartan (SR-47436, BMS-186295) is a highly potent and specific angiotensin II type 1 (AT1) receptor antagonist with IC50 of 1.3 nM.

Name: Alprostadil
Information: Alprostadil is used as a drug in the treatment of erectile dysfunction and has vasodilatory properties. It is a Prostaglandin Analog and Prostaglandin E1 Agonist.

Name: Norfloxacin
Information: Norfloxacin is a broad-spectrum antibiotic.

Name: Lactulose
Information: Lactulose, a disaccharide composed of galactose and fructose, is a stimulator of health-promoting bacterium growth in the gastrointestinal tract, used to treat chronic constipation and hepatic encephalopathy.

Name: Tadalafil
Information: Tadalafil is a PDE-5 inhibitor with IC50 of 1.8 nM in a cell-free assay. Tadalafil is at least 9000 times more selective for PDE5 than most of the other families of PDEs, with the exception of PDE11. It can partial inhibits PDE11

Name: Cyclosporine
Information: Cyclosporine is a calcineurin phosphatase pathway inhibitor, used as an immunosuppressant drug to prevent rejection in organ transplantation.

Name: Pracinostat (SB939)
Information: Pracinostat (SB939) is a potent pan-HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 40-140 nM with exception for HDAC6. It has no activity against the class III isoenzyme SIRT I. Phase 2.

Name: Cidofovir
Information: Cidofovir suppresses virus replication by selective inhibition of viral DNA synthesis.

Name: Natamycin
Information: Natamycin, a natural and versatile anti-fungal agent during fermentation by the bacterium Streptomyces natalensis, commonly found in soil with little to no flavour interference

Name: Ibuprofen Lysine
Information: Ibuprofen Lysine is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug.

Name: CCT129202
Information: CCT129202 is an ATP-competitive pan-Aurora inhibitor for Aurora A, Aurora B and Aurora C with IC50 of 0.042 μM, 0.198 μM and 0.227 μM, respectively. It is less potent to FGFR3, GSK3β, PDGFRβ, etc.

Name: AT7519
Information: AT7519 is a multi-CDK inhibitor for CDK1, 2, 4, 6 and 9 with IC50 of 10-210 nM. It is less potent to CDK3 and little active to CDK7. Phase 2.

Name: Adavosertib （MK-1775）
Information: MK-1775 is a potent and selective Wee1 inhibitor with IC50 of 5.2 nM in a cell-free assay hinders G2 DNA damage checkpoint. Phase 2.

Name: Quizartinib (AC220)
Information: Quizartinib (AC220) is a second-generation FLT3 inhibitor for Flt3(ITD/WT) with IC50 of 1.1 nM/4.2 nM in MV4-11 and RS411 cells, respectively, 10-fold more selective for Flt3 than KIT, PDGFRα, PDGFRβ, RET, and CSF-1R. Phase 3.

Name: LY2811376
Information: LY2811376 is the first orally available non-peptidic β-secretase(BACE1) inhibitor with IC50 of 239 nM-249 nM, that act to decrease Aβ secretion with EC50 of 300 nM, demonstrated to have 10-fold selectivity towards BACE1 over BACE2, and more than 50-fold inhibition over other aspartic proteases including cathepsin D, pepsin, or renin. Phase 1.

Name: AZD7762
Information: AZD7762 is a potent and selective inhibitor of Chk1 with IC50 of 5 nM in a cell-free assay. It is equally potent against Chk2 and less potent against CAM, Yes, Fyn, Lyn, Hck and Lck. Phase 1.

Name: R406 (free base)
Information: R406 (free base) is a potent Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 41 nM in a cell-free assay, strongly inhibits Syk but not Lyn, 5-fold less potent to Flt3. Phase 1.

Name: CP-673451
Information: CP-673451 is a selective inhibitor of PDGFRα/β with IC50 of 10 nM/1 nM in cell-free assays, exhibits >450-fold selectivity over other angiogenic receptors, has antiangiogenic and antitumor activity.

Name: DMXAA (Vadimezan)
Information: DMXAA (Vadimezan) is a vascular disrupting agents (VDA) and competitive inhibitor of DT-diaphorase with Ki of 20 μM and IC50 of 62.5 μM in cell-free assays, respectively. Phase 3.

Name: Telaprevir (VX-950)
Information: Telaprevir (VX-950) is an HCV NS3-4A serine protease inhibitor with IC50 of 0.35 μM.

Name: Saxagliptin
Information: Saxagliptin is a selective and reversible DPP4 inhibitor with IC50 of 26 nM.

Name: Selisistat (EX 527)
Information: Selisistat (EX 527) is a potent and selective SIRT1 inhibitor with IC50 of 38 nM in a cell-free assay, exhibits >200-fold selectivity against SIRT2 and SIRT3. Phase 2.

Name: Febuxostat
Information: Febuxostat is a selective xanthine oxidase inhibitor with Ki of 0.6 nM.

Name: Dapagliflozin
Information: Dapagliflozin is a potent and selective hSGLT2 inhibitor with EC50 of 1.1 nM, exhibiting 1200-fold selectivity over hSGLT1. Phase 4.

Name: Nebivolol HCl
Information: Nebivolol HCl selectively inhibits β1-adrenoceptor with IC50 of 0.8 nM.

Name: Pimobendan
Information: Pimobendan is a selective inhibitor of PDE3 with IC50 of 0.32 μM.

Name: AZD8055
Information: AZD8055 is a novel ATP-competitive mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 0.8 nM in MDA-MB-468 cells with excellent selectivity (?1,000-fold) against PI3K isoforms and ATM/DNA-PK. Phase 1.

Name: PHT-427
Information: PHT-427 is a dual Akt and PDPK1 inhibitor (high affinity binding for the PH domains of Akt and PDPK1) with Ki of 2.7 μM and 5.2 μM, respectively.

Name: KRN 633
Information: KRN 633 is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of VEGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 170 nM/160 nM/125 nM, weakly inhibits PDGFR-α/β and c-Kit, does not block the phosphorylation of FGFR-1, EGFR or c-Met in cell.

Name: AT7867
Information: AT7867 is a potent ATP-competitive inhibitor of Akt1/2/3 and p70S6K/PKA with IC50 of 32 nM/17 nM/47 nM and 85 nM/20 nM in cell-free assays, respectively little activity outside the AGC kinase family.

Name: BMS-777607
Information: BMS-777607 is a Met-related inhibitor for c-Met, Axl, Ron and Tyro3 with IC50 of 3.9 nM, 1.1 nM, 1.8 nM and 4.3 nM in cell-free assays, 40-fold more selective for Met-related targets versus Lck, VEGFR-2, and TrkA/B, and more than 500-fold greater selectivity versus all other receptor and non receptor kinases. Phase 1/2.

Name: VX-809 (Lumacaftor)
Information: VX-809 (Lumacaftor) acts to correct CFTR mutations common in cystic fibrosis by increasing mutant CFTR (F508del-CFTR) maturation,EC50 of 0.1 μM in fisher rat thyroid cells. Phase 3.

Name: Pomalidomide
Information: Pomalidomide inhibits LPS-induced TNF-α release with IC50 of 13 nM in PBMCs.

Name: Tazarotene
Information: Tazarotene is a retinoid prodrug of tazarotenic acid, which is a RAR agonist, used to treat psoriasis, acne, and sun damaged skin.

Name: Fasudil (HA-1077) HCl
Information: Fasudil(HA-1077), a potent and selective inhibitor of Rho kinase, displays less potent inhibiton over PKA, PKG, PKC and MLCK with Ki of 1.6, 1.6, 3.3, and 36 μM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Doramapimod (BIRB 796)
Information: Doramapimod (BIRB 796) is a pan-p38 MAPK inhibitor with IC50 of 38 nM, 65 nM, 200 nM and 520 nM for p38α/β/γ/δ in cell-free assays, and binds p38α with Kd of 0.1 nM in THP-1 cells, 330-fold greater selectivity versus JNK2, weak inhibition for c-RAF, Fyn and Lck, insignificant inhibition of ERK-1, SYK, IKK2.

Name: Sulfasalazine
Information: Sulfasalazine is a sulfa derivative of mesalazine, used as an anti-inflammatory agent to treat bowel disease and rheumatoid arthritis.

Name: Candesartan
Information: Candesartan is an angiotensin II receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.26 nM.

Name: Palbociclib (PD0332991) Isethionate
Information: Palbociclib (PD0332991) Isethionate is a highly selective inhibitor of CDK4/6 with IC50 of 11 nM/16 nM in cell-free assays. It shows no activity against CDK1/2/5, EGFR, FGFR, PDGFR, InsR, etc. Phase 3.

Name: Apixaban
Information: Apixaban is a highly selective, reversible inhibitor of Factor Xa with Ki of 0.08 nM and 0.17 nM in human and rabbit, respectively.

Name: Semagacestat (LY450139)
Information: Semagacestat (LY450139) is a γ-secretase blocker for Aβ42, Aβ40 and Aβ38 with IC50 of 10.9 nM, 12.1 nM and 12.0 nM, also inhibits Notch signaling with IC50 of 14.1 nM in H4 human glioma cell. Phase 3.

Name: Reserpine
Information: Reserpine is an inhibitor of multidrug efflux pumps, used as an antipsychotic and antihypertensive drug.

Name: Furosemide
Information: Furosemide is a potent NKCC2 (Na-K-2Cl symporter) inhibitor, used in the treatment of congestive heart failure and edema.

Name: Olmesartan Medoxomil
Information: Olmesartan Medoxomil (CS-866) is a selective angiotensin II type 1 (AT(1)) receptor antagonist, used in the treatment of high blood pressure.

Name: Cefdinir
