Information: Cefdinir is an oral cephalosporin antibiotic, used to treat bacterial infections in many different parts of the body.

Name: Clotrimazole
Information: Clotrimazole alters the permeability of the fungal cell wall by inhibiting the biosynthesis of ergosterol, used in the treatment of fungal infections.

Name: Rizatriptan Benzoate
Information: Rizatriptan Benzoate is an agonist at serotonin 5-HT1B and 5-HT1D receptors, used to treat acute migraine attacks.

Name: Pyridostigmine Bromide
Information: Pyridostigmine Bromide is a parasympathomimetic and a reversible cholinesterase inhibitor.

Name: Methimazole
Information: Methimazole is an antithyroid medicine.

Name: Metolazone
Information: Metolazone is a diuretic that primarily used to treat congestive heart failure and high blood pressure.

Name: Cefoperazone
Information: Cefoperazone is a cephalosporin antibiotic for inhibition of rMrp2-mediated [3H]E217βG uptake with IC50 of 199 μM.

Name: Silodosin
Information: Silodosin is a highly selective α1A-adrenoceptor antagonist, used in treatment of benign prostatic hyperplasia.

Name: Riluzole
Information: Riluzole is a glutamate release inhibitor with neuroprotective, anticonvulsant, anxiolytic and anesthetic qualities.

Name: Risperidone
Information: Risperidone is a mutil-targeted antagonist for dopamine, serotonin, adrenergic and histamine receptors, used to treat schizophrenia and bipolar disorder.

Name: Sulfapyridine
Information: Sulfapyridine is a sulfonamide antibacterial.

Name: Sulfameter
Information: Sulfameter is a long-acting sulfonamide antibacterial.

Name: Prilocaine
Information: Prilocaine is a local anesthetic of the amino amide type. It acts on sodium channels on the neuronal cell membrane, limiting the spread of seizure activity and reducing seizure propagation.

Name: Darunavir Ethanolate
Information: Darunavir Ethanolate (DRV) is a nonpeptidic HIV protease inhibitor, used to treat HIV infection.

Name: Prednisone
Information: Prednisone (Adasone) is a synthetic corticosteroid agent that is particularly effective as an immunosuppressant compound.

Name: Acetylcysteine
Information: Acetylcysteine(N-acetyl-l-cysteine) is a ROS(reactive oxygen species) inhibitor that antagonizes the activity of proteasome inhibitors. It is also a tumor necrosis factor production inhibitor, used mainly as a mucolytic, protects against acetaminophen overdose-induced hepatotoxicity by maintaining or restoring hepatic concentrations of glutathione.

Name: Alendronate sodium trihydrate
Information: Alendronate sodium trihydrate, a nitrogen-containing bisphosphonate, is a potent inhibitor of bone resorption used for the treatment and prevention of osteoporosis.

Name: Ethinyl Estradiol
Information: Ethinyl Estradiol is an orally bio-active estrogen used in almost all modern formulations of combined oral contraceptive pills.

Name: Naproxen Sodium
Information: Naproxen Sodium is a COX inhibitor for COX-1 and COX-2 with IC50 of 8.7 μM and 5.2 μM, respectively.

Name: Nitazoxanide
Information: Nitazoxanide is a synthetic nitrothiazolyl-salicylamide derivative and an antiprotozoal agent. (IC50 for canine influenza virus ranges from 0.17 to 0.21 μM)

Name: Triamcinolone Acetonide
Information: Triamcinolone acetonide is a synthetic glucocorticoid, used in the symptomatic treatment of inflammation.

Name: Orlistat
Information: Orlistat is a general lipase inhibitor with IC50 of 122 ng/ml for PL from human duodenal juice.

Name: Allopurinol
Information: Allopurinol is a purine analog inhibitor of the enzyme xanthine oxidase, used to treat gout or kidney stones, and to decrease levels of uric acid.

Name: Allopurinol Sodium
Information: Allopurinol Sodium is a xanthine oxidase inhibitor with an IC50 of 7.82±0.12 μM.

Name: Zafirlukast
Information: Zafirlukast is an oral leukotriene receptor antagonist (LTRA), used to prevent asthma symptoms.

Name: Erythromycin
Information: Erythromycin is a macrolide antibiotic that has an antimicrobial spectrum similar to or slightly wider than that of penicillin (IC50=1.5 μg/ml).

Name: Amphotericin B
Information: Amphotericin B (AmB) is an amphipathic polyene antibiotic which permeabilizes ergosterol-containing membranes.

Name: Ibuprofen
Information: Ibuprofen (Dolgesic) is an anti-inflammatory inhibitor targeting COX-1 and COX-2 with IC50 of 13 μM and 370 μM, respectively.

Name: Amprenavir
Information: Amprenavir is a potent PXR-selective agonist, and an HIV protease inhibitor, used to treat HIV.

Name: Albendazole
Information: Albendazole is a member of the benzimidazole compounds used as a drug indicated for the treatment of a variety of worm infestations.

Name: Chlorothiazide
Information: Chlorothiazide is a diuretic and antihypertensive. (IC50=3.8 mM)

Name: Methyldopa
Information: Methyldopa (Aldomet) is a DOPA decarboxylase competitive inhibitor with an ED50 of 21.8 mg/kg.

Name: Ursodiol
Information: Ursodiol reduces cholesterol absorption and is used to dissolve (cholesterol) gallstones. (IC50=0.22 μM)

Name: Nitrofural
Information: Nitrofural is a topical anti-infective agent with an IC50 of 22.83 ± 1.2 μM. (Rat LD50 = 590 mg/kg)

Name: Ketoprofen
Information: Ketoprofen is a dual COX1/2 inhibitor, used as a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug to treat arthritis-related inflammatory pains.

Name: Ketorolac
Information: Ketorolac (Ketorolac tromethamine) is a non-selective COX inhibitor of COX-1 and COX-2 with IC50 of 1.23 μM and 3.50 μM, respectively.

Name: Adenosine
Information: Adenosine is a nucleoside composed of a molecule of adenine attached to a ribose sugar molecule (ribofuranose) moiety via a β-N9-glycosidic bond.

Name: Cytarabine
Information: Cytarabine is an antimetabolic agent and DNA synthesis inhibitor with IC50 of 16 nM in wild-type CCRF-CEM cells.

Name: Zolmitriptan
Information: Zolmitriptan is a novel and highly selective 5-HT(1B/1D) receptor agonist, used in the treatment of acute migraines.

Name: Telbivudine
Information: Telbivudine is a potent, and selective HBV reverse transcriptase inhibitor, used to treat HBV infection.

Name: Monobenzone
Information: Monobenzone is a compound used as a topical agent for medical depigmentation. It can specifically block tyrosinase.

Name: Tretinoin
Information: Tretinoin, which is a ligand for both the retinoic acid receptor (RAR) and the retinoid X receptor (RXR), can induce granulocytic differentiation and apoptosis in acute promyelocytic leukemia (APL) cells.

Name: Phenylbutazone
Information: Phenylbutazone is used as a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agent for the treatment of chronic pain, including the symptoms of arthritis.

Name: Ezetimibe
Information: Ezetimibe is a potent, selective, cholesterol absorption inhibitor, used to lower cholesterol.

Name: Enalaprilat Dihydrate
Information: Enalaprilat is an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor with IC50 of 1.94 nM.

Name: Dofetilide
Information: Dofetilide is a selective potassium channel ((hERG)) blocker, used as a Class III antiarrhythmic drug.

Name: Isradipine
Information: Isradipine is a potent and selective L-type voltage-gated calcium channel blocker, used to treat high blood pressure.

Name: Estrone
Information: Estrone is an estrogenic hormone.

Name: Flucytosine
Information: Flucytosine (5-Fluorocytosine, 5-FC) is an antifungal drug with IC50 of 0.93 μM in C. albicans.

Name: Trichlormethiazide
Information: Trichlormethiazide is a diuretic with properties similar to those of hydrochlorothiazide.

Name: Loteprednol etabonate
Information: Loteprednol etabonate is a potent glucocorticoid receptor agonist, used in treatment of inflammation of the eye due to allergies.

Name: （6-）ε-Aminocaproic acid
Information: （6-）ε-?Aminocaproic acid is a derivative and analogue of the amino acid lysine.

Name: Aminoglutethimide
Information: Aminoglutethimide is an aromatase inhibitor with IC50 of 10 μM.

Name: Aminophylline
Information: Aminophylline is a competitive nonselective phosphodiesterase inhibitor with an IC50 of 0.12 mM and also a nonselective adenosine receptor antagonist.

Name: Lubiprostone
Information: Lubiprostone is an activator of ClC-2 chloride channels, used in the management of idiopathic chronic constipation.

Name: Amorolfine HCl
Information: Amorolfine HCl is an antifungal reagent.

Name: Chloramphenicol
Information: Chloramphenicol is a bacteriostatic by inhibiting protein synthesis.

Name: Flurbiprofen
Information: Flurbiprofen is a member of the phenylalkanoic acid derivative family of non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs).

Name: Disulfiram
Information: Disulfiram is a specific inhibitor of aldehyde-dehydrogenase (ALDH1), used for the treatment of chronic alcoholism by producing an acute sensitivity to alcohol.

Name: Mesalamine
Information: Mesalamine is a specific inhibitor of TNFα-induced IKK activity, used to treat inflammatory bowel disease.

Name: Ipratropium Bromide
Information: Ipratropium Bromide is an antagonist of M3 type muscarinic acetylcholine receptors, used for the treatment of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD).

Name: Sulfanilamide
Information: Sulfanilamide (Sulphanilamide) is a competitive inhibitor for bacterial enzyme dihydropteroate synthetase with IC50 of 320 μM.

Name: Betamethasone Dipropionate
Information: Betamethasone Dipropionate is a glucocorticoid steroid with anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressive abilities.

Name: Meprednisone
Information: Meprednisone is a glucocorticoid and a methylated derivative of prednisone.

Name: Betamethasone Valerate
Information: Betamethasone Valerate is a moderately potent glucocorticoid steroid with anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressive properties.

Name: Praziquantel
Information: Praziquantel is an anthelmintic effective against flatworms.

Name: Busulfan
Information: Busulfan is a cell cycle non-specific alkylating antineoplastic agent.

Name: Carbamazepine
Information: Carbamazepine (Carbatrol) is a sodium channel blocker with IC50 of 131 μM in rat brain synaptosomes.

Name: Hydrocortisone
Information: Hydrocortisone is a steroid hormone or glucocorticoid produced by the adrenal gland.

Name: Torsemide
Information: Torsemide is a pyridyl sulfonylurea with a chemical structure between that of traditional loop diuretics and Cl- channel blockers, used to treat hypertension.

Name: Desonide
Information: Desonide is a low potency topical corticosteroid.

Name: Didanosine
Information: Didanosine is a reverse transcriptase inhibitor with an IC50 of 0.49 μM.

Name: Divalproex Sodium
Information: Divalproex Sodium, consisting of a compound of sodium valproate and valproic acid in a 1:1 molar relationship in an enteric coated form, is a HDAC inhibitor, used in the treatment for epilepsy.

Name: Emtricitabine
Information: Emtricitabine (FTC) is a new nucleoside agent that has activity against both human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) and hepatitis B virus. It is a reverse transcriptase inhibitor. Intracellular half-life is 39 h.

Name: Progesterone
Information: Progesterone is an endogenous steroid hormone involved in the menstrual cycle, pregnancy, and embryogenesis of humans and other species. A potent agonist of the nuclear progesterone receptor (nPR) with Kd of 1 nM An agonist of the membrane progesterone receptors(mPRs) An antagonist of the σ1 receptor.

Name: Lamivudine
Information: Lamivudine is a potent nucleoside analog reverse transcriptase inhibitor, used for treatment of chronic HBV and HIV/AIDS. It works by blocking the HIV reverse transcriptase and hepatitis B virus polymerase.

Name: Eplerenone
Information: Eplerenone is a mineralocorticoid receptor antagonist, and blocks the action of aldosterone, used to control high blood pressure.

Name: Estradiol
Information: Estradiol, or more precisely, 17β-estradiol, is a human sex hormone and steroid, and the primary female sex hormone.

Name: Deferasirox
Information: Deferasirox is an iron chelator, also a cytochrome P450 3A4 inducer, Cytochrome P450 2C8 inhibitor, and Cytochrome P450 1A2 inhibitor.

Name: Piroxicam
Information: Piroxicam is a non-selective COX inhibitor, used in the treatment of rheumatoid and osteoarthritis.

Name: Gemcitabine
Information: Gemcitabine, a nucleic acid synthesis inhibitor, is a very potent and specific deoxycytidine analogue, used as chemotherapy.

Name: Glipizide
Information: Glipizide is used to treat high blood sugar levels caused by a type of diabetes mellitus called type 2 diabetes.

Name: Glyburide (Glibenclamide)
Information: Glyburide (Glibenclamide) is a known blocker of vascular ATP-sensitive K+ channels (KATP), used in the treatment of type 2 diabetes.

Name: Fomepizole
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Information: Fomepizole is a competitive inhibitor of alcohol dehydrogenase, the enzyme that catalyzes the initial steps in the metabolism of ethylene glycol and methanol to their toxic metabolites.

Name: Adefovir Dipivoxil
Information: Adefovir Dipivoxil is a reverse transcriptase inhibitor, used in the treatment of chronic hepatitis B virus (HBV).

Name: Zalcitabine
Information: Zalcitabine is a nucleoside analog HIV reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NARTI).

Name: Azathioprine
Information: Azathioprine is an immunosuppressive drug, inhibiting purine synthesis and GTP-binding protein Rac1 activation, used in the treatment of organ transplantation and autoimmune diseases.

Name: Indomethacin
Information: Indomethacin is a nonselective COX1 and COX2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.1 μg/mL and 5 μg/mL, respectively, used to reduce fever, pain, stiffness, and swelling.

Name: Paliperidone
Information: Paliperidone, the main active metabolite of Risperidone, is a potent serotonin-2A and dopamine-2 receptor antagonist, used in the treatment of schizophrenia.

Name: Terbinafine
Information: Terbinafine is used to treat infections caused by a fungus. It works by killing the fungus or preventing its growth.

Name: Levonorgestrel
Information: Levonorgestrel is a female hormone that prevents ovulation.

Name: Gemfibrozil
Information: Gemfibrozil is an activator of peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-alpha (PPARα), used for the treatment of hypercholesterolemia and hypertriglyceridemia.

Name: Indapamide
Information: Indapamide is a non-thiazide sulphonamide diuretic compound, generally used in the treatment of hypertension, as well as decompensated cardiac failure.

Name: Mitotane
Information: Mitotane, is an antineoplastic medication used in the treatment of adrenocortical carcinoma.

Name: Methylprednisolone
Information: Methylprednisolone is a synthetic glucocorticoid receptor agonist, used to achieve prompt suppression of inflammation.

Name: Meloxicam
Information: Meloxicam is a selective COX inhibitor, used to relieve pain and fever effects.

Name: Mesna
Information: Mesna, a sulfhydryl compound that is used to reduce the incidence of hemorrhagic cystitis associated with certain chemotherapeutic agents.

Name: Methocarbamol
Information: Methocarbamol is a carbonic anhydrase inhibitor, used as a central muscle relaxant to treat skeletal muscle spasms.

Name: Prednisolone
Information: Prednisolone is a synthetic glucocorticoid with anti-inflammatory and immunomodulating properties.

Name: Telmisartan
Information: Telmisartan is an angiotensin II receptor antagonist (ARB) used in the management of hypertension.

Name: Thiabendazole
Information: Thiabendazole inhibits the mitochondrial helminth-specific enzyme, fumarate reductase, with anthelminthic property, used as an anthelmintic and fungicide agent. It is a potent inhibitor of cytochrome P450 1A2 (CYP1A2).

Name: Guaifenesin
Information: Guaifenesin is an expectorant used to relieve chest congestion.

Name: Rifabutin
Information: Rifabutin is a semisynthetic ansamycin antibiotic, used in the treatment of Mycobacterium avium intracellulare (MAI) and tuberculosis.

Name: Nevirapine
Information: Nevirapine is a non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NNRTI) used to treat HIV-1 infection and AIDS.

Name: NEXIUM (esomeprazole magnesium)
Information: Esomeprazole Magnesium is a proton pump inhibitor to reduce gastric acid secretion.

Name: Nicotinic Acid
Information: Nicotinic Acid is a water-soluble vitamin belonging to the vitamin B family.

Name: Nimodipine
Information: Nimodipine is a dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker and an autophagy inhibitor, used in the treatment of high blood pressure.

Name: Nisoldipine
Information: Nisoldipine (Sular) is a calcium channel blocker belonging to the dihydropyridines class, specific for L-type Cav1.2 with IC50 of 10 nM.

Name: L-Glutamine
Information: L-Glutamine (Gln) is one of the 20 amino acids encoded by the standard genetic code and also a major respiratory fuel and substrate for nucleic acid synthesis in mammalian intestinal cells.

Name: Octocrylene
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Information: Octocrylene is an organic compound used as an ingredient in sunscreens and cosmetics.

Name: Gadodiamide Hydrate
Information: Gadodiamide Hydrate, a nonionic Gd3+ chelate, is frequently injected i.v. into magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) to enhance contrast.

Name: Oxybutynin
Information: Oxybutynin is a competitive antagonist of the M1, M2, and M3 subtypes of the muscarinic acetylcholine receptor, used to relieve urinary and bladder difficulties.

Name: Enoxacin
Information: Enoxacin is an oral broad-spectrum fluoroquinolone antibacterial agent by inhibiting bacterial DNA gyrase and topoisomerase IV, used to treat a wide variety of infections.

Name: Pitavastatin Calcium
Information: Pitavastatin calcium, a novel member of the medication class of statins, is a calcium salt formulation of pitavastatin which is a highly effective HMG-CoA reductase inhibitor.

Name: Rifapentine
Information: Rifapentine is an antibiotic, which inhibits DNA-dependent RNA polymerase activity, used to treat tuberculosis.

Name: Suprofen
Information: Suprofen is a dual COX-1/COX-2 inhibitor, used as a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory analgesic and antipyretic.

Name: Pyrazinamide
Information: Pyrazinamide is an agent used to treat tuberculosis.

Name: Quetiapine Fumarate
Information: Quetiapine Fumarate is an atypical antipsychotic used in the treatment of schizophrenia, bipolar I mania, bipolar II depression, bipolar I depression and shows affinity for various neurotransmitter receptors including serotonin, dopamine, histamine, and adrenergic receptors.

Name: Rifampin
Information: Rifampin is a DNA-dependent RNA polymerase inhibitor, used to treat a number of bacterial infections.

Name: Beta Carotene
Information: Beta Carotene is an organic compound and classified as a terpenoid. It is a precursor (inactive form) of vitamin A.

Name: Cefditoren Pivoxil
Information: Cefditoren Pivoxil is a broad-spectrum antibiotic against Gram-negative and Gram-positive bacteria.

Name: Sulfadiazine
Information: Sulfadiazine is a sulfonamide antibiotic.

Name: Chlorprothixene
Information: Chlorprothixene has strong binding affinities to dopamine and histamine receptors, such as D1, D2, D3, D5, H1, 5-HT2, 5-HT6 and 5-HT7, with Ki of 18 nM, 2.96 nM, 4.56 nM, 9 nM, 3.75 nM, 9.4 nM, 3 nM and 5.6 nM, respectively.

Name: Oxytetracycline (Terramycin)
Information: Oxytetracycline is a broad-spectrum tetracycline antibiotic, used to treat infections with bacteria.

Name: Thioguanine
Information: Thioguanine, a purine antimetabolite, inhibits DNMT1 activity through ubiquitin-targeted degradation, used in the treatment of acute lymphoblastic leukemia, autoimmune disorders (e.g., Crohn's disease, rheumatoid arthritis) and organ transplant recipients.

Name: Thiotepa
Information: Thiotepa(Thioplex) is an alkylating agent used to treat cancer.

Name: Toremifene Citrate
Information: Toremifene Citrate is an oral selective estrogen receptor modulator (SERM), used in the treatment of advanced breast cancer.

Name: Ethionamide
Information: Ethionamide is an antibiotic used in the treatment of tuberculosis.

Name: Trifluridine
Information: Trifluridine is an anti-herpesvirus antiviral agent by interacting viral DNA replication, used primarily on the eye.

Name: Azacitidine
Information: Azacitidine is a nucleoside analogue of cytidine that specifically inhibits DNA methylation by trapping DNA methyltransferases.

Name: Vidarabine
Information: Vidarabine is an antiviral drug by interfering with the synthesis of viral DNA, used to treat herpes simplex and varicella zoster viruses.

Name: Verteporfin
Information: Verteporfin is a small molecule that inhibits TEAD–YAP association and YAP-induced liver overgrowth. It is also a potent second-generation photosensitizing agent derived from porphyrin.

Name: Teniposide
Information: Teniposide is a chemotherapeutic medication mainly used in the treatment of childhood acute lymphocytic leukemia (ALL).

Name: Tetrabenazine (Xenazine)
Information: Tetrabenazine(Nitoman, Xenazine) acts primarily as a reversible high-affinity inhibitor of mono-amine uptake into granular vesicles of presynaptic neurons by binding selectively to VMAT-2 Also blocks dopamine D2 receptors, but this affinity is 1,000-fold lower than its affinity for VMAT-2.

Name: Rifaximin
Information: Rifaximin is a RNA synthesis inhibitor by binding the β subunit of the bacterial DNA-dependent RNA polymerase, used to treat traveler's diarrhea caused by certain bacteria.

Name: Simvastatin
Information: Simvastatin is a competitive inhibitor of HMG-CoA reductase with Ki of 0.1-0.2 nM in cell-free assays.

Name: Ramipril
Information: Ramipril is an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM.

Name: Fenofibrate
Information: Fenofibrate (Tricor, Trilipix) is a compound of the fibrate class and fibric acid derivative.

Name: Ranolazine
Information: Ranolazine is a calcium uptake inhibitor via the sodium/calcium channel, used to treat chronic angina.

Name: Ranitidine Hydrochloride
Information: Ranitidine is a histamine H2-receptor antagonist, used to treat stomach or intestinal ulcers.

Name: AICAR (Acadesine)
Information: AICAR (Acadesine), an AMPK activator, results in accumulation of ZMP, which mimics the stimulating effect of AMP on AMPK and AMPK kinase. Phase 3.

Name: Acipimox
Information: Acipimox is a niacin derivative used as a hypolipidemic agent.

Name: Aciclovir
Information: Aciclovir is a synthetic nucleoside analogue active against herpesviruses.

Name: Nifedipine
Information: Nifedipine is a dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker, used to lower hypertension and to treat angina.

Name: Amiloride HCl
Information: Amiloride is a selective T-type calcium channel blocker, an epithelial sodium channel blocker and a selective inhibitor of urokinase plasminogen activator (uPA)(Ki=7 μM).

Name: Amlodipine Besylate
Information: Amlodipine Besylate is a long-acting calcium channel blocker, used to lower blood pressure and prevent chest pain.

Name: Chlorpheniramine Maleate
Information: Chlorpheniramine (Chlorpheniramine maleate, Chlorphenamine) is an histamine H1 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 12 nM.

Name: Fenoprofen Calcium
Information: Fenoprofen Calcium is a nonsteroidal, anti-inflammatory antiarthritic agent.

Name: Erdosteine
Information: Erdosteine is a mucolytic which is used in treatment of excessive viscous mucus.

Name: Nedaplatin
Information: Nedaplatin is a derivative of cisplatin and DNA damage agent for tumor colony forming units with IC50 of 94 μM.

Name: Betaxolol HCl
Information: Betaxolol is a β1 adrenergic receptor blocker with IC50 of 6 μM.

Name: Proparacaine HCl
Information: Proparacaine HCl is a voltage-gated sodium channels antagonist with ED50 of 3.4 mM.

Name: Pranlukast
Information: Pranlukast is an orally administered, and selective antagonist of the cysteinyl leukotrienes (LT) C(4), LTD(4) and LTE(4), used in the prophylactic treatment of chronic bronchial asthma.

Name: Oxfendazole
Information: Oxfendazole is a broad spectrum benzimidazole anthelmintic.

Name: Carvedilol
Information: Carvedilol is a non-selective beta blocker/alpha-1 blocker, used to treat congestive heart failure (CHF) and high blood pressure.

Name: Atracurium Besylate
Information: Atracurium Besylate is a neuromuscular blocking agent with ED95 of 0.2 mg/kg.

Name: Butoconazole nitrate
Information: Butoconazole nitrate is an anti-fungal agent that inhibits PHA-stimulated release of cytokines-- IL-2, TNFα, IFN and GM-CSF from human peripheral blood lymphocytes (IC50 of 7.2 μg/mL, 14.4 μg/mL, 7.36 μg/mL and 7.6 μg/mL, respectively).

Name: Azithromycin
Information: Azithromycin is an antibiotic by inhibiting protein synthesis, used for the treatment of bacterial infections.

Name: Albendazole Oxide
Information: Albendazole is a tubulin polymerization or assembly inhibitor, used for the treatment of a variety of parasitic worm infestations.

Name: Flubendazole
Information: Flubendazole is an autophagy inducer by targeting Atg4B, used to treat internal parasite and worm infection.

Name: Chloroxine
Information: Chloroxine is a synthetic antibacterial compound that is effective in the treatment of dandruff and seborrheic dermatitis when incorporated in a shampoo.

Name: Lomustine
Information: Lomustine inhibits cancer cells by damaging the DNA and stops cells from dividing.

Name: Chenodeoxycholic Acid
Information: Chenodeoxycholic Acid is a naturally occurring human bile acid, and inhibits production of cholesterol in the liver and absorption in the intestines.

Name: Cimetidine
Information: Cimetidine, a histamine congener, competitively inhibits histamine binding to histamine H2 receptors.

Name: Clemastine Fumarate
Information: Clemastine Fumarate (Clemastine) is a selective histamine H1 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 3 nM.

Name: Curcumin
Information: Curcumin is the principal curcuminoid of the popular Indian spice turmeric, which is a member of the ginger family (Zingiberaceae). It is an inhibitor of p300 histone acetylatransferase（IC50~25 μM） and Histone deacetylase activates Nrf2 pathway and supresses the activation of transcription factor NF-κB.

Name: Daidzein
Information: Daidzein is a natural isoflavone phytoestrogen found in Leguminosae, used as a component of foods and dietary supplements.

Name: Oxibendazole
Information: Oxibendazole is a benzimidazole drug that interferes with metabolic pathways, used to protect against roundworms, strongyles, threadworms, pinworms and lungworm infestations in horses and some domestic pets.

Name: Penicillamine
Information: Penicillamine is used as an antirheumatic and as a chelating agent in Wilson’s disease.

Name: Bifonazole
Information: Bifonazole is a substituted imidazole antifungal agent.

Name: Pefloxacin Mesylate
Information: Pefloxacin Mesylate is a synthetic chemotherapeutic agent and an antibacterial agent with IC50 of 6.7 nM.

Name: Metoprolol Tartrate
Information: Metoprolol Tartrate is a selective β1 receptor blocker medication, used to treat hypertension and heart failure.

Name: Etidronate
Information: Etidronate is a non-aminobisphosphonate, show protein tyrosine phosphatase (PTP) inhibitory activity, used for the treatment of Paget's disease and the prevention of heterotopic ossification.

Name: Dienestrol
Information: Dienestrol(Restrol) is a synthetic, non-steroidal estrogen. It is an estrogen receptor agonist.

Name: Diethylstilbestrol
Information: Diethylstilbestrol is a synthetic nonsteroidal estrogen, used to prevent miscarriage and other pregnancy complications.

Name: Diltiazem HCl
Information: Diltiazem HCl (Tiazac) is a benzothiazepine derivative with vasodilating action due to its antagonism of the actions of the calcium ion in membrane functions.

Name: Diphenhydramine HCl
Information: Diphenhydramine HCl is a first-generation histamine H1 receptor antagonist, used in various allergic conditions such as rhinitis, urticaria and conjunctivitis.

Name: Dapoxetine HCl
Information: Dapoxetine HCl is a short-acting novel selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor, used for the treatment of premature ejaculation.

Name: Tranexamic Acid
Information: Tranexamic Acid is an antifibrinolytic for blocking lysine-binding sites of plasmin and elastase-derived plasminogen fragments with IC50 of 5 mM.

Name: Valaciclovir HCl
Information: Valaciclovir HCl, an aciclovir prodrug, inhibits activity of virus DNA polymerase, used to treat infections caused by herpes simplex virus (HSV) and varicella zoster virus, and for prophylaxis against cytomegalovirus (CMV).

Name: Ganciclovir
Information: Ganciclovir is an antiviral drug for feline herpesvirus type-1 with IC50 of 5.2 μM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Roxatidine Acetate HCl
Information: Roxatidine Acetate HCl is a specific and competitive histamin H2-receptor antagonist, with IC50 of 3.2 μM, inhibits gastric acid secretion and ulcer formation.

Name: Protionamide
Information: Protionamide is a drug used in the treatment of tuberculosis.

Name: Idoxuridine
Information: Idoxuridine is an antiviral agent for feline herpesvirus type-1 with IC50 of 4.3 μM.

Name: Sparfloxacin
Information: Sparfloxacin is a fluoroquinolone antibiotic, shows broad and potent antibacterial activity.

Name: Felodipine
Information: Felodipine is a selective L-type Ca2+ channel blocker with IC50 of 0.15 nM.

Name: Deflazacort
Information: Deflazacort is a glucocorticoid used as an anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressant.

Name: Nizatidine
Information: Nizatidine is a histamine H2 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.9 nM, also inhibits AChE with IC50 of 6.7 μM.

Name: Carbidopa
Information: Carbidopa is an aromatic-L-amino-acid decarboxylase inhibitor with an IC50 of 29 ± 2 μM.

Name: Valsartan
Information: Valsartan is a selective angiotensin II receptor antagonist, used to treat high blood pressure and congestive heart failure.

Name: Dipyridamole
Information: Dipyridamole (Persantine) is a phosphodiesterase inhibitor that blocks uptake and metabolism of adenosine by erythrocytes and vascular endothelial cells.

Name: Hydroxyurea
Information: Hydroxyurea is an antineoplastic agent that inhibits DNA synthesis through the inhibition of ribonucleoside diphosphate reductase.

Name: Potassium Iodide
Information: Potassium Iodide is used to treat overactive thyroid and to protect the thyroid gland from the effects of radiation from inhaled or swallowed radioactive iodine.

Name: Tropisetron HCl
Information: Tropisetron HCl is a potent and selective 5-HT3 receptor antagonist and α7-nicotinic receptor agonist, used to treat nausea and vomiting following chemotherapy.

Name: Nicotinamide (Vitamin B3)
Information: Nicotinamide (Vitamin B3), a water-soluble vitamin, is an active component of coenzymes NAD and NADP, and also act as an inhibitor of sirtuins.
Synonyms: Niacinamide, Vitamin PP, Nicotinic acid amide

Name: Vitamin B12
Information: Vitamin B12 is a water soluble vitamin with a key role in the normal functioning of the brain and nervous system, and for the formation of blood.

Name: Diclofenac Sodium
Information: Diclofenac Sodium is a non-selective COX inhibitor with IC50 of 0.5 μg/ml and 0.5 μg/ml for COX-1 and -2 in intact cells, respectively, used as a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) to relieve pain and reduce swelling in flammation.

Name: Avobenzone
Information: Avobenzone is an oil soluble ingredient used in sunscreen products to absorb the full spectrum of UVA rays and a dibenzoylmethane derivative.

Name: Amlodipine
Information: Amlodipine is a long-acting calcium channel blocker, used to lower blood pressure and prevent chest pain.

Name: Metronidazole
Information: Metronidazole, a synthetic antibacterial and antiprotozoal agent of the nitroimidazole class, is used against protozoa.

Name: Flutamide
Information: Flutamide is an antiandrogen drug, with its active metablolite binding at androgen receptor with Ki values of 55 nM, and primarily used to treat prostate cancer.

Name: Fluvastatin Sodium
Information: Fluvastatin Sodium inhibits HMG-CoA reductase activity with IC50 of 8 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Tioconazole
Information: Tioconazole is an antifungal medication with an average IC50 of 1.7 μM.

Name: Disodium Cromoglycate
Information: Disodium Cromoglycate is an antiallergic drug with IC50 of 39 μg/mL.

Name: Tropicamide
Information: Tropicamide is an anticholinergic and a muscarinic receptor subtype M4-preferring antagonist with IC50 of 8.0 nM.

Name: Pregnenolone
Information: Pregnenolone is an endogenous steroid hormone, used in the treatment of fatigue, Alzheimer’s disease, trauma and injuries.

Name: Sulfamethoxazole
Information: Sulfamethoxazole is a sulfonamide bacteriostatic antibiotic with an IC50 of 2.7 μM.

Name: Sulfisoxazole
Information: Sulfisoxazole is a sulfonamide antibacterial with an oxazole substituent.

Name: Crystal Violet
Information: Crystal violet is a triarylmethane dye.

Name: Haloperidol
Information: Haloperidol (Haldol) is an antipsychotic and butyrophenone.

Name: Phenindione
Information: Phenindione is an anticoagulant which functions as a Vitamin K antagonist.

Name: Irsogladine
Information: Irsogladine is an anti-gastric ulcer agent that facilitates gap-junctional intercellular communication through M1 muscarininc acetylcholine receptor binding.

Name: Triamcinolone
Information: Triamcinolone is a glucocorticoid given, as the free alcohol or in esterified form, orally, intramuscularly, by local injection, by inhalation, or applied topically in the management of various disorders in which corticosteroids are indicated.

Name: Nystatin (Fungicidin)
Information: Nystatin, which belongs to the polyene group of antimycotics, is frequently used as a topical agent in the treatment of oro-pharyngeal candidosis.

Name: Isoniazid
Information: Isoniazid is a prodrug that blocks the action of fatty acid synthase by interacting with KatG , used for the prevention and treatment of tuberculosis.

Name: Levamisole hydrochloride
Information: (-)-Tetramisole is an inhibitor of alkaline phosphatase, used as an anthelmintic.

Name: Levofloxacin
Information: Levofloxacin is a broad-spectrum antibiotic topoisomerase II and topoisomerase IV inhibitor, used to treat respiratory, urinary tract, gastrointestinal, and abdominal infections.

Name: Enalapril Maleate
Information: Enalapril Maleate is an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor, used in the treatment of hypertension, diabetic nephropathy, and chronic heart failure.

Name: Menadione
Information: Menadione(Vitamin K3), a fat-soluble compound, is an inhibitor of Cdc25 phosphatase and mitochondrial DNA polymerase γ (pol γ), used as a nutritional supplement.

Name: Metformin HCl
Information: Metformin HCl decreases hyperglycemia in hepatocytes primarily by suppressing glucose production by the liver (hepatic gluconeogenesis).

Name: Methoxsalen
Information: Methoxsalen is a naturally occurring photoactive substance found in the seeds of the Ammi majus (Umbelliferae) plant, used in the diagnosis and treatment of psoriasis A CYP2A5/6 inhibitor.

Name: Miconazole Nitrate
Information: Miconazole Nitrate is an imidazole antifungal agent by inhibiting ergosterol biosynthesis and inducing ROS, used to treat vaginal yeast infections.

Name: Sulfamethizole
Information: Sulfamethizole is a sulfathiazole antibacterial agent.

Name: Sulbactam
Information: Sulbactam is a beta-lactamase inhibitor with an average IC50 of 0.8 μM.

Name: Tolfenamic Acid
Information: Tolfenamic Acid is a COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.2 μM.

Name: Pranoprofen
Information: Pranoprofen is a non-steroidal COX inhibitor, used as an anti-inflammatory drug in ophthalmology.

Name: Rimantadine
Information: Rimantadine (Flumadine) is an anti-influenza virus drug for T. brucei with IC50 of 7 μM.

Name: Primidone
Information: Primidone is an anticonvulsant of the pyrimidinedione class.

Name: Nefiracetam
Information: Nefiracetam is a GABAergic, cholinergic, and monoaminergic neuronal system enhancer for Ro 5-4864-induced convulsions. Phase 2.

Name: Nicorandil
Information: Nicorandil is a potassium channel activator, and stimulates guanylate cyclase to increase formation of cyclic GMP (cGMP).

Name: Tamoxifen Citrate
Information: Tamoxifen Citrate is an antagonist of the estrogen receptor by competitive inhibition of estrogen binding.

Name: Meglumine
Information: Meglumine is an amino sugar derived from sorbitol for THP-1 cells with IC50 of 22 μg/mL.

Name: Aripiprazole
Information: Aripiprazole is a novel atypical antipsychotic drug that is reported to be a high-affinity 5-HT receptor partial agonist.

Name: Sarafloxacin HCl
Information: Sarafloxacin HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of sarafloxacin which is a quinolone antibiotic drug with IC50 of 0.96 μg/L.

Name: Methscopolamine
Information: Methscopolamine is a muscarinic acetylcholine receptor blocker.

Name: Amiodarone HCl
Information: Amiodarone HCl is a sodium/potassium-ATPase inhibitor and an autophagy activator, used to treat various types of cardiac dysrhythmias.

Name: Adenine sulfate
Information: Adenine sulfate is a sulfate salt form of adenine which is a purine derivative and a nucleobase with a variety of roles in biochemistry.

Name: Adenine HCl
Information: Adenine HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of adenine which is a purine derivative and a nucleobase with a variety of roles in biochemistry.

Name: Ticlopidine HCl
Information: Ticlopidine HCl is an P2 receptor inhibitor against ADP-induced platelet aggregation with IC50 of ~2 μM.

Name: ATP
Information: ATP Disodium is a disodium salt form of adenosine-triphosphate that is used in cells as a coenzyme.

Name: Meclizine 2HCl
Information: Meclizine is a histamine H1 receptor antagonist used to treat nausea and motion sickness, has anti-histamine, anti-muscarinic and anti-oxidative phosphorylation properties, also an agonist ligand for mCAR (constitutive androstane receptor) and an inverse agonist for hCAR.

Name: Mometasone furoate
Information: Mometasone Furoate is a glucocorticoid receptor agonist, used topically to reduce inflammation of the skin or in the airways.

Name: Propylthiouracil
Information: Propylthiouracil is a thyroperoxidase and 5'-deiodinase inhibitor, used to treat hyperthyroidism.

Name: Capsaicin(Vanilloid)
Information: Capsaicin is an active component of chili peppers, which are plants belonging to the genus Capsicum.

Name: Fluticasone propionate
Information: Fluticasone Propionate is a synthetic glucocorticoid, used to treat non-allergic and allergic rhinitis.

Name: Lacidipine
Information: Lacidipine is a L-type calcium channel blocker, used for treating high blood pressure.

Name: Procarbazine HCl
Information: Procarbazine HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of procarbazine which is a polyfunctional alkylating compound, used for the treatment of Hodgkin's lymphoma.

Name: D-Cycloserine
Information: D-cycloserine is an analog of the amino acid D-alanine, used as an antibiotic in the treatment of tuberculosis.

Name: Sodium butyrate
Information: Sodium butyrate, sodium salt of butyric acid, is a histone deacetylase inhibitor and competitively binds to the zinc sites of class I and II histone deacetylases (HDACs).

Name: Elvitegravir (GS-9137, JTK-303)
Information: Elvitegravir (GS-9137, JTK-303) is an HIV integrase inhibitor for HIV-1 IIIB, HIV-2 EHO and HIV-2 ROD with IC50 of 0.7 nM, 2.8 nM and 1.4 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Maraviroc
Information: Maraviroc is a CCR5 antagonist for MIP-1α, MIP-1β and RANTES with IC50 of 3.3 nM, 7.2 nM and 5.2 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Raltegravir (MK-0518)
Information: Raltegravir (MK-0518) is a potent integrase (IN) inhibitor for WT and S217Q PFV IN with IC50 of 90 nM and 40 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. It shows greater than 1000-fold selectivity for HIV-1 IN over several related Mg2+-dependent enzyme such as HCV polymerase, HIV reverse transcriptase, HIV RNaseH and human α-, β-, γ-polymerases.

Name: Pyrimethamine
Information: Pyrimethamine is a dihydrofolate reductase (DHFR) inhibitor, used as an antimalarial drug.

Name: Sulindac
Information: Sulindac is a non-steroidal COX inhibitor, which potently inhibits prostaglandin synthesis, used in the treatment of acute or chronic inflammatory conditions.

Name: Taurine
Information: Taurine is an organic acid widely distributed in animal tissues.

Name: Pramipexole 2HCl Monohydrate
Information: Pramipexole 2HCl Monohydrateis a novel non-ergoline dopamine (DA) agonist, used to treat Parkinson's disease.

Name: PCI-34051
Information: PCI-34051 is a potent and specific HDAC8 inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM in a cell-free assay. It has greater than 200-fold selectivity over HDAC1 and 6, more than 1000-fold selectivity over HDAC2, 3, and 10.

Name: PF-573228
Information: PF-573228 is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of FAK with IC50 of 4 nM in a cell-free assay, ~50- to 250-fold selective for FAK than Pyk2, CDK1/7 and GSK-3β.

Name: BMS-265246
Information: BMS-265246 is a potent and selective CDK1/2 inhibitor with IC50 of 6 nM/9 nM in a cell-free assay. It is 25-fold more selective for CDK1/2 than CDK4.

Name: Suplatast Tosylate
Information: Suplatast Tosilate is a novel capsular anti-asthmatic agent that suppresses both IgE production, IL-4 and IL-5 synthesis with IC50 above 100 μM.

Name: Mirtazapine
Information: Mirtazapine is an adrenergic and seroton receptor antagonist, used to treat depression.

Name: Benidipine HCl
Information: Benidipine HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of benidipine which is a dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker.

Name: ENMD-2076 L-(+)-Tartaric acid
Information: ENMD-2076 L-(+)-Tartaric acid is the tartaric acid of ENMD-2076, selective activity against Aurora A and Flt3 with IC50 of 14 nM and 1.86 nM, 25-fold more selective for Aurora A than Aurora B and less potent to VEGFR2/KDR and VEGFR3, FGFR1 and FGFR2 and PDGFRα. Phase 2.

Name: Formoterol Hemifumarate
Information: Formoterol Hemifumarate is a potent, selective and long-acting β2-adrenoceptor agonist used in the management of asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease(COPD).

Name: Chlormezanone
Information: Chlormezanone，a non-benzodiazepine that is used in the management of anxiety. It has been suggested for use in the treatment of muscle spasm.

Name: Ketotifen Fumarate
Information: Ketotifen Fumarate is a fumaric acid salt of ketotifen which is a H1-antihistamine and mast cell stabilizer.

Name: Urapidil HCl
Information: Urapidil HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of urapidil which is α1-adrenoceptor antagonist and 5-HT1A receptor agonist with pIC50 of 6.13 and 6.4 respectively.

Name: Diclazuril
Information: Diclazuril is an anti-coccidial drug.

Name: Uridine
Information: Uridine is a nucleoside, contains a uracil attached to a ribose ring via a β-N1-glycosidic bond.

Name: Flunarizine 2HCl
Information: Flunarizine 2HCl is a dihydrochloride salt form which is a calcium channel blocker with a Ki of 68 nM.

Name: Fenticonazole Nitrate
Information: Fenticonazole Nitrate is an azole antifungal agent.

Name: Rebamipide
Information: Rebamipide is a cholecystokinin type 1 (CCK1) receptor inhibitor for inhibiting [125I]BH-CCK-8S with IC50 of 37.7 μM.

Name: Epalrestat
Information: Epalrestat is an aldose reductase inhibitor with IC50 of 72 nM.

Name: Aspartame
Information: Aspartame is an artificial, non-saccharide sweetener used as a sugar substitute in some foods and beverages.

Name: Candesartan Cilexetil
Information: Candesartan Cilexetil is an angiotensin II receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.26 nM, used in the treatment of hypertension.

Name: Phentolamine Mesylate
Information: Phentolamine Mesylate is a reversible and nonselective alpha-adrenergic receptor antagonist, used for the prevention or control of hypertensive episodes.

Name: Nimesulide
Information: Nimesulide is a relatively COX-2 selective inhibitor with IC50 of 26 μM.

Name: Dyclonine HCl
Information: Dyclonine HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of dyclonine which is an oral anaesthetic, reversibly binds to activated sodium channels on the neuronal membrane, thereby decreasing the neuronal membrane's permeability to sodium ions, leading to an increased threshold for excitation.

Name: Cyproterone Acetate
Information: Cyproterone acetate is an androgen receptor (AR) antagonist with IC50 of 7.1 nM, as well as a weak progesterone receptor agonist with weak pro-gestational and glucocorticoid activity.

Name: Memantine HCl
Information: Memantine HCl is a CYP2B6 and CYP2D6 inhibitor for recombinant CYP2B6 and CYP2D6 with Ki of 0.51 nM and 94.9 μM, respectively.

Name: Cyproheptadine HCl
Information: Cyproheptadine HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of cyproheptadine which is a histamine receptor antagonist.

Name: Doxifluridine
Information: Doxifluridine is an oral prodrug that is converted to the cytotoxic agent 5-fluorouracil (5-FU).

Name: Pioglitazone HCl
Information: Pioglitazone HCl is a selective peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-gamma (PPARgamma) agonist, used to treat diabetes.

Name: Lornoxicam
Information: Lornoxicam is a non-steroidal COX-1/COX-2 inhibitor, used as an anti-inflammatory drug to treat pain, osteoarthritis, and rheumatoid arthritis.

Name: Clindamycin Phosphate
Information: Clindamycin Phosphate is a lincosamide antibiotic for Plasmodium falciparum with IC50 of 12 nM.

Name: Captopril
Information: Captopril is an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor with IC50 of 6 nM.

Name: Oxytetracycline Dihydrate
Information: Oxytetracycline Dihydrate is a prescription antibiotic, interfering with the ability of bacteria to produce essential proteins.

Name: Cytidine
Information: Cytidine is a nucleoside molecule that is formed when cytosine is attached to a ribose ring, cytidine is a component of RNA.

Name: Orphenadrine Citrate
Information: Orphenadrine Citrate is a skeletal muscle relaxant, it acts in the central nervous system to produce its muscle relaxant effects.

Name: Gimeracil
Information: Gimeracil is an inhibitor of dihydropyrimidine dehydrogenase, which inhibits the early step in homologous recombination for double strand breaks repair.

Name: Cyclophosphamide Monohydrate
Information: Cyclophosphamide Monohydrate is a nitrogen mustard alkylating agent, it attaches the alkyl group to the guanine base of DNA, shown to crosslink DNA, causing strand breakage and inducing mutations.

Name: Tolnaftate
Information: Tolnaftate is a synthetic thiocarbamate used as an anti-fungal agent.

Name: Terazosin HCl Dihydrate
Information: Terazosin HCl is a selective α1-adrenoceptor antagonist, used for treatment of symptoms of an enlarged prostate (BPH).

Name: Bromhexine HCl
Information: Bromhexine HCl is a medication prescribed for coughs which works by dissolving hard phlegm.

Name: Lovastatin
Information: Lovastatin is an inhibitor of HMG-CoA reductase with IC50 of 3.4 nM in a cell-free assay, used for lowering cholesterol (hypolipidemic agent).

Name: Tiopronin
Information: Tiopronin is an antioxidant agent, used for the treatment of cystinuria by controlling the rate of cystine precipitation and excretion.

Name: Balofloxacin
Information: Balofloxacin is a quinolone antibiotic, inhibiting the synthesis of bacterial DNA by interference with the enqyme DNA gyrase.

Name: Lafutidine
Information: Lafutidine, a newly developed histamine H(2)-receptor antagonist, inhibits gastric acid secretion.

Name: Moxonidine
Information: Moxonidine is a selective agonist at the imidazoline receptor subtype 1, used as antihypertensive agent.

Name: Ozagrel HCl
Information: Ozagrel HCl is a selective <n>thromboxane A(2) (TXA(2)) synthetase inhibitor with IC50 of 11 nM for rabbit platelet, used for the improvement of postoperative cerebrovascular contraction and accompanying cerebral ischaemia.

Name: Argatroban
Information: Argatroban is a potent and selective synthetic thrombin inhibitor with Ki ranging from 5 nM to 39 nM, used as an anticoagulant.

Name: Prulifloxacin (NM441, AF 3013)
Information: Prulifloxacin, the prodrug of ulifloxacin, is a broad-spectrum oral fluoroquinolone antibacterial agent.

Name: Rosiglitazone HCl
Information: Rosiglitazone HCl is a blood glucose-lowering drugs, stimulating insulin secretion by binding to the PPAR receptors in fat cells.

Name: Lisinopril
Information: Lisinopril is an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor, used in treatment of hypertension, congestive heart failure, and heart attacks, and also in preventing renal and retinal complications of diabetes.

Name: Atorvastatin Calcium
Information: Atorvastatin Calcium is an inhibitor of HMG-CoA reductase used as a cholesterol-lowering medication that blocks the production of cholesterol.

Name: Famotidine
Information: Famotidine is a histamine H2–receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.6 mM, commonly used to treat heartburn, GERD, ulcers, and other digestive conditions.

Name: Moexipril HCl
Information: Moexipril HCl is a potent orally active nonsulfhydryl angiotensin converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor, used for the treatment of hypertension and congestive heart failure.

Name: Clevidipine Butyrate
Information: Clevidipine Butyrate is a dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker, uses as an agent for the reduction of blood pressure.

Name: Procaterol HCl
Information: Procaterol HCl is a short-acting β2-adrenergic receptor agonist with K<sub>p</sub> of 8 nM, used for the treatment of asthma

Name: Duloxetine HCl
Information: Duloxetine HCl is a serotonin-norepinephrine reuptake inhibitor with Ki of 4.6 nM, used for treatment of major depressive disorder and generalized anxiety disorder (GAD).

Name: Trimebutine
Information: Trimebutine is an agonist of peripheral mu, kappa and delta opiate receptors, used as spasmolytic agent for treatment of both acute and chronic abdominal pain.

Name: Ivabradine HCl
Information: Ivabradine HCl, a new If inhibitor with IC 50 of 2.9 μM which acts specifically on the pacemaker activity of the sinoatrial node, is a pure heart rate lowering agent.

Name: Rivastigmine Tartrate
Information: Rivastigmine Tartrate is a cholinesterase inhibitor with IC50 of 5.5 μM, and used as a parasympathomimetic or cholinergic agent for the treatment of mild to moderate Alzheimer disease.

Name: Dexmedetomidine HCl
Information: Dexmedetomidine HCl is a highly selective and potent alpha-2 adrenoceptor agonist, which reduces anesthetic requirements for patients by providing significant sedation.

Name: Betaxolol
Information: Betaxolol is a selective beta1 adrenergic receptor blocker used in the treatment of hypertension and glaucoma.

Name: Detomidine HCl
Information: Detomidine HCl produce dose-dependent sedative and analgesic effects, mediatated by activation of α2 catecholamine receptors.

Name: Fosinopril Sodium
Information: Fosinopril Sodium is the ester prodrug of an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor, used for the treatment of hypertension and some types of chronic heart failure.

Name: Almotriptan Malate
Information: Almotriptan Malate is a selective 5-hydroxytryptamine1B/1D (5-HT1B/1D) receptor agonist, used for the treatment of Migraine attacks in adults.

Name: Ambrisentan
Information: Ambrisentan is a highly selective antagonist of the endothelin-1 type A receptor, used in the treatment of pulmonary arterial hypertension (PAH).

Name: Bexarotene
Information: Bexarotene is a retinoid specifically selective for retinoid X receptors, used as an oral antineoplastic agent in the treatment of cutaneous T-cell lymphoma.

Name: Temocapril HCl
Information: Temocapril HCl is the hydrochloride of Temocapril, which is a long-acting angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor, used for the treatment of hypertension.

Name: Gabexate Mesylate
Information: Gabexate Mesylate is a serine protease inhibitor with IC50 of 0.19 μM which is used therapeutically in the treatment of pancreatitis and disseminated intravascular coagulation.

Name: Rasagiline Mesylate
Information: Rasagiline Mesylate is a new MAO-B inhibitor for the treatment of idiopathic Parkinson's disease.

Name: Naltrexone HCl
Information: Naltrexone HCl is an opioid receptor antagonist used primarily in the management of alcohol dependence and opioid dependence.

Name: Levosulpiride
Information: Levosulpiride is a selective antagonist for D2 dopamine receptors used as an antipsychotic and prokinetic agent.

Name: Pantoprazole
Information: Pantoprazole is a proton pump inhibitor used for short-term treatment of erosion and ulceration of the esophagus caused by gastroesophageal reflux disease.

Name: Azasetron HCl
Information: Azasetron HCl is a selective 5-HT3 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.33 nM used in the management of nausea and vomiting induced by cancer chemotherapy.

Name: Flunixin Meglumin
Information: Flunixin Meglumin is a potent inhibitor of the enzyme cyclooxygenase (COX) used as analgesic agent with anti-inflammatory and antipyretic activity.

Name: Imidapril HCl
Information: Imidapril HCl is an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor with IC50 of 2.6 nM, used for the treatment of hypertension.

Name: Vinpocetine
Information: Vinpocetine is a selective inhibitor of voltage-sensitive sodium channel for the treatment of stroke, vascular dementia and Alzheimer's disease.

Name: Lapatinib
Information: Lapatinib, used in the form of Lapatinib Ditosylate, is a potent EGFR and ErbB2 inhibitor with IC50 of 10.8 and 9.2 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Cisatracurium Besylate
Information: Cisatracurium Besylate is a nondepolarizing neuromuscular blocking agent, antagonizing the action of acetylcholine by inhibiting neuromuscular transmission.

Name: Dronedarone HCl
Information: Dronedarone HCl is a multichannel blocker targeting potassium channel, sodium channel and calcium channel, used as an antiarrhythmic drug for treatment of atrial fibrillation (AF).

Name: Conivaptan HCl
Information: Conivaptan HCl is an orally active, non-peptide, vasopressin V1A and V2 receptor antagonist, used in the treatment of euvolemic and hypervolemic hyponatremia.

Name: Ibutilide Fumarate
Information: Ibutilide Fumarate is a Class III antiarrhythmic agent that is indicated for acute cardioconversion of atrial fibrillation and atrial flutter of a recent onset to sinus rhythm by induction of slow inward sodium current, which prolongs action potential and refractory period of myocardial cells.

Name: Probucol
Information: Probucol is an anti-hyperlipidemic drug by lowering the level of cholesterol in the bloodstream by increasing the rate of LDL catabolism.

Name: Arbidol HCl
Information: Arbidol HCl is a broad-spectrum antiviral compound that blocks viral fusion, used in treatment of influenza and other respiratory viral infections.

Name: Dextrose
Information: Dextrose, a simple sugar (monosaccharide), is an important carbohydrate in biology.

Name: Xylose
Information: Xylose is a sugar first isolated from wood.

Name: Mestranol
Information: Mestranol is the 3-methyl ether of ethinyl estradiol, which is a potent estrogen receptor agonist and used as oral contraceptives.

Name: Naftopidil
Information: Naftopidil is a selective α1-adrenergic receptor antagonist with Ki of 3.7 nM, 20 nM, and 1.2 nM for α1a, α1b, and α1d, respectively, used for the treatment of benign prostatic hyperplasia.

Name: S- (+)-Rolipram
Information: S-(+)-Rolipram inhibits human monocyte cyclic AMP-specific PDE4 with IC50 of 0.75 μM, has anti-inflammatory and anti-depressant activity in the central nervous system, less potent than its R enantiomer.

Name: Bazedoxifene HCl
Information: Bazedoxifene HCl is a novel, non-steroidal, indole-based estrogen receptor modulator (SERM) binding to both ERα and ERβ with IC50 of 23 nM and 89 nM, respectively.

Name: Fudosteine
Information: Fudosteine is a cysteine derivative and a MUC5AC mucin hypersecretion inhibitor, used as a muco-active agent with indications for chronic respiratory diseases.

Name: Atropine sulfate monohydrate
Information: Atropine sulfate monohydrate is a competitive antagonist for the muscarinic acetylcholine receptor, used to decrease the production of saliva and secretions of the airway prior to surgery.

Name: Roflumilast
Information: Roflumilast is a selective inhibitor of PDE4 with IC50 of 0.2-4.3 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Gabapentin
Information: Gabapentin is a GABA analogue, used to treat seizures and neuropathic pain.

Name: AZD8330
Information: AZD8330 is a novel, selective, non-ATP competitive MEK 1/2 inhibitor with IC50 of 7 nM. Phase 1.

Name: GSK1292263
Information: GSK1292263 is a novel GPR119 agonist, showing potential for the treatment of type 2 diabetes. Phase 2.

Name: Neratinib (HKI-272)
Information: Neratinib (HKI-272) is a highly selective HER2 and EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 59 nM and 92 nM in cell-free assays weakly inhibits KDR and Src, no significant inhibition to Akt, CDK1/2/4, IKK-2, MK-2, PDK1, c-Raf and c-Met. Phase 3.

Name: Sonidegib (Erismodegib, NVP-LDE225)
Information: Sonidegib (Erismodegib, NVP-LDE225) is a Smoothened (Smo) antagonist, inhibiting Hedgehog (Hh) signaling with IC50 of 1.3 nM (mouse) and 2.5 nM (human) in cell-free assays, respectively. Phase 3.

Name: Sitafloxacin Hydrate
Information: Sitafloxacin Hydrate is a new-generation, broad-spectrum oral fluoroquinolone antibiotic.

Name: CGS 21680 HCl
Information: CGS 21680 HCl is an adenosine A2 receptor agonist with IC50 of 22 nM, exhibits 140-fold over A1 receptor.

Name: Dabigatran Etexilate
Information: Dabigatran Etexilate is the prodrug of dabigatran, a potent, nonpeptidic small molecule that specifically and reversibly inhibits both free and clot-bound thrombin by binding to the active site of the thrombin molecule.

Name: LY2608204
Information: LY2608204 activates glucokinase (GK) with EC50 of 42 nM. Phase 2.

Name: LY2886721
Information: LY2886721 is a BACE inhibitor used for the treatment of Alzheimer's Disease. Phase 1/2.

Name: Taladegib (LY2940680)
Information: Taladegib (LY2940680) binds to the Smoothened (Smo) receptor and potently inhibits Hedgehog (Hh) signaling. Phase 1/2.

Name: KW-2449
Information: KW-2449 is a multiple-targeted inhibitor, mostly for Flt3 with IC50 of 6.6 nM, modestly potent to FGFR1, Bcr-Abl and Aurora A little effect on PDGFRβ, IGF-1R, EGFR. Phase 1.

Name: Tebipenem Pivoxil
Information: Tebipenem pivoxil is an oral carbapenem antibiotic, use to treat otolaryngologic and respiratory infections.

Name: Almorexant HCl
Information: Almorexant HCl is an orally active, dual orexin receptor antagonist with IC50 of 6.6 nM and 3.4 nM for OX1 and OX2 receptor, respectively. Phase 3.

Name: RAF265 (CHIR-265)
Information: RAF265 (CHIR-265) is a potent selective inhibitor of C-Raf/B-Raf/B-Raf V600E with IC50 of 3-60 nM, and exhibits potent inhibition on VEGFR2 phosphorylation with EC50 of 30 nM in cell-free assays. Phase 2.

Name: Bazedoxifene Acetate
Information: Bazedoxifene Acetate is a third generation selective estrogen receptor modulator (SERM).

Name: Rosuvastatin Calcium
Information: Rosuvastatin Calcium is a competitive inhibitor of HMG-CoA reductase with IC50 of 11 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Givinostat (ITF2357)
Information: Givinostat (ITF2357) is a potent HDAC inhibitor for maize HD2, HD1B and HD1A with IC50 of 10 nM, 7.5 nM and 16 nM in cell-free assays. Phase 2.

Name: Telotristat Etiprate (LX 1606 Hippurate)
Information: Telotristat Etiprate (LX 1606 Hippurate) is an orally bioavailable, tryptophan hydroxylase (TPH) inhibitor with potential antiserotonergic activity. Phase 3.

Name: Dichlorphenamide (Diclofenamide)
Information: Dichlorphenamide is a sulfonamide and a carbonic anhydrase inhibitor of the meta-Disulfamoylbenzene class.

Name: AG-14361
Information: AG14361 is a potent inhibitor of PARP1 with Ki of <5 nM in a cell-free assay. It is at least 1000-fold more potent than the benzamides.

Name: Gandotinib (LY2784544)
Information: Gandotinib (LY2784544) is a potent JAK2 inhibitor with IC50 of 3 nM, effective in JAK2V617F, 8- and 20-fold selective versus JAK1 and JAK3. Phase 2.

Name: Ixazomib (MLN2238)
Information: MLN2238 inhibits the chymotrypsin-like proteolytic (β5) site of the 20S proteasome with IC50 and Ki of 3.4 nM and 0.93 nM in cell-free assays, respectively, also inhibits the caspase-like (β1) and trypsin-like (β2) proteolytic sites, with IC50 of 31 and 3500 nM. Phase 3.

Name: Ixazomib Citrate (MLN9708)
Information: Ixazomib Citrate (MLN9708) immediately hydrolyzed to MLN2238, the biologically active form, on exposure to aqueous solutions or plasma. MLN2238 inhibits the chymotrypsin-like proteolytic (β5) site of the 20S proteasome with IC50/Ki of 3.4 nM/0.93 nM in cell-free assays, less potent to β1 and little activity to β2. Phase 3.

Name: SB743921 HCl
Information: SB743921 is a kinesin spindle protein (KSP) inhibitor with Ki of 0.1 nM, almost no affinity to MKLP1, Kin2, Kif1A, Kif15, KHC, Kif4 and CENP-E. Phase 1/2.

Name: AST-1306
Information: AST-1306 is a novel irreversible inhibitor of EGFR and ErbB2 with IC50 of 0.5 nM and 3 nM, also effective in mutation EGFR T790M/L858R, more potent to ErbB2-overexpressing cells, 3000-fold selective for ErbB family than other kinases.

Name: SB505124
Information: SB505124 is a selective inhibitor of TGFβR for ALK4, ALK5 with IC50 of 129 nM and 47 nM in cell-free assays, respectively, also inhibits ALK7, but does not inhibit ALK1, 2, 3, or 6.

Name: Avasimibe
Information: Avasimibe inhibits ACAT with IC50 of 3.3 μM, also inhibits human P450 isoenzymes CYP2C9, CYP1A2 and CYP2C19 with IC50 of 2.9 μM, 13.9 μM and 26.5 μM, respectively.

Name: Sapitinib (AZD8931)
Information: Sapitinib (AZD8931) is a reversible, ATP competitive inhibitor of EGFR, ErbB2 and ErbB3 with IC50 of 4 nM, 3 nM and 4 nM in cell-free assays, more potent than Gefitinib or Lapatinib against NSCLC cell, 100-fold more selective for the ErbB family than MNK1 and Flt. Phase 2.

Name: GSK461364
Information: GSK461364 inhibits purified Plk1 with Ki of 2.2 nM in a cell-free assay. It is more than 1000-fold selective against Plk2/3. Phase 1.

Name: R406
Information: R406 is a potent Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 41 nM in cell-free assays, strongly inhibits Syk but not Lyn, 5-fold less potent to Flt3. Phase 1.

Name: Lexibulin (CYT997)
Information: Lexibulin (CYT997) is a potent microtubule polymerization inhibitor with IC50 of 10-100 nM in cancer cell lines. Phase 2.

Name: SGI-1776 free base
Information: SGI-1776 free base is a novel ATP competitive inhibitor of Pim1 with IC50 of 7 nM in a cell-free assay, 50- and 10-fold selective versus Pim2 and Pim3, also potent to Flt3 and haspin. Phase 1.

Name: Aliskiren Hemifumarate
Information: Aliskiren hemifumarate is a direct renin inhibitor with IC50 of 1.5 nM.

Name: BMS-794833
Information: BMS-794833 is a potent ATP competitive inhibitor of Met/VEGFR2 with IC50 of 1.7 nM/15 nM, also inhibits Ron, Axl and Flt3 with IC50 of <3 nM a prodrug of BMS-817378. Phase 1.

Name: R788 (Fostamatinib) Disodium
Information: R788 (Fostamatinib) disodium, a prodrug of the active metabolite R406, is a Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 41 nM in a cell-free assay, strongly inhibits Syk but not Lyn, 5-fold less potent to Flt3. Phase 3.

Name: Formestane
Information: Formestane is a second generation selective aromatase inhibitor with an IC50 of 80 nM.

Name: AZ 960
Information: AZ 960 is a novel ATP competitive JAK2 inhibitor with IC50 and Ki of <3 nM and 0.45 nM, 3-fold selectivity of AZ960 for JAK2 over JAK3.

Name: DAPT (GSI-IX)
Information: DAPT (GSI-IX) is a novel γ-secretase inhibitor, which inhibits Aβ production with IC50 of 20 nM in HEK 293 cells.

Name: Mubritinib (TAK 165)
Information: Mubritinib (TAK-165) is a potent inhibitor of HER2/ErbB2 with IC50 of 6 nM in BT-474 cell no activity to EGFR, FGFR, PDGFR, JAK1, Src and Blk in BT-474 cell line. Phase 1.

Name: Irinotecan HCl Trihydrate
Information: Irinotecan prevents DNA from unwinding by inhibition of topoisomerase 1.

Name: Momelotinib (CYT387)
Information: Momelotinib (CYT387) is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of JAK1/JAK2 with IC50 of 11 nM/18 nM, ~10-fold selectivity versus JAK3. Phase 3.

Name: SB590885
Information: SB590885 is a potent B-Raf inhibitor with Ki of 0.16 nM in a cell-free assay, 11-fold greater selectivity for B-Raf over c-Raf, no inhibition to other human kinases.

Name: Apatinib?mesylate
Information: Apatinib is an orally bioavailable, selective VEGFR2 inhibitor with IC50 of 1 nM.

Name: UK 383367
Information: UK-383367 is a procollagen C-proteinase inhibitor with IC50 of 44 nM, has excellent selectivity over MMPs.

Name: Idelalisib (CAL-101, GS-1101)
Information: Idelalisib (CAL-101, GS-1101) is a selective p110δ inhibitor with IC50 of 2.5 nM in cell-free assays shown to have 40- to 300-fold greater selectivity for p110δ than p110α/β/γ, and 400- to 4000-fold more selectivity to p110δ than C2β, hVPS34, DNA-PK and mTOR.

Name: Belnacasan (VX-765)
Information: Belnacasan (VX-765) is a potent and selective inhibitor of caspase-1 with Ki of 0.8 nM in a cell-free assay. Phase 2.

Name: Eltrombopag Olamine
Information: Eltrombopag Olamine is a member of the biarylhydrazone class, which is a nonpeptide agonist of the thrombopoietin receptor (TpoR).

Name: Galunisertib (LY2157299)
Information: Galunisertib (LY2157299) is a potent TGFβ receptor I (TβRI) inhibitor with IC50 of 56 nM in a cell-free assay. Phase 2/3.

Name: Telatinib
Information: Telatinib is a potent inhibitor of VEGFR2/3, c-Kit and PDGFRα with IC50 of 6 nM/4 nM, 1 nM and 15 nM, respectively. Phase 2.

Name: Ketanserin
Information: Ketanserin is a specific 5-HT2A serotonin receptor antagonist with Ki of 2.5 nM for rat and human 5-HT2A, used as an antihypertensive drug.

Name: Esomeprazole sodium
Information: Esomeprazole Sodium is a sodium salt of esomeprazole that is a potent proton pump inhibitor with an IC50 of 0.076 mg/kg.

Name: Volasertib (BI 6727)
Information: Volasertib (BI 6727) is a highly potent Plk1 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.87 nM in a cell-free assay. It shows 6- and 65-fold greater selectivity against Plk2 and Plk3. Phase 3.

Name: Palomid 529 (P529)
Information: Palomid 529 (P529) inhibits both the mTORC1 and mTORC2 complexes, reduces phosphorylation of pAktS473, pGSK3βS9, and pS6 but no effect observed on pMAPK or pAktT308. Phase 1.

Name: Fesoterodine Fumarate
Information: Fesoterodine Fumarate is a prodrug of 5-hydroxymethyl tolterodine that is a muscarinic AChR receptor antagonist, used to treat overactive bladder syndrome.

Name: Degrasyn (WP1130)
Information: Degrasyn (WP1130) is a selective deubiquitinase (DUB: USP5, UCH-L1, USP9x, USP14, and UCH37) inhibitor and also suppresses Bcr/Abl, also a JAK2 transducer (without affecting 20S proteasome) and activator of transcription (STAT).

Name: AR-42
Information: AR-42 is an HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 30 nM. Phase 1.

Name: Buparlisib (BKM120, NVP-BKM120)
Information: Buparlisib (BKM120, NVP-BKM120) is a selective PI3K inhibitor of p110α/β/δ/γ with IC50 of 52 nM/166 nM/116 nM/262 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. Reduced potency against VPS34, mTOR, DNAPK, with little activity to PI4Kβ. Phase 2.

Name: Silmitasertib (CX-4945)
Information: Silmitasertib (CX-4945) is a potent and selective inhibitor of CK2 (casein kinase 2) with IC50 of 1 nM in a cell-free assay, less potent to Flt3, Pim1 and CDK1 (inactive in cell-based assay). Phase 1/2.

Name: (-)-Epigallocatechin Gallate
Information: (-)-Epigallocatechin Gallate(EGCG) is the main catechin extraction of green tea that inhibits telomerase and DNA methyltransferase. EGCG blocks the activation of EGF receptors and HER-2 receptors. ECGG inhibits fatty acid synthase and glutamate dehydrogenase activity.

Name: (-)-Huperzine A (HupA)
Information: (-)-Huperzine A is a potent, highly specific and reversible inhibitor of acetylcholinesterase (AChE) with Ki of 7 nM, exhibiting 200-fold more selectivity for G4 AChE over G1 AChE. Also acts as an NMDA receptor antagonist. Phase 4.

Name: 4-Methylumbelliferone (4-MU)
Information: 4-Methylumbelliferone is a hyaluronic acid (HA) synthesis inhibitor with an IC50 of 0.4 mM.

Name: Esculin
Information: Esculin is a glucoside found in horse chestnuts.

Name: Amygdalin
Information: Amygdalin is a glycoside initially isolated from the seeds of the tree Prunus dulcis, also known as bitter almonds.

Name: Andrographolide
Information: Andrographolide is a labdane diterpenoid that is the main bioactive component of the medicinal plant Andrographis paniculata.

Name: Apigenin
Information: Apigenin is a potent P450 inhibitor for CYP2C9 with Ki of 2 μM.

Name: Arbutin
Information: Arbutin is a tyrosinase inhibitor with an IC50 of 1.09 mM.

Name: Artemether
Information: Artemether is an antimalarial for the treatment of resistant strains of falciparum malaria.

Name: Artesunate
Information: Artesunate is a part of the artemisinin group of agents with an IC50 of < 5 μM for small cell lung carcinoma cell line H69. It is a potential inhibitor of STAT-3 and exhibits selective cytotoxicity of cancer cells over normal cells in vitro A potent inhibitor of EXP1.

Name: Baicalein
Information: Baicalein is a CYP2C9 and prolyl endopeptidase inhibitor.

Name: Baicalin
Information: Baicalin is a known prolyl endopeptidase inhibitor and affects the GABA receptors.

Name: Bergenin
Information: Bergenin is trihydroxybenzoic acid glycoside and the C-glycoside of 4-O-methyl gallic acid.

Name: Berberine chloride
Information: Berberine chloride is a quaternary ammonium salt from the group of isoquinoline alkaloids.

Name: Bilobalide
Information: Bilobalide is a biologically active terpenic trilactone present in Ginkgo biloba.

Name: Caffeic Acid
Information: Caffeic acid is a hydroxycinnamic acid, a naturally occurring organic compound.

Name: Chlorogenic Acid
Information: Chlorogenic acid is a hydroxycinnamic acid and a member of a family of naturally occurring organic compounds.

Name: Cinchonidine
Information: Cinchonidine is an alkaloid used in asymmetric synthesis in organic chemistry.

Name: Cinchonine(LA40221)
Information: Cinchonine is an alkaloid and a stereoisomer and pseudo-enantiomer of cinchonidine.

Name: Colchicine
Information: Colchicine is a microtubule polymerization inhibitor with an IC50 of 3 nM.

Name: Cyclosporin A
Information: Cyclosporin A is an immunosuppressive agent, binds to the cyclophilin and then inhibits calcineurin with IC50 of 7 nM in a cell-free assay, widely used in organ transplantation to prevent rejection.

Name: Cytisine
Information: Cytisine is a nicotinic acetylcholine receptor agonist.

Name: Daidzin
Information: Daidzin, a natural organic compound in the class of phytochemicals known as isoflavones, is a potent and selective inhibitor of human mitochondrial aldehyde dehydrogenase and inhibits ALDH-I selectively (Ki=20 nM) at least 500 times less effective against ALDH-Ⅱ, the cytosolic isozyme (Ki=10 μM).

Name: Dihydroartemisinin (DHA)
Information: Dihydroartemisinin (DHA) is a semi-synthetic derivative of artemisinin and isolated from the traditional Chinese herb Artemisia annua.

Name: Diosmin
Information: Diosmin is a semisynthetic phlebotropic agent and a member of the flavonoid family.

Name: DL-Carnitine HCl
Information: DL-Carnitine HCl is a quaternary ammonium compound biosynthesized from the amino acids lysine and methionine.

Name: Emodin
Information: Emodin is a purgative resin, 6-methyl-1,3,8-trihydroxyanthraquinone, from rhubarb, the buckthorn and Japanese Knotweed (Fallopia japonica).

Name: Enoxolone
Information: Enoxolone is a pentacyclic triterpenoid derivative of the beta-amyrin type obtained from the hydrolysis of glycyrrhizic acid, which was obtained from the herb liquorice.

Name: Formononetin
Information: Formononetin is a phytoestrogen from the root of Astragalus membranaceus and an O-methylated isoflavone.

Name: Ferulic Acid
Information: Ferulic Acid is a hydroxycinnamic acid and a type of organic compound found in the Ferula assafoetida L. or Ligusticum chuanxiong.

Name: Glycyrrhizin (Glycyrrhizic Acid)
Information: Glycyrrhizin (Glycyrrhizic Acid) is a direct HMGB1(high mobility group box 1) inhibitor that inhibits HMGB1-dependent inflammatory molecule expression and oxidative stress modulates P38 and P-JNK but not p-ERK signalling Also inhibits 11 beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase and monoamine oxidase (MAO).

Name: gossypol-Acetic acid
Information: Gossypol Acetate is a polyphenolic aldehyde that permeates cells and acts as an inhibitor for several dehydrogenase enzymes such as lactate dehydrogenase, NAD-linked enzymes.

Name: Gramine
Information: Gramine is a naturally occurring indole alkaloid present in several plant species.

Name: Grape Seed Extract
Information: Grape Seed Extract are industrial derivatives from whole grape seeds that have a great concentration of vitamin E, flavonoids, linoleic acid, and OPCs.

Name: Hesperidin
Information: Hesperidin is a flavanone glycoside found abundantly in citrus fruits.

Name: Honokiol
Information: Honokiol is the active principle of magnolia extract that inhibits Akt-phosphorylation and promotes ERK1/2 phosphorylation. Phase 3.

Name: Hyodeoxycholic acid (HDCA)
Information: Hyodeoxycholic(HDCA) acid is a secondary bile acid, one of the metabolic byproducts of intestinal bacteria.

Name: Indole-3-carbinol
Information: Indole-3-carbinol is produced by the breakdown of the glucosinolate glucobrassicin, which can be found at relatively high levels in cruciferous vegetables. Indole-3-carbinol suppresses NF-κB and IκBα kinase activation.

Name: Kaempferol
Information: Kaempferol, a natural flavonol, functions as an ERRα and ERRγ inverse agonist. It inhibits topoisomerase I catalyzed DNA religation and may also inhibit the activity of fatty acid synthase.

Name: Kanamycin sulfate
Information: Kanamycin sulfate(Kanamycin monosulfate) is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, available in oral, intravenous, and intramuscular forms, and used to treat a wide variety of infections.

Name: Kinetin
Information: Kinetin is a type of cytokinin, a class of plant hormone that promotes cell division.

Name: L-(+)-Rhamnose Monohydrate
Information: L(+)-Rhamnose (Rham) is a naturally-occurring deoxy sugar that is found primarily in plants and some bacteria.

Name: Lappaconitine
Information: Lappaconitine (LC) is a natural diterpenoid alkaloid (DTA), acting as a human heart sodium channel blocker and possessing a wide range of biological activities, including anti-arrhythmic, anti-inflammatory, antioxidative, anticancer, epileptiform etc.

Name: Luteolin
Information: Luteolin is a flavonoid found in Terminalia chebula, which is a non-selective phisphodiesterase PDE inhibitor for PDE1-5 with Ki of 15.0 &muM, 6.4 &muM, 13.9 &muM, 11.1 &muM and 9.5 &muM, respectively. Phase 2.

Name: Magnolol
Information: Magnolol is a bioactive lignin found in the bark of the Houpu magnolia (Magnolia officinalis) which shows antifungal properties. It can block TNF-α-induced NF-KB activation.

Name: Methyl-Hesperidin
Information: Methyl Hesperidin is a flavanone glycoside (flavonoid) (C28H34O15) found abundantly in citrus fruits. Its aglycone form is called hesperetin.

Name: Morin Hydrate
Information: Morin hydrate(Aurantica) is a flavonoid isolated from Maclura pomifera (Osage orange), Maclura tinctoria (old fustic) and from leaves of Psidium guajava (common guava).

Name: Nalidixic acid
Information: Nalidixic acid is a synthetic 1,8-naphthyridine antimicrobial agent with a limited bacteriocidal spectrum. It is an inhibitor of the A subunit of bacterial DNA gyrase.

Name: Naringin
Information: Naringin is a flavanone glycoside, which exerts a variety of pharmacological effects such as antioxidant activity, blood lipid lowering, anticancer activity, and inhibition of cytochrome P450 enzymes.

Name: Neohesperidin Dihydrochalcone (Nhdc)
Information: Neohesperidin dihydrochalcone(Nhdc), sometimes abbreviated to neohesperidin DC or simply NHDC, is an artificial sweetener derived from citrus.

Name: Neohesperidin
Information: Neohesperidin, a flavanone glycoside found in citrus fruits, is an antioxidant agent.

Name: Oleanolic Acid
Information: Oleanolic Acid is a non-toxic, hepatoprotective triterpenoid found in Phytolacca Americana, which exerts antitumor and antiviral properties.

Name: Orotic acid (6-Carboxyuracil)
Information: Orotic acid(6-Carboxyuracil) is a heterocyclic compound and an acid.

Name: Osthole
Information: Osthol is an O-methylated coumarin, which is found in the plants such as Cnidium monnieri, Angelica archangelica and Angelica pubescens.

Name: Oxymatrine
Information: Oxymatrine is a quinolizidine alkaloid extracted from the root of Sophora flavescens with anti-inflammatory, antifibrosis, and antitumor effects, inhibits the iNOS expression and TGF-β/Smad pathway. It is used for the treatment of viral hepatitis, cancer, viral myocarditis, gastrointestinal hemorrhage and skin diseases.

Name: Paeonol
Information: Paeonol (Peonol), a phenolic compound extracted from Chinese herbs Paeonia suffruticosa (moutan cortex) and Cynanchum paniculatum, inhibits MAO with an IC50 of about 50 &muM.

Name: (-)-Parthenolide
Information: (-)-Parthenolide, an inhibitor of the Nuclear Factor-κB Pathway, specifically depletes HDAC1 protein without affecting other class I/II HDACs Also promotes the ubiquitination of MDM2 and activates p53 cellular functions.

Name: Piperine
Information: Piperine (1-Piperoylpiperidine) is the alkaloid responsible for the pungency of black pepper and long pepper, which has also been used in some forms of traditional medicine and as an insecticide.

Name: Puerarin
Information: Puerarin (Kakonein), an isoflavones found in the root of Radix puerariae, is a 5-HT2C receptor and benzodiazepine site antagonist.

Name: Quercetin Dihydrate
Information: Quercetin, a polyphenolic flavonoid found in a wide variety of plant-based foods, such as apples, onions, berries, and red wine, is utilized in many different cultures for their nervous system and anticancer effects.

Name: Rotenone (Barbasco)
Information: Rotenone is a botanical insecticide that is an inhibitor of mitochondrial electron transport.

Name: Rutin
Information: Rutin, a flavonol glycoside found in many plants including buckwheat tobacco forsythia hydrangea viola, etc., which possesses healthy effects for human.

Name: Salicin
Information: Salicin is a phenol β-glycosid produced from willow bark that shows anti-inflammatory effects. It is a natural, non-selective COX-1 and COX-2 inhibitor.

Name: Sclareol
Information: Sclareol, a labdane-type diterpene isolated from clary sage (Salvia sclarea), exerts growth inhibition and cytotoxic activity against a variety of human cancer cell lines.

Name: Silibinin
Information: Silibinin, the main flavonoid extracted from the milk thistle Silybum marianum, displays hepatoprotective properties in acute and chronic liver injury.

Name: Silymarin
Information: Silymarin (Silybin B), a polyphenolic flavonoid extracted from the seeds of Silybum marianum or milk thistle, is used in the prevention and treatment of liver diseases and primary liver cancer.

Name: Sinomenine
Information: Sinomenine, a pure alkaloid extracted from the chinese medical plant Sinomenium acutum, is used for the treatment of rheumatism and arthritis.

Name: Synephrine
Information: Synephrine, a natural protoalkaloid in the extract of bitter orange and other citrus species, is commonly used for weight loss.

Name: Tangeretin
Information: Tangeretin, a natural polymethoxylated flavone concentrated in the peel of citrus fruits, is known to have antiproliferative, antiinvasive, antimetastatic and antioxidant activities.

Name: Tanshinone I
