Information: Tanshinone I, an active principle isolated from Salvia miltiorrhiza (Danshen), is structurally similar to tanshinone IIA and may possess similar cytotoxic effects on tumor cells.

Name: Tanshinone IIA
Information: Tanshinone IIA(Tanshinone B) is the most abundant diterpene quinone in Danshen, Salviae miltiorrhizae Radix, a widely prescribed traditional herbal medicine that is used to treat cardiovascular and inflammatory diseases A natural monoacylglycerol lipase inhibitor.

Name: Taxifolin (Dihydroquercetin)
Information: Taxifolin, type I inhibitor for VEGFR-2 kinase, is a flavonoid in many plants such as Taxus chinensis, Siberian larch, Cedrus deodara and so on.

Name: Troxerutin
Information: Troxerutin, a natural bioflavonoid isolated from Sophora japonica., has been reported to have many benefits and medicinal properties.

Name: Ursolic Acid
Information: Ursolic acid (Malol) is a pentacyclic triterpene acid, used in cosmetics.

Name: Yohimbine HCl
Information: Yohimbine has been used as a mydriatic and in the treatment of impotence. It is also alleged to be an aphrodisiac.

Name: 5-hydroxytryptophan (5-HTP)
Information: 5-Hydroxytryptophan (5-HTP), also known as oxitriptan (INN), is a naturally occurring amino acid and chemical precursor for the treatment of depression.

Name: Aloin
Information: Aloin, a natural anthracycline from Aloe vera, is a tyrosinase inhibitor.

Name: Ammonium Glycyrrhizinate
Information: Ammonium Glycyrrhizinate inhibits growth and cytopathology of several unrelated DNA and RNA viruses.

Name: Butylscopolamine Bromide
Information: Butylscopolamine Bromide, is a peripherally acting antimuscarinic, anticholinergic agent used as an abdominal-specific antispasmodic.

Name: Diosmetin
Information: Diosmetin is a bioflavonoid found in spearmint, oregano, and many other plants.

Name: D-Mannitol
Information: D-Mannitol is an osmotic diuretic agent and a weak renal vasodilator.

Name: Gastrodin
Information: Gastrodin, an anti-inflammatory polyphenol extracted from Chinese natural herbal Gastrodia elata Blume., benefits neurodegenerative diseases.

Name: Hematoxylin
Information: Hematoxylin (Hydroxybrazilin) is a compound that forms strongly colored complexes with certain metal ions, notably Fe(III) and Al(III) salts and a kind of stain in histology.

Name: Indirubin
Information: Indirubin is a potent cyclin-dependent kinases and GSK-3β inhibitor with IC50 of about 5 μM and 0.6 μM.

Name: L-carnitine
Information: L-carnitine is constituent of striated muscle and liver. It is used therapeutically to stimulate gastric and pancreatic secretions and in the treatment of hyperlipoproteinemias.

Name: Naringin Dihydrochalcone
Information: Naringin Dihydrochalcone(Naringin DC) is a new-style sweetening agent and an artificial sweetener derived from naringin and also an inhibitor of CYP enzymes.

Name: Polydatin
Information: Polydatin is a crystal component extracted from the root stem of perennial herbage Polygonum Cuspidatum Sieb.et Zucc.

Name: Quercetin
Information: Quercetin, a natural flavonoid present in vegetables, fruit and wine, is a stimulator of recombinant SIRT1 and also a PI3K inhibitor with IC50 of 2.4-5.4 μM. Phase 4.

Name: Sorbitol
Information: Sorbitol is a sugar alcohol and a sugar substitute.

Name: Salidroside
Information: Salidroside, a phenylpropanoid glycoside isolated from Rhodiola rosea, has been reported to have a broad spectrum of pharmacological properties.

Name: Palmatine chloride
Information: Palmatine hydrochloride (Palmatine chloride (6CI,7CI) Fibrauretin) is a hydrochloride salt of palmatine which is a protoberberine alkaloid.

Name: Sodium Danshensu
Information: Sodium Danshensu is a mono sodium of danshensu, which is a natural phenolic acid of caffeic acid derivatives isolated from Salvia miltiorrhiza.

Name: Isoliquiritigenin
Information: Isoliquiritigenin, an anti-tumor flavonoid from the root of Glycyrrhiza glabra, inhibits aldose reductase with an IC50 of 320 nM.

Name: Paeoniflorin
Information: Paeoniflorin is a herbal constituent extracted from the root of Paeonia albiflora Pall.

Name: Geniposide
Information: Geniposide is an iridoid glycoside isolated from the fruit of Gardenia jasminoides Ellis.

Name: Chondroitin sulfate
Information: Chondroitin sulfate (CS) is a major component of the extracellular matrix (ECM) of many connective tissues, including cartilage, bone, skin, ligaments and tendons. It reduces the IL-1β-induced nuclear factor-kB (NF-κB) translocation in chondrocytes in vitro.

Name: Ipriflavone (Osteofix)
Information: Ipriflavone (7-Isopropoxyisoflavon) is used to inhibit bone resorption.

Name: (S)-10-Hydroxycamptothecin
Information: 10-Hydroxycamptothecin is a DNA topoisomerase I inhibitor with potent anti-tumor activity.

Name: Hypoxanthine
Information: Hypoxanthine, a naturally occurring purine derivative, an intermediate product of uric acid synthesis, formed from adenylic acid and itself a precursor of xanthine.

Name: Rotundine
Information: Rotundine (L-tetrahydropalmatine, L-THP) is a selective dopamine D1 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 166 nM.

Name: Synephrine HCl
Information: SynephrineHCl (Oxedrine, p-Synephrine) is a sympathomimetic α-adrenergic receptor (AR) agonist.

Name: Guanosine
Information: Guanosine is a purine nucleoside comprising guanine attached to a ribose (ribofuranose) ring via a &beta-N9-glycosidic bond.

Name: Inosine
Information: Inosine is a nucleoside that is formed when hypoxanthine is attached to a ribose ring via a &beta-N9-glycosidic bond.

Name: Tolbutamide
Information: Tolbutamide is an inhibitor of potassium channel, used for type II diabetes.

Name: Levosimendan
Information: Levosimendan is a calcium sensitizer acting through calcium-dependent binding to cardiac troponin C (cTnC), provides treatment for heart failure.

Name: Gambogic Acid
Information: Gambogic Acid activates caspases with EC50 of 0.78-1.64 &muM and competitively inhibits Bcl-XL, Bcl-2, Bcl-W, Bcl-B, Bfl-1 and Mcl-1 with IC50 of 1.47, 1.21, 2.02, 0.66, 1.06 and 0.79 &muM, respectively.

Name: Forskolin
Information: Forskolin is a ubiquitous activator of eukaryotic adenylyl cyclase (AC) in a wide variety of cell types, commonly used to raise levels of cAMP in the study and research of cell physiology.

Name: Equol
Information: Equol ,a metabolite of soybeans, is an important isoflavone in humans，specifically binds to 5α-DHT, has a modest affinity for recombinant estrogen receptor ERβ. Phase 2.

Name: Amantadine HCl
Information: Amantadine HCl is used to treat or prevent infections of the respiratory tract caused by a certain virus.

Name: Amfebutamone (Bupropion) HCl
Information: Amfebutamone (Bupropion) HCl is a selective norepinephrine-dopamine reuptake inhibitor with IC50 of 6.5 and 3.4 μM for the reuptake of dopamine and norepinephrine, respectively.

Name: Benserazide HCl
Information: Benserazide HCl is a peripherally-acting aromatic L-amino acid decarboxylase (AAAD) or DOPA decarboxylase inhibitor.

Name: Bupivacaine HCl
Information: Bupivacaine HCl binds to the intracellular portion of voltage-gated sodium channels and blocks sodium influx into nerve cells, used for treating cardiac arrhythmias.

Name: Bethanechol chloride
Information: Bethanechol chloride is a selective muscarinic receptor agonist without any effect on nicotinic receptors.

Name: Chlorpromazine HCl
Information: Chlorpromazine HCl is a dopamine and potassium channel inhibitor with IC50 of 6.1 and 16 μM for inward-rectifying K+ currents and time-independent outward currents.

Name: Clindamycin HCl
Information: Clindamycin HCl inhibits protein synthesis by acting on the 50S ribosomal, used for the treatment of bacterial infections.

Name: Clonidine HCl
Information: Clonidine HCl is a direct-acting α2 adrenergic agonist with an ED50 of 0.02±0.01 mg/kg.

Name: Clozapine
Information: Clozapine is an atypical antipsychotic drug by acting as a 5-HT antagonist, used in the treatment of schizophrenia.

Name: Pramipexole
Information: Pramipexole is a partial/full D2S, D2L, D3, D4 receptor agonist with a Ki of 3.9, 2.2, 0.5 and 5.1 nM for D2S, D2L, D3, D4 receptor, respectively.

Name: Domperidone
Information: Domperidone is an oral dopamine D2 receptor antagonist, used to treat nausea and vomiting.

Name: Donepezil HCl
Information: Donepezil is a specific and potent AChE inhibitor for bAChE and hAChE with IC50 of 8.12 nM and 11.6 nM , respectively.

Name: Estriol
Information: Estriol is an antagonist of the G-protein coupled estrogen receptor in estrogen receptor-negative breast cancer cells.

Name: Famciclovir
Information: Famciclovir is a guanine analogue antiviral drug used for the treatment of various herpesvirus infections.

Name: Fenbendazole
Information: Fenbendazole is a broad spectrum benzimidazole anthelmintic used against gastrointestinal parasites with an IC50 of about 0.01 μg/mL.

Name: Fluocinolone Acetonide
Information: Fluocinolone Acetonide is a corticosteroid that binds to the cytosolic glucocorticoid receptor.

Name: Gallamine Triethiodide
Information: Gallamine Triethiodide is a cholinergic receptor blocker with an IC50 of 68.0 ± 8.4 μM.

Name: Hexestrol
Information: Hexestrol binds to ERα and ERβ with EC50 of 0.07 nM and 0.175 nM, respectively.

Name: Imatinib (STI571)
Information: Imatinib (STI571) is a multi-target inhibitor of tyrosine kinase with inhibition for v-Abl, c-Kit and PDGFR, IC50 values are 0.6 μM, 0.1 μM and 0.1 μM in cell-free or cell-based assays, respectively.

Name: Itraconazole
Information: Itraconazole is a relatively potent inhibitor of CYP3A4 with IC50 of 6.1 nM, used as a triazole antifungal agent.

Name: Lincomycin HCl
Information: Lincomycin hydrochloride(Lincocin) is the monohydrated salt of lincomycin, a substance produced by the growth of a member of the lincolnensis group of Streptomyces lincolnensis.

Name: Loperamide HCl
Information: Loperamide HCl is a selective μ-opioid receptor agonist opioid with Ki of 3.3 nM, 15-fold and 350-fold selective over the δ subtype and the κ subtype of the opioid receptor, used against diarrhea resulting from gastroenteritis or inflammatory bowel disease.

Name: Manidipine
Information: Manidipine is a calcium channel blocker (dihydropyridine type) that is used clinically as an antihypertensive.

Name: Manidipine 2HCl
Information: Manidipine 2HCl is a HCl salt form of Manidipine, which is a calcium channel blocker with IC50 of 2.6 nM, used clinically as an antihypertensive. Phase 4.

Name: Milrinone
Information: Milrinone is a phosphodiesterase 3 (PDE3) inhibitor, used to increase the heart's contractility.

Name: Mitoxantrone 2HCl
Information: Mitoxantrone is a type II topoisomerase inhibitor with IC50 of 2.0 μM, 0.42 mM for HepG2 and MCF-7/wt cells, respectively.

Name: Moroxydine HCl
Information: Moroxydine HCl is a synthetic antiviral compound chemically belonging to the series of the heterocyclic biguanidines.

Name: Mycophenolic acid
Information: Mycophenolic acid is a potent IMPDH inhibitor and the active metabolite of an immunosuppressive drug, used to prevent rejection in organ transplantation.

Name: Nateglinide
Information: Nateglinide is an insulin secretagog agent that lowers blood glucose levels by stimulating insulin secretion from the pancreas.

Name: Neostigmine Bromide
Information: Neostigmine Bromide is a reversible acetylcholinesterase inhibitor.

Name: Nitrendipine
Information: Nitrendipine is a dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker with an IC50 of 95 nM.

Name: Novobiocin Sodium
Information: Novobiocin Sodium is an aminocoumarin antibiotic that targets bacterial DNA gyrase (TopoIV), used to treat susceptible gram positive bacteria.

Name: Olanzapine
Information: Olanzapine is a high affinity for 5-HT2 serotonin and D2 dopamine receptor antagonist.

Name: Olopatadine HCl
Information: Olopatadine HCl is a histamine blocker and mast cell stabilizer with an IC50 of 559 μM for the release of histamine.

Name: Ozagrel
Information: Ozagrel is a selective thromboxane A(2) (TXA(2)) synthetase inhibitor with IC50 of 11 nM for rabbit platelet, used for the improvement of postoperative cerebrovascular contraction and accompanying cerebral ischaemia.

Name: Pancuronium dibromide
Information: Pancuronium dibromide is a competitive nicotinic acetylcholine receptor antagonist, used as a muscle relaxant.

Name: Phenoxybenzamine HCl
Information: Phenoxybenzamine HCl is a non-specific, irreversible alpha antagonist with an IC50 of 550 nM.

Name: Propafenone HCl
Information: Propafenone HCl is a classic anti-arrhythmic medication, which treats illnesses associated with rapid heartbeats such as atrial and ventricular arrhythmias.

Name: Pyrantel Pamoate
Information: Pyrantel pamoate, a broad-spectrum anthelmintic drug, is used to treat a number of parasitic worm infections.

Name: Quinine HCl Dihydrate
Information: Quinine HCl Dihydrate is a white crystalline K+ channel blocker, used to treat malaria.

Name: Racecadotril
Information: Racecadotril is a peripherally acting enkephalinase inhibitor with an IC50 of 4.5 μM.

Name: Ribavirin
Information: Ribavirin, a synthetic guanosine analogue, possesses a broad spectrum of activity against DNA and RNA viruses.

Name: Rosiglitazone maleate
Information: Rosiglitazone, a member of the thiazolidinedione class of antihyperglycaemic agents, is a high-affinity selective agonist of the peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-γ with IC50 of 42 nM.

Name: Roxithromycin
Information: Roxithromycin is a semi-synthetic macrolide antibiotic. It is used to treat respiratory tract, urinary and soft tissue infections.

Name: Salbutamol Sulfate
Information: Salbutamol Sulfate is a short-acting β2-adrenergic receptor agonist with an IC50 of 8.93 ?M.

Name: Scopolamine HBr
Information: Scopolamine HBr is a competitive muscarinic acetylcholine receptor with an IC50 of 55.3 nM.

Name: Sotalol HCl
Information: Sotalol is a non-selective beta blocker and a potassium channel blocker with an IC50 of 43 μM.

Name: Spectinomycin 2HCl
Information: Spectinomycin 2HCl is a new parenteral antibiotic prepared from Streptomyces spectabilis.

Name: Sulfadoxine
Information: Sulfadoxine is an ultra-long-lasting sulfonamide with an IC50 of 249 μg/ml for P. vivax.

Name: Tenoxicam
Information: Tenoxicam is a good HO. radicals scavenger with an IC50 of 56.7 μM.

Name: Tobramycin
Information: Tobramycin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic with an IC50 of 9.7 μM.

Name: Vardenafil HCl Trihydrate
Information: Vardenafil HCl Trihydrate is a new type PDE inhibitor with IC50 of 0.7 and 180 nM for PDE5 and PDE1, respectively.

Name: Xylazine HCl
Information: Xylazine is an α2-Adrenergic receptor agonist, used as a sedative and muscle relaxant.

Name: Maprotiline HCl
Information: Maprotiline HCl is a selective noradrenalin re-uptake inhibitor, used in the treatment of depression.

Name: NAD+
Information: NAD+ is a coenzyme composed of ribosylnicotinamide 5'-diphosphate coupled to adenosine 5'-phosphate by pyrophosphate linkage.

Name: Naphazoline HCl
Information: Naphazoline HCl is an ocular vasoconstrictor and imidazoline derivative sympathomimetic amine.

Name: Epinephrine bitartrate
Information: Epinephrine bitartrate is an alpha- and beta-adrenergic receptor stimulator.

Name: L-Adrenaline
Information: L-Adrenaline belongs to a group of the compounds known as catecholamines.

Name: Phenytoin Sodium
Information: Phenytoin Sodium is an inactive voltage-gated sodium channel stabilizer.

Name: Phenytoin
Information: Phenytoin is an inactive voltage-gated sodium channel stabilizer.

Name: Methacycline HCl
Information: Methacycline HCl is a tetracycline antibiotic, and also an inhibitor of epithelial–mesenchymal transition (EMT) with IC50 of roughly 5 μM, used to treat various infections.

Name: Ciclopirox
Information: Ciclopirox is a broad-spectrum antifungal agent working as an iron chelator.

Name: Dopamine HCl
Information: Dopamine HCl is a catecholamine neurotransmitter present in a wide variety of animals,And a dopamine D1-5 receptors agonist.

Name: 7-Aminocephalosporanic acid
Information: 7-Aminocephalosporanic acid is used for synthesis of cephalosporin antibiotics and intermediates.

Name: Ritodrine HCl
Information: Ritodrine HCl is a hydrochloride salt of ritodrine which is a β-2 adrenergic receptor agonist.

Name: Isoconazole nitrate
Information: Isoconazole nitrate (Travogen) is an azole antifungal reagent.

Name: Econazole nitrate
Information: Econazole Nitrate is a Ca2+ channel blocker, used as an antifungal medicine that fights infections caused by fungus.

Name: Miconazole
Information: Miconazole (Monistat) is an imidazole antifungal agent.

Name: Secnidazole
Information: Secnidazole (Flagentyl) is a nitroimidazole anti-infective.

Name: Acetanilide
Information: Acetanilide is an aniline derivative and has possess analgesic.

Name: Lomefloxacin HCl
Information: Lomefloxacin HCl is a hydrochloride salt of lomefloxacin and is a fluoroquinolone antibiotic.

Name: Clomipramine HCl
Information: Clomipramine HCl is a hydrochloride salt of clomipramine which is a serotonin transporter (SERT), norepinephrine transporter (NET) dopamine transporter (DAT) blocker with Ki of 0.14, 54 and 3 nM, respectively.

Name: Phenformin HCl
Information: Phenformin HCl is a hydrochloride salt of phenformin that is an anti-diabetic drug from the biguanide class. It activates AMPK, increasing activity and phosphorylation.

Name: Ceftiofur HCl
Information: Ceftiofur HCl is a cephalosporin antibiotic, used to treat both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria infection.

Name: Tiotropium Bromide hydrate
Information: Tiotropium Bromide hydrate is a monohydrate of tiotropium bromide (Spiriva Tiova BA 679BR tiopropium) that is an anticholinergic and bronchodilator and a muscarinic receptor antagonist.

Name: Trospium chloride
Information: Trospium chloride is a competitive muscarinic cholinergic receptor antagonist.

Name: Tolterodine tartrate
Information: Tolterodine tartrate is a tartrate salt of tolterodine that is a competitive muscarinic receptor antagonist.

Name: Sulbactam sodium
Information: Sulbactam sodium (Unasyn) is an irreversible β-lactamase inhibitor.

Name: Azelastine HCl
Information: Azelastine HCl is a potent, second-generation, selective, histamine receptor antagonist, used in the treatment of rhinitis.

Name: 5-Aminolevulinic acid HCl
Information: 5-Aminolevulinic Acid HCl is an intermediate in the porphyrin synthesis pathway, used as a photosensitizing agent and a antineoplastic agent.

Name: Daphnetin
Information: Daphnetin, a natural coumarin derivative, is a protein kinase inhibitor, inhibits EGFR, PKA and PKC with IC50 of 7.67 μM, 9.33 μM and 25.01 μM, respectively, also known to exhibit anti-inflammatory and anti-oxidant activities.

Name: Clarithromycin
Information: Clarithromycin is a macrolide antibiotic and a CYP3A4 inhibitor, used to treat a number of bacterial infections.

Name: Rosiglitazone
Information: Rosiglitazone is a potent antihyperglycemic agent and a potent thiazolidinedione insulin sensitizer with IC50 of 12, 4 and 9 nM for rat, 3T3-L1 and human adipocytes, respectively. Rosiglitazone is a pure ligand of PPAR-gamma, and has no PPAR-alpha-binding action.

Name: Terbinafine HCl
Information: Terbinafine HCl inhibits ergosterol synthesis by inhibiting squalene epoxidase, used as an antifungal drug.

Name: Cortisone acetate
Information: Cortisone acetate (Cortone) is an acetate salt form of cortisone that is a steroid hormone and a glucocorticoid.

Name: Amiloride HCl dihydrate
Information: Amiloride HCl dihydrate is a potent epithelial sodium channel (ENaC) blocker, used in the management of hypertension and congestive heart failure.

Name: Clomifene citrate
Information: Clomifene Citrate is a selective estrogen receptor modulator, used in the treatment of ovulation induction.

Name: Hydralazine HCl
Information: Hydralazine HCl is a hydrochloride salt of hydralazine, which is a direct-acting smooth muscle relaxant used to treat hypertension by acting as a vasodilator primarily in arteries and arterioles.

Name: Oxacillin sodium monohydrate
Information: Oxacillin sodium monohydrate is an antibacterial agent and is a narrow spectrum beta-lactam antibiotic of the penicillin class.

Name: Cloxacillin Sodium
Information: Cloxacillin Sodium is a sodium salt of cloxacillin that is a penicillinase-resistant, acid resistant, semi-synthetic penicillin.

Name: Amoxicillin Sodium
Information: Amoxicillin Sodium is a moderate- spectrum, bacteriolytic, β-lactam antibiotic.

Name: Isoprenaline HCl
Information: Isoprenaline is a non-selective beta-adrenergic receptor agonist, used for the treatment of bradycardia and heart block.

Name: Medroxyprogesterone acetate
Information: Medroxyprogesterone acetate (MPA) is a synthetic progestin and act as a potent progesterone receptor agonist, used to treat abnormal menstruation or irregular vaginal bleeding.

Name: Neomycin sulfate
Information: Neomycin sulfate is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, used to treat bacteria infections.

Name: Phenylephrine HCl
Information: Phenylephrine HCl is a selective α1-adrenergic receptor agonist, used primarily as a decongestant.

Name: Prednisolone Acetate
Information: Prednisolone Acetate is a synthetic corticosteroid drug that is particularly effective as an immunosuppressant agent.

Name: Streptomycin sulfate
Information: Streptomycin sulfate is a sulfate salt of streptomycin that is a protein synthesis inhibitor.

Name: Tetracaine HCl
Information: Tetracaine HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of tetracaine which is a potent local anaesthetic and a channel function allosteric inhibitor.

Name: Tetracycline HCl
Information: Tetracycline HCl is a hydrochloride salt of tetracycline that is a broad-spectrum polyketide antibiotic.

Name: Vancomycin HCl
Information: Vancomycin HCl is a hydrochloride of vancomycin that is a narrow-spectrum glycopeptide antibacterial agent.

Name: Xylometazoline HCl
Information: Xylometazoline is an α-adrenoceptor agonist commonly used as nasal decongestant, exhibits highest potency at α2B-adrenoceptor subtype with EC50 of 99 μM.

Name: Phenacetin
Information: Phenacetin is a non-opioid analgesic without anti-inflammatory properties.

Name: Zidovudine
Information: Zidovudine (ZDV) is a nucleoside analogue reverse transcriptase inhibitor, used to treat HIV.

Name: Quinapril HCl
Information: Quinapril HCl is the hydrochloride salt of quinapril that is an angiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitor with a Ki of 20 μM.

Name: Trazodone HCl
Information: Trazodone HCl is an antidepressant belonging to the class of serotonin receptor antagonists and reuptake inhibitors for treatment of anxiety disorders.

Name: Thiamphenicol
Information: Thiamphenicol is an antimicrobial antibiotic and a methyl-sulfonyl analogue of chloramphenicol.

Name: Clobetasol propionate
Information: Clobetasol propionate is an anti-inflammatory corticosteroid used to treat various skin disorders.

Name: Brompheniramine hydrogen maleate
Information: Brompheniramine hydrogen maleate is a histamine H1 receptors antagonist.

Name: Dimethyl Fumarate
Information: Dimethyl fumarate is the methyl ester of fumaric acid, used to treat people with relapsing forms of multiple sclerosis.

Name: Miglitol
Information: Miglitol is an oral anti-diabetic drug.

Name: Pioglitazone
Information: Pioglitazone is a selective peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-gamma (PPARγ) agonist, used to treat diabetes A weak activator for full-length hPPARα, but not full-length hPPARδ.

Name: Tolvaptan
Information: Tolvaptan is an orally effective nonpeptide arginine vasopressin V2 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 3 nM, used to treat hyponatremia.

Name: Pramiracetam
Information: Pramiracetam is a more potent nootropic drug derived from piracetam.

Name: Clindamycin palmitate HCl
Information: Clindamycin palmitate HCl is a water soluble hydrochloride salt of the ester of clindamycin and palmitic acid and a lincosamide antibiotic.

Name: Oseltamivir Phosphate
Information: Oseltamivir Phosphate is a potent and selective inhibitor of the neuraminidase that is essential for replication of influenza A and B viruses, used to prevent influenza.

Name: L-Thyroxine
Information: L-Thyroxine is a synthetic form of thyroxine and a hormone replacement drug.

Name: Gliclazide
Information: Gliclazide is a whole-cell beta-cell ATP-sensitive potassium currents blocker with an IC50 of 184 nM.

Name: Acemetacin
Information: Acemetacin is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug and a glycolic acid ester of indometacin that is a cyclooxygenase inhibitor.

Name: Tioxolone
Information: Tioxolone is a metalloenzyme carbonic anhydrase I inhibitor with a Ki of 91 nM.

Name: Dehydroepiandrosterone (DHEA)
Information: Dehydroepiandrosterone is an important endogenous steroid hormone, which is an androgen receptor antagonist and an estrogen receptor agonist.

Name: Idebenone
Information: Idebenone is a synthetic analog of coenzyme Q10 (CoQ10) and a brain stimulant.

Name: Mifepristone
Information: Mifepristone is a remarkably active antagonist of progesterone receptor and glucocorticoid receptor with IC50 of 0.2 nM and 2.6 nM, respectively.

Name: Buflomedil HCl
Information: Buflomedil HCl is a vasodilator used to treat claudication or the symptoms of peripheral arterial disease A nonselective alpha adrenergic receptor inhibitor.

Name: Fluocinonide
Information: Fluocinonide (Vanos) is a potent glucocorticoid steroid used topically as anti-inflammatory agent for the treatment of skin disorders such as eczema.

Name: Inulin
Information: Inulin(Inulin and sodium chloride), a starch found in the tubers and roots of many plants. Since it is hydrolyzable to fructose, it is classified as a fructosan.

Name: Lonidamine
Information: Lonidamine is an orally administered small molecule hexokinase inactivator.

Name: Clorsulon
Information: Clorsulon is used in the treatment of Fasciola hepatica infections in calves and sheep.

Name: Arecoline HBr
Information: Arecoline is a muscarinic acetylcholine receptor agonist.

Name: Noradrenaline bitartrate monohydrate
Information: Noradrenaline bitartrate monohydrate is a direct alpha-adrenergic receptors stimulator.

Name: TAK-733
Information: TAK-733 is a potent and selective MEK allosteric site inhibitor for MEK1 with IC50 of 3.2 nM, inactive to Abl1, AKT3, c-RAF, CamK1, CDK2, c-Met, etc. Phase 1.

Name: MG-132
Information: MG132 is a potent cell-permeable proteasome and calpain inhibitor with IC50s of 0.1 and 1.2 μM for the inhibition of proteasome and calpain, respectively.

Name: GSK256066
Information: GSK256066 is a selective PDE4B(equal affinity to isoforms A-D) inhibitor with IC50 of 3.2 pM, >380,000-fold selectivity versus PDE1/2/3/5/6 and >2500-fold selectivity against PDE4B versus PDE7.Phase 2.

Name: AZD5438
Information: AZD5438 is a potent inhibitor of CDK1/2/9 with IC50 of 16 nM/6 nM/20 nM in cell-free assays. It is less potent to CDK5/6 and also inhibits GSK3β. Phase 1.

Name: Omecamtiv mecarbil (CK-1827452)
Information: Omecamtiv mecarbil (CK-1827452) is a specific cardiac myosin activator and a clinical drug for left ventricular systolic heart failure. Phase 2.

Name: OSI-027
Information: OSI-027 is a selective and potent dual inhibitor of mTORC1 and mTORC2 with IC50 of 22 nM and 65 nM in cell-free assays, and more than 100-fold selectivity observed for mTOR than PI3Kα, PI3Kβ, PI3Kγ or DNA-PK. Phase 1.

Name: Fostamatinib (R788)
Information: Fostamatinib (R788), a prodrug of the active metabolite R406, is a Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 41 nM, strongly inhibits Syk but not Lyn, 5-fold less potent to Flt3. Phase 3.

Name: Rabusertib (LY2603618)
Information: Rabusertib (LY2603618) is a highly selective Chk1 inhibitor with potential anti-tumor activity in a cell-free assay. IC50=7 nM, showing approximately 100-fold more potent against Chk1 than against any of the other protein kinases evaluated.

Name: Gedatolisib (PF-05212384, PKI-587)
Information: Gedatolisib (PF-05212384, PKI-587) is a highly potent dual inhibitor of PI3Kα, PI3Kγ and mTOR with IC50 of 0.4 nM, 5.4 nM and 1.6 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. Phase 2.

Name: PNU-120596
Information: PNU-120596 is a positive allosteric modulator of α7 nAChR with EC50 of 216 nM.

Name: GW3965 HCl
Information: GW3965 HCl is a potent, selective LXR agonist for hLXRα and hLXRβ with EC50 of 190 and 30 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: URB597
Information: URB597 is a potent, orally bioavailable FAAH inhibitor with IC50 of 4.6 nM, with no activity on other cannabinoid-related targets. Phase 1.

Name: BMS-378806
Information: BMS-378806 selectively inhibits the binding of HIV-1 gp120 to the CD4 receptor with EC50 of 0.85-26.5 nM in virus.

Name: NPS-2143
Information: NPS-2143 is a novel potent and selective antagonist of Ca(2+) receptor with IC50 of 43 nM.

Name: Rebastinib (DCC-2036)
Information: Rebastinib (DCC-2036) is a conformational control Bcr-Abl inhibitor for Abl1(WT) and Abl1(T315I) with IC50 of 0.8 nM and 4 nM, also inhibits SRC, LYN, FGR, HCK, KDR, FLT3, and Tie-2, and low activity to seen towards c-Kit. Phase 1.

Name: CCT128930
Information: CCT128930 is a potent, ATP-competitive and selective inhibitor of Akt2 with IC50 of 6 nM in a cell-free assay, 28-fold greater selectivity for Akt2 than the closely related PKA kinase.

Name: Fasiglifam?(TAK-875)
Information: Fasiglifam?(TAK-875) is a selective GPR40 agonist with EC50 of 14 nM in human GPR40 expressing CHO cell line, 400-fold more potent than oleic acid.

Name: SNX-2112 (PF-04928473)
Information: SNX-2112 (PF-04928473) selectively binds to the ATP pocket of HSP90α and HSP90β with Ka of 30 nM and 30 nM, uniformly more potent than 17-AAG.

Name: PF-04929113 (SNX-5422)
Information: PF-04929113 (SNX-5422) is a potent and selective HSP90 inhibitor with Kd of 41 nM and induces Her-2 degradation with IC50 of 37 nM. Phase 1/2.

Name: Omipalisib (GSK2126458, GSK458)
Information: Omipalisib (GSK2126458, GSK458) is a highly selective and potent inhibitor of p110α/β/δ/γ, mTORC1/2 with Ki of 0.019 nM/0.13 nM/0.024 nM/0.06 nM and 0.18 nM/0.3 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. Phase 1.

Name: 5-hydroxymethyl Tolterodine (PNU 200577, 5-HMT, 5-HM)
Information: 5-hydroxymethyl tolterodine (PNU 200577) is a new muscarinic receptor antagonist with Kb of 0.84 nM.

Name: MK-0752
Information: MK-0752 is a moderately potent γ-secretase inhibitor, which reduces Aβ40 production with IC50 of 5 nM. Phase 1/2.

Name: WYE-125132 (WYE-132)
Information: WYE-125132 (WYE-132) is a highly potent, ATP-competitive mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 0.19 nM highly selective for mTOR versus PI3Ks or PI3K-related kinases hSMG1 and ATR.

Name: ICG-001
Information: ICG-001 antagonizes Wnt/β-catenin/TCF-mediated transcription and specifically binds to CREB-binding protein (CBP) with IC50 of 3 μM, but is not the related transcriptional coactivator p300.

Name: WAY-100635 Maleate
Information: WAY-100635 Maleate is a potent and selective 5-HT receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.95 nM.

Name: Clinofibrate
Information: Clinofibrate inhibits hydroxymethylglutaryl coenzyme A reductase (HMGCR) with IC50 of 0.47 mM, is a lipid-lowering agent used for controlling high cholesterol and triacylglyceride levels in the blood.

Name: Ciprofibrate
Information: Ciprofibrate is a peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor agonist.

Name: Dolutegravir (GSK1349572)
Information: Dolutegravir (GSK1349572) is a two-metal-binding HIV integrase inhibitor with IC50 of 2.7 nM in a cell-free assay, modest activity against raltegravir-resistant signature mutants Y143R, Q148K, N155H, and G140S/Q148H.

Name: PF-00562271 Besylate
Information: PF-00562271 is the benzenesulfonate salt of PF-562271, which is a potent, ATP-competitive, reversible inhibitor of FAK with IC50 of 1.5 nM, ~10-fold less potent for Pyk2 than FAK and >100-fold selectivity against other protein kinases, except for some CDKs. Phase 1.

Name: Trametinib (GSK1120212)
Information: Trametinib (GSK1120212) is a highly specific and potent MEK1/2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.92 nM/1.8 nM in cell-free assays, no inhibition of the kinase activities of c-Raf, B-Raf, ERK1/2.

Name: Flavopiridol HCl
Information: Flavopiridol HCl competes with ATP to inhibit CDKs including CDK1, CDK2, CDK4 and CDK6 with IC50 of ~ 40 nM in cell-free assays. It is 7.5-fold more selective for CDK1/2/4/6 than CDK7. Flavopiridol is initially found to inhibit EGFR and PKA. Phase 1/2.

Name: Ibrutinib (PCI-32765)
Information: Ibrutinib (PCI-32765) is a potent and highly selective Brutons tyrosine kinase (Btk) inhibitor with IC50 of 0.5 nM in cell-free assays, modestly potent to Bmx, CSK, FGR, BRK, HCK, less potent to EGFR, Yes, ErbB2, JAK3, etc.

Name: CHIR-124
Information: CHIR-124 is a novel and potent Chk1 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.3 nM in a cell-free assay. It shows 2,000-fold selectivity against Chk2, 500- to 5,000-fold less activity against CDK2/4 and Cdc2.

Name: KW-2478
Information: KW-2478 is a nonansamycin HSP90 inhibitor with IC50 of 3.8 nM. Phase 1.

Name: Mardepodect (PF-2545920)
Information: PF-2545920 is a potent and selective PDE10A inhibitor with IC50 of 0.37 nM, with >1000-fold selectivity over the PDE.

Name: R547
Information: R547 is a potent ATP-competitive inhibitor of CDK1/2/4 with Ki of 2 nM/3 nM/1 nM. It is less potent to CDK7 and GSK3α/β, while inactive to other kinases. Phase 1.

Name: ADX-47273
Information: ADX47273 is a potent and specific mGlu5 positive allosteric modulator(PAM) with EC50 of 0.17 μM, showing no activity at other mGlu subtypes.

Name: BMY 7378 Dihydrochloride
Information: BMY 7378 is a multi-targeted inhibitor of α2C-adrenoceptor and α1D-adrenoceptor with pKi of 6.54 and 8.2, respectively, and acts as a mixed agonist and antagonist for 5-HT1A receptor with pKi of 8.3.

Name: TG101209
Information: TG101209 is a selective JAK2 inhibitor with IC50 of 6 nM, less potent to Flt3 and RET with IC50 of 25 nM and 17 nM in cell-free assays, ~30-fold selective for JAK2 than JAK3, sensitive to JAK2V617F and MPLW515L/K mutations.

Name: Resminostat
Information: Resminostat dose-dependently and selectively inhibits HDAC1/3/6 with IC50 of 42.5 nM/50.1 nM/71.8 nM, less potent to HDAC8 with IC50 of 877 nM.

Name: Turofexorate Isopropyl (XL335)
Information: Turofexorate Isopropyl (XL335) is a potent, selective FXR agonist with EC50 of 4 nM, highly selective versus other nuclear receptors, such as LXR, PPAR, ER and etc. Phase 1.

Name: Nepicastat (SYN-117) HCl
Information: Nepicastat (SYN-117) HCl is a potent and selective inhibitor of both bovine and human dopamine-β-hydroxylase with IC50 of 8.5 nM and 9 nM, with negligible affinity for twelve other enzymes and thirteen neurotransmitter receptors. Phase 2.

Name: Apitolisib (GDC-0980, RG7422)
Information: Apitolisib (GDC-0980, RG7422) is a potent, class I PI3K inhibitor for PI3Kα/β/δ/γ with IC50 of 5 nM/27 nM/7 nM/14 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. Also a mTOR inhibitor with Ki of 17 nM in a cell-free assay, and highly selective versus other PIKK family kinases. Phase 2.

Name: RS-127445
Information: RS-127445 is a selective 5-HT2B receptor antagonist with pKi of 9.5 and pIC50 of 10.4, exhibits >1000-fold selectivity against other 5-HT receptors.

Name: CH5132799
Information: CH5132799 inhibits class I PI3Ks, particularly PI3Kα with IC50 of 14 nM less potent to PI3Kβδγ, while sensitive in PIK3CA mutations cell lines. Phase 1.

Name: KX2-391
Information: KX2-391, the first clinical Src inhibitor (peptidomimetic class) that targets the peptide substrate site of Src, with GI50 of 9-60 nM in cancer cell lines. Phase 2.

Name: GSK1838705A
Information: GSK1838705A is a potent IGF-1R inhibitor with IC50 of 2.0 nM, modestly potent to IR and ALK with IC50 of 1.6 nM and 0.5 nM, respectively, and little activity to other protein kinases.

Name: Geldanamycin
Information: Geldanamycin is a natural existing HSP90 inhibitor with Kd of 1.2 μM, specifically disrupts glucocorticoid receptor (GR)/HSP association.

Name: CP-91149
Information: CP-91149 is a selective glycogen phosphorylase (GP) inhibitor with IC50 of 0.13 μM in the presence of glucose, 5- to 10-fold less potent in the absence of glucose.

Name: TAK-901
Information: TAK-901 is a novel inhibitor of Aurora A/B with IC50 of 21 nM/15 nM. It is not a potent inhibitor of cellular JAK2, c-Src or Abl. Phase 1.

Name: AMG-900
Information: AMG 900 is a potent and highly selective pan-Aurora kinases inhibitor for Aurora A/B/C with IC50 of 5 nM/4 nM /1 nM. It is >10-fold selective for Aurora kinases than p38α, Tyk2, JNK2, Met and Tie2. Phase 1.

Name: Nilvadipine
Information: Nilvadipine is a potent calcium channel blocker with an IC50 of 0.03 nM.

Name: JTC-801
Information: JTC-801 is a selective opioid receptor-like1 (ORL1) receptor antagonist with IC50 of 94 nM, weakly inhibits receptors δ, κ, and μ.

Name: PH-797804
Information: PH-797804 is a novel pyridinone inhibitor of p38α with IC50 of 26 nM in a cell-free assay 4-fold more selective versus p38β and does not inhibit JNK2. Phase 2.

Name: Dacomitinib (PF299804, PF299)
Information: Dacomitinib (PF299804, PF299) is a potent, irreversible pan-ErbB inhibitor, mostly to EGFR with IC50 of 6 nM in a cell-free assay, effective against NSCLCs with EGFR or ERBB2 mutations (resistant to gefitinib) as well as those harboring the EGFR T790M mutation. Phase 2.

Name: AG-1478 (Tyrphostin AG-1478)
Information: AG-1478 (Tyrphostin AG-1478) is a selective EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 3 nM in cell-free assays, almost no activity on HER2-Neu, PDGFR, Trk, Bcr-Abl and InsR.

Name: Crenolanib (CP-868596)
Information: Crenolanib (CP-868596) is a potent and selective inhibitor of PDGFRα/β with Kd of 2.1 nM/3.2 nM in CHO cells, also potently inhibits FLT3, sensitive to D842V mutation not V561D mutation, >100-fold more selective for PDGFR than c-Kit, VEGFR-2, TIE-2, FGFR-2, EGFR, erbB2, and Src.

Name: MK-8776 (SCH 900776)
Information: MK-8776 (SCH 900776) is a selective Chk1 inhibitor with IC50 of 3 nM in a cell-free assay. It shows 500-fold selectivity against Chk2. Phase 2.

Name: Fedratinib (SAR302503, TG101348)
Information: Fedratinib (SAR302503, TG101348) is a selective inhibitor of JAK2 with IC50 of 3 nM in cell-free assays, 35- and 334-fold more selective for JAK2 versus JAK1 and JAK3. Phase 2.

Name: PAC-1
Information: PAC-1 is a potent procaspase-3 activator with EC50 of 0.22 μM and the first small molecule known to directly activate procaspase-3 to caspase-3.

Name: GSK1070916
Information: GSK1070916 is a reversible and ATP-competitive inhibitor of Aurora B/C with IC50 of 3.5 nM/6.5 nM. It displays >100-fold selectivity against the closely related Aurora A-TPX2 complex. Phase 1.

Name: Niraparib (MK-4827)
Information: Niraparib (MK-4827) is a selective inhibitor of PARP1/2 with IC50 of 3.8 nM/2.1 nM, with great activity in cancer cells with mutant BRCA-1 and BRCA-2. It is >330-fold selective against PARP3, V-PARP and Tank1. Phase 3.

Name: PHA-767491
Information: PHA-767491 is a potent ATP-competitive dual Cdc7/CDK9 inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM and 34 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.It displays ~20-fold selectivity against CDK1/2 and GSK3-β, 50-fold selectivity against MK2 and CDK5, 100-fold selectivity against PLK1 and CHK2.

Name: PF-04691502
Information: PF-04691502 is an ATP-competitive PI3K(α/β/δ/γ)/mTOR dual inhibitor with Ki of 1.8 nM/2.1 nM/1.6 nM/1.9 nM and 16 nM in cell-free assays, little activity against either Vps34, AKT, PDK1, p70S6K, MEK, ERK, p38, or JNK. Phase 2.

Name: AMG-458
Information: AMG 458 is a potent c-Met inhibitor with Ki of 1.2 nM, ~350-fold selectivity for c-Met than VEGFR2 in cells.

Name: Anacetrapib (MK-0859)
Information: Anacetrapib (MK0859) is a potent, selective, reversible rhCETP and mutant CETP(C13S) inhibitor with IC50 of 7.9 nM and 11.8 nM, increases HDL-C and decreases LDL-C, does not increase aldosterone or blood pressure. Phase 3.

Name: BGT226 (NVP-BGT226)
Information: BGT226 (NVP-BGT226) is a novel class I PI3K/mTOR inhibitor for PI3Kα/β/γ with IC50 of 4 nM/63 nM/38 nM. Phase 1/2.

Name: Milciclib (PHA-848125)
Information: Milciclib (PHA-848125) is a potent, ATP-competitive CDK inhibitor for CDK2 with IC50 of 45 nM. It is >3-fold more selective for CDK2 than CDK1, 2, 4, 5, and 7. Phase 2.

Name: Tivantinib (ARQ 197)
Information: Tivantinib (ARQ 197) is the first non-ATP-competitive c-Met inhibitor with Ki of 0.355 μM in a cell-free assay, little activity to Ron, and no inhibition to EGFR, InsR, PDGFRα or FGFR1/4. Phase 3.

Name: AT406 (SM-406)
Information: AT406 (SM-406) is a potent Smac mimetic and an antagonist of IAP (inhibitor of apoptosis protein via E3 ubiquitin ligase), binding to XIAP-BIR3, cIAP1-BIR3 and cIAP2-BIR3 with Ki of 66.4 nM, 1.9 nM, and 5.1 nM, 50- to 100-fold higher affinities than the Smac AVPI peptide. Phase 1.

Name: Varlitinib
Information: Varlitinib is a selective and potent ErbB1(EGFR) and ErbB2(HER2) inhibitor with IC50 of 7 nM and 2 nM, respectively. Phase 2.

Name: Evofosfamide (TH-302)
Information: TH-302 is selective hypoxia-activated prodrug targeting hypoxic regions of solid tumors with IC50 of 19 nM, demonstrates 270-fold enhanced cytotoxicity under hypoxia versus their potency under aerobic conditions, stable to cytochrome P450 metabolism.

Name: CUDC-907
Information: CUDC-907 is a dual PI3K and HDAC inhibitor for PI3Kα and HDAC1/2/3/10 with IC50 of 19 nM and 1.7 nM/5 nM/1.8 nM/2.8 nM, respectively. Phase 1.

Name: Canagliflozin
Information: Canagliflozin is a highly potent and selective SGLT2 inhibitor for hSGLT2 with IC50 of 2.2 nM in a cell-free assay, exhibits 413-fold selectivity over hSGLT1.

Name: Alectinib (CH5424802)
Information: Alectinib (CH5424802) is a potent ALK inhibitor with IC50 of 1.9 nM in cell-free assays, sensitive to L1196M mutation and higher selectivity for ALK than PF-02341066, NVP-TAE684 and PHA-E429.

Name: MK-2048
Information: MK-2048 is a potent inhibitor of integrase (IN) and INR263K with IC50 of 2.6 nM and 1.5 nM, respectively.

Name: Dinaciclib (SCH727965)
Information: Dinaciclib (SCH727965) is a novel and potent CDK inhibitor for CDK2, CDK5, CDK1 and CDK9 with IC50 of 1 nM, 1 nM, 3 nM and 4 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. It also blocks thymidine (dThd) DNA incorporation. Phase 3.

Name: Dovitinib (TKI-258) Dilactic Acid
Information: Dovitinib Dilactic acid (TKI258 Dilactic acid) is the Dilactic acid of Dovitinib, which is a multitargeted RTK inhibitor, mostly for class III (FLT3/c-Kit) with IC50 of 1 nM/2 nM, also potent to class IV (FGFR1/3) and class V (VEGFR1-4) RTKs with IC50 of 8-13 nM, less potent to InsR, EGFR, c-Met, EphA2, Tie2, IGFR1 and HER2. Phase 4.

Name: MK-5108 (VX-689)
Information: MK-5108 (VX-689) is a highly selective Aurora A inhibitor with IC50 of 0.064 nM in a cell-free assay and is 220- and 190-fold more selective for Aurora A than Aurora B/C, while it inhibits TrkA with less than 100-fold selectivity. Phase 1.

Name: Dalcetrapib (JTT-705, RO4607381)
Information: Dalcetrapib (JTT-705) is a rhCETP inhibitor with IC50 of 0.2 μM that increases the plasma HDL cholesterol. Phase 3.

Name: SB705498
Information: SB705498 is a TRPV1 antagonist for hTRPV1, antagonizes capsaicin, acid, and heat activation of TRPV1 with IC50 of 3 nM, 0.1 nM and 6 nM, shows a degree of voltage dependence, exhibits >100-fold selectivity for TRPV1 over TRPM8. Phase 2.

Name: MK-2461
Information: MK-2461 is a potent, multi-targeted inhibitor for c-Met(WT/mutants) with IC50 of 0.4-2.5 nM, less potent to Ron, Flt1 8- to 30-fold greater selectivity of c-Met targets versus FGFR1, FGFR2, FGFR3, PDGFRβ, KDR, Flt3, Flt4, TrkA, and TrkB. Phase 1/2. .

Name: CPI-613
Information: CPI-613, a lipoate analog, inhibits mitochondrial enzymes pyruvate dehydrogenase (PDH) and α-ketoglutarate dehydrogenase in NCI-H460 cell line, disrupts tumor cell mitochondrial metabolism. Phase 2.

Name: GW842166X
Information: GW842166X is a potent and highly selective agonist of cannabinoid receptor CB2 receptor with EC50 of 63 nM, shows no significant activity at CB1 receptor. Phase 2.

Name: RITA (NSC 652287)
Information: RITA (NSC 652287) induces both DNA-protein and DNA-DNA cross-links with no detectable DNA single-strand breaks, and also inhibits MDM2-p53 interaction by targeting p53.

Name: Vistusertib (AZD2014)
Information: Vistusertib (AZD2014) is a novel mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 2.8 nM in a cell-free assay highly selective against multiple PI3K isoforms (α/β/γ/δ). AZD2014 showed no or weak binding to the majority of kinases when tested at 1 μM.

Name: TAK-285
Information: TAK-285 is a novel dual HER2 and EGFR(HER1) inhibitor with IC50 of 17 nM and 23 nM, >10-fold selectivity for HER1/2 than HER4, less potent to MEK1/5, c-Met, Aurora B, Lck, CSK etc. Phase 1.

Name: A-803467
Information: A-803467 is a selective NaV1.8 channel blocker with IC50 of 8 nM, blocks tetrodotoxin-resistant currents, exhibits >100-fold selectivity against human NaV1.2, NaV1.3, NaV1.5, and NaV1.7.

Name: Laquinimod
Information: Laquinimod is a potent immunomodulator. Phase 3.

Name: Capmatinib (INCB28060)
Information: Capmatinib (INCB28060) is a novel, ATP-competitive inhibitor of c-MET with IC50 of 0.13 nM in a cell-free assay, inactive against RONβ, as well as EGFR and HER-3. Phase 1.

Name: Tofacitinib (CP-690550,Tasocitinib)
Information: Tofacitinib (CP-690550,Tasocitinib) is a novel inhibitor of JAK3 with IC50 of 1 nM in cell-free assays, 20- to 100-fold less potent against JAK2 and JAK1.

Name: Istradefylline
Information: Istradefylline is a selective adenosine A2A receptor (A2AR) antagonist with Ki of 2.2 nM. Phase 3.

Name: Sotrastaurin
Information: Sotrastaurin is a potent and selective pan-PKC inhibitor, mostly for PKCθ with Ki of 0.22 nM in a cell-free assay inactive to PKCζ. Phase 2.

Name: Torcetrapib
Information: Torcetrapib is a CETP inhibitor with IC50 of 37 nM, elevates HDL-C and reduces nonHDL-C in plasma. Phase 3.

Name: Sofosbuvir (PSI-7977, GS-7977)
Information: Sofosbuvir (PSI-7977, GS-7977) is a HCV NS5B polymerase inhibitor for the treatment of chronic hepatitis C virus (HCV) infection.

Name: WP1066
Information: WP1066 is a novel inhibitor of JAK2 and STAT3 with IC50 of 2.30 μM and 2.43 μM in HEL cells shows activity to JAK2, STAT3, STAT5, and ERK1/2 not JAK1 and JAK3. Phase 1.

Name: Lonafarnib
Information: Lonafarnib is an orally bioavailable FPTase inhibitor for H-ras, K-ras-4B and N-ras with IC50 of 1.9 nM, 5.2 nM and 2.8 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. Phase 3.

Name: AZD4547
Information: AZD4547 is a novel selective FGFR inhibitor targeting FGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 0.2 nM/2.5 nM/1.8 nM in cell-free assays, weaker activity against FGFR4, VEGFR2(KDR), and little activity observed against IGFR, CDK2, and p38. Phase 2/3.

Name: Galeterone
Information: Galeterone is a selective CYP17 inhibitor and androgen receptor (AR) antagonist with IC50 of 300 nM and 384 nM, respectively, and is a potent inhibitor of human prostate tumor growth. Phase 2.

Name: Dabrafenib (GSK2118436)
Information: Dabrafenib (GSK2118436) is a mutant BRAFV600 specific inhibitor with IC50 of 0.8 nM in cell-free assays, with 4- and 6-fold less potency against B-Raf(wt) and c-Raf, respectively.

Name: Ipatasertib (GDC-0068)
Information: Ipatasertib (GDC-0068) is a highly selective pan-Akt inhibitor targeting Akt1/2/3 with IC50 of 5 nM/18 nM/8 nM in cell-free assays, 620-fold selectivity over PKA. Phase 2.

Name: MPEP
Information: MPEP is a selective mGlu5 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 36 nM, exhibits no appreciable activity at mGlu1b/2/3/4a/7b/8a/6 receptors.

Name: Sapanisertib (INK 128, MLN0128)
Information: Sapanisertib (INK 128, MLN0128) is a potent and selective mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 1 nM in cell-free assays >200-fold less potent to class I PI3K isoforms, superior in blocking mTORC1/2 and sensitive to pro-invasion genes (vs Rapamycin). Phase 1.

Name: AT101
Information: AT101, the R-(-) enantiomer of Gossypol acetic acid, binds with Bcl-2, Bcl-xL and Mcl-1 with Ki of 0.32 μM, 0.48 μM and 0.18 μM in cell-free assays does not inhibit BIR3 domain and BID. Phase 2.

Name: Ciproxifan Maleate
Information: Ciproxifan is a highly potent and selective histamin H3-receptor antagonist with IC50 of 9.2 nM, with low apparent affinity at other receptor subtypes.

Name: Alpelisib (BYL719)
Information: Alpelisib (BYL719) is a potent and selective PI3Kα inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM in a cell-free assay, and minimal effect on PI3Kβ/γ/δ. Phase 2.

Name: Tacedinaline (CI994)
Information: Tacedinaline (CI994) is a selective class I HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 0.9, 0.9, 1.2, and >20 μM for human HDAC 1, 2, 3, and 8, respectively. Phase 3.

Name: TAE226 (NVP-TAE226)
Information: TAE226 (NVP-TAE226) is a potent FAK inhibitor with IC50 of 5.5 nM and modestly potent to Pyk2, ~10- to 100-fold less potent against InsR, IGF-1R, ALK, and c-Met.

Name: OC000459
Information: OC000459 is a potent and selective D prostanoid receptor 2 (DP2) antagonist with IC50 of 13 nM. Phase 2.

Name: Tideglusib
Information: Tideglusib is an irreversible, non ATP-competitive GSK-3β inhibitor with IC50 of 60 nM in a cell-free assay fails to inhibit kinases with a Cys homologous to Cys-199 located in the active site. Phase 2.

Name: JNJ-1661010
Information: JNJ-1661010 is a potent and selective FAAH inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM (rat) and 12 nM (human), exhibits >100-fold selectivity for FAAH-1 when compared to FAAH-2.

Name: Clindamycin
Information: Clindamycin inhibits protein synthesis by acting on the 50S ribosomal, used for the treatment of bacterial infections.

Name: Epiandrosterone
Information: Epiandrosterone is a steroid hormone with weak androgenic activity, is a natural metabolite of DHEA.

Name: Apalutamide?(ARN-509)
Information: Apalutamide (ARN-509) is a selective and competitive androgen receptor inhibitor with IC50 of 16 nM in a cell-free assay, useful for prostate cancer treatment. Phase 3.

Name: SAR131675
Information: SAR131675 is a VEGFR3 inhibitor with IC50/Ki of 23 nM/12 nM in cell-free assays, about 50- and 10-fold more selective for VEGFR3 than VEGFR1/2, little activity against Akt1, CDKs, PLK1, EGFR, IGF-1R, c-Met, Flt2 etc.

Name: Semaxanib (SU5416)
Information: Semaxanib (SU5416) is a potent and selective VEGFR(Flk-1/KDR) inhibitor with IC50 of 1.23 μM, 20-fold more selective for VEGFR than PDGFRβ, lack of activity against EGFR, InsR and FGFR. Phase 3.

Name: SB269970 HCl
Information: SB269970 HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of SB-269970, which is a 5-HT7 receptor antagonist with pKi of 8.3, exhibits >50-fold selectivity against other receptors.

Name: Baricitinib (LY3009104, INCB028050)
Information: Baricitinib (LY3009104, INCB028050) is a selective JAK1 and JAK2 inhibitor with IC50 of 5.9 nM and 5.7 nM in cell-free assays, ~70 and ~10-fold selective versus JAK3 and Tyk2, no inhibition to c-Met and Chk2. Phase 3.

Name: Carfilzomib (PR-171)
Information: Carfilzomib (PR-171) is an irreversible proteasome inhibitor with IC50 of <5 nM in ANBL-6 cells, displayed preferential in vitro inhibitory potency against the ChT-L activity in the β5 subunit, but little or no effect on the PGPH and T-L activities.

Name: SB 271046 hydrochloride
Information: SB 271046 hydrochloride is a potent, selective and orally active 5-HT6 receptor antagonist with pKi of 8.9, exhibits 200-fold greater selectivity over other 5-HT receptor subtypes.

Name: (-)-MK 801 maleate
Information: (-)-MK-801 (Dizocilpine) is a potent N-methyl-D-aspartate (NMDA) receptor antagonist with Ki of 30.5 nM.

Name: Golvatinib (E7050)
Information: Golvatinib (E7050) is a dual c-Met and VEGFR-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 14 nM and 16 nM, does not inhibit bFGF-stimulated HUVEC growth (up to 1000 nM). Phase 1/2.

Name: IMD 0354
Information: IMD-0354 is an IKKβ inhibitor and blocks IκBα phosphorylation in NF-κB pathway.

Name: WHI-P154
Information: WHI-P154 is a potent JAK3 inhibitor with IC50 of 1.8 μM, no activity against JAK1 or JAK2, also inhibits EGFR, Src, Abl, VEGFR and MAPK, prevents Stat3, but not Stat5 phosphorylation.

Name: Alogliptin（SYK-322）benzoate
Information: Alogliptin is a potent, selective inhibitor of DPP-4 with IC50 of <10 nM, exhibits greater than 10,000-fold selectivity over DPP-8 and DPP-9.

Name: GW5074
Information: GW5074 is a potent and selective c-Raf inhibitor with IC50 of 9 nM, no effect on the activities of JNK1/2/3, MEK1, MKK6/7, CDK1/2, c-Src, p38 MAP, VEGFR2 or c-Fms is noted.

Name: Camostat Mesilate
Information: Camostat is a trypsin-like protease inhibitor, inhibits airway epithelial sodium channel (ENaC) function with IC50 of 50 nM, less potent to trpsin, prostasin and matriptase.

Name: Prucalopride
Information: Prucalopride is a selective, high affinity 5-HT receptor agonist for 5-HT4A and 5-HT4B receptor with Ki of 2.5 nM and 8 nM, respectively, exhibits >290-fold selectivity against other 5-HT receptor subtypes.

Name: (+)-MK 801 maleate
Information: (+)-MK-801 is a potent, selective and non-competitive NMDA receptor antagonist with Kd of 37.2 nM in rat brain membranes.

Name: L-NAME HCl
Information: L-NAME is a nonselective inhibitor of nitric oxide synthetases (NOS) for nNOS (bovine), eNOS (human), and iNOS (murine), with Ki of 15 nM, 39 nM and 4.4 μM, respectively.

Name: AMD3465 hexahydrobromide
Information: AMD3465 is a monomacrocyclic CXCR4 antagonist.

Name: Acesulfame Potassium
Information: Acesulfame potassium is a non-nutritive sweetener.

Name: PF-562271
Information: PF-562271 is a potent, ATP-competitive, reversible inhibitor of FAK with IC50 of 1.5 nM in cell-free assays, ~10-fold less potent for Pyk2 than FAK and >100-fold selectivity against other protein kinases, except for some CDKs.

Name: SB742457
Information: SB742457 is a highly selective 5-HT6 receptor antagonist with pKi of 9.63, exhibits >100-fold selectivity over other receptors. Phase 2.

Name: Cobicistat (GS-9350)
Information: Cobicistat (GS-9350) is a potent and selective inhibitor of CYP3A with IC50 of 30-285 nM.

Name: S-Ruxolitinib (INCB018424)
Information: S-Ruxolitinib is the chirality of INCB018424, which is the first potent, selective, JAK1/2 inhibitor to enter the clinic with IC50 of 3.3 nM/2.8 nM, >130-fold selectivity for JAK1/2 versus JAK3. Phase 3.

Name: Lumiracoxib
Information: Lumiracoxib is a novel, selective COX-2 inhibitor with Ki of 0.06 μM. It also inhibits COX1 with Ki of 3 μM.

Name: PF-477736
Information: PF-477736 is a selective, potent and ATP-competitive Chk1 inhibitor with Ki of 0.49 nM in a cell-free assay and also inhibits VEGFR2, Aurora-A, FGFR3, Flt3, Fms (CSF1R), Ret and Yes. It shows ~100-fold selectivity for Chk1 than Chk2. Phase 1.

Name: JNJ-7777120
Information: JNJ-7777120 is the first potent and selective non-imidazole histamine H4 receptor antagonist with Ki of 4.5 nM, exhibits >1000-fold selectivity over the other histamin receptors.

Name: Ki16198
Information: Ki16198 is the methyl ester of Ki16425, which is a LPA antagonist and inhibits LPA1- and LPA3-induced inositol phosphate production with Ki of 0.34 μM and 0.93 μM, respectively, shows weaker inhibition for LPA2, no activity at LPA4, LPA5, LPA6.

Name: Pirfenidone
Information: Pirfenidone is an inhibitor for TGF-β production and TGF-β stimulated collagen production, reduces production of TNF-α and IL-1β, and also has anti-fibrotic and anti-inflammatory properties. Phase 3.

Name: Hygromycin B
Information: Hygromycin B, a selective antibiotic that is effective on most bacteria, fungi and higher eukaryotes, inhibits protein synthesis by interfering with translocation and causing mistranslation at the 70S ribosome.

Name: Tempol
Information: Tempol is a superoxide scavenger that displays neuroprotective, anti-inflammatory and analgesic effects. Phase 2.

Name: Dapivirine (TMC120)
Information: Dapivirine (TMC120) is a non-nucleoside inhibitor for HIV reverse transcriptase with IC50 of 24 nM, inhibits a broad panel of HIV-1 isolates from different classes, inclucing a wide range of NNRTI-resistant isolates. Phase 3.

Name: HC-030031
Information: HC-030031 is a selective TRPA1 channel blocker that antagonizes AITC- and formalin-evoked calcium influx with IC50 of 6.2 μM and 5.3 μM respectively.

Name: Mozavaptan
Information: Mozavaptan is a novel competitive vasopressin receptor antagonist for both V1 and V2 receptors with IC50 of 1.2 μM and 14 nM, respectively.

Name: Icotinib
Information: Icotinib is a potent and specific EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM, including the EGFR, EGFR(L858R), EGFR(L861Q), EGFR(T790M) and EGFR(T790M, L858R).

Name: CHIR-99021 (CT99021) HCl
Information: CHIR-99021 HCl (CT99021) is hydrochloride of CHIR-99021, which is a GSK-3α/β inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM/6.7 nM CHIR-99021 shows greater than 500-fold selectivity for GSK-3 versus its closest homologs Cdc2 and ERK2.

Name: Evacetrapib (LY2484595)
Information: Evacetrapib (LY2484595) is a potent and selective inhibitor of CETP with IC50 of 5.5 nM, elevates HDL cholesterol without increases in aldosterone or blood pressure. Phase 3.

Name: TDZD-8
Information: TDZD-8 is a non-ATP competitive GSK-3β inhibitor with IC50 of 2 μM minimal inhibitory effect observed on CDK1, casein kinase II, PKA and PKC.

Name: TAK-715
Information: TAK-715 is a p38 MAPK inhibitor for p38α with IC50 of 7.1 nM, 28-fold more selective for p38α over p38β, no inhibition to p38γ/δ, JNK1, ERK1, IKKβ, MEKK1 or TAK1. Phase 2.

Name: Carbazochrome sodium sulfonate (AC-17)
Information: Carbazochrome sodium sulfonate (AC-17) is an antihemorrhagic for use in the treatment of hemorrhoids.

Name: Clevudine
Information: Clevudine is an antiviral drug for the treatment of hepatitis B.

Name: Rivaroxaban
Information: Rivaroxaban is a direct inhibitor of Factor Xa with Ki and IC50 of 0.4 nM and 0.7 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. It is selective for human factor Xa, for which it has >10 000-fold greater selectivity than for other biologically relevant serine proteases (IC50 >20 μM).

Name: Prostaglandin E2 (PGE2)
Information: Prostaglandin E2 palys important effects in labour (softens cervix and causes uterine contraction) and also stimulates osteoblasts to release factors that stimulate bone resorption by osteoclasts.

Name: Paroxetine HCl
Information: Paroxetine HCl is an antidepressant drug of the SSRI type.

Name: Zanamivir
Information: Zanamivir is a neuraminidase inhibitor used in the treatment and prophylaxis of influenza caused by influenza A virus and influenza B virus.

Name: Zaltoprofen
Information: Zaltoprofen is an inhibitor of COX-1 and COX-2 for treatment of arthritis.

Name: Pazopanib
Information: Pazopanib is a novel multi-target inhibitor of VEGFR1, VEGFR2, VEGFR3, PDGFR, FGFR, c-Kit and c-Fms with IC50 of 10 nM, 30 nM, 47 nM, 84 nM, 74 nM, 140 nM and 146 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Plerixafor 8HCl (AMD3100 8HCl)
Information: Plerixafor 8HCl (AMD3100 8HCl) is the hydrochloride of Plerixafor, a chemokine receptor antagonist for CXCR4 and CXCL12-mediated chemotaxis with IC50 of 44 nM and 5.7 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Amoxicillin
Information: Amoxicillin is a moderate-spectrum, bacteriolytic, β-lactam antibiotic used to treat bacterial infections caused by susceptible microorganisms.

Name: Aspirin
Information: Aspirin is a salicylate, and irreversible COX1 and COX2 inhibitor, used as an analgesic to relieve minor aches and pains, as an antipyretic to reduce fever, and as an anti-inflammatory medication.

Name: Niflumic acid
Information: Niflumic acid is an inhibitor of cyclooxygenase-2 used for joint and muscular pain.

Name: Ciclopirox ethanolamine
Information: Ciclopirox ethanolamine (Ciclopirox olamine, HOE 296) is a broad-spectrum antifungal agent working as an iron chelator.

Name: Rimonabant
Information: Rimonabant is a selective antagonist of CB1 with IC50 of 13.6 nM and EC50 of 17.3 nM in hCB1 transfected HEK 293 membrane.

Name: Cabazitaxel
Information: Cabazitaxel is a semi-synthetic derivative of a natural taxoid that kills cancer cells by inhibiting cell division and growth. Cabazitaxel exerts its effects by inhibiting microtubule growth and assembly, processes that are essential for cells to divide.

Name: Bufexamac
Information: Bufexamac is a COX inhibitor for IFN-α release with EC50 of 8.9 μM.

Name: Lamotrigine
Information: Lamotrigine is a novel anticonvulsant drug for inhibition of 5-HT with IC50 of 240 μM and 474 μM in human platelets and rat brain synaptosomes, and also is a sodium channel blocker.

Name: Fenoprofen calcium hydrate
Information: Fenoprofen calcium hydrate is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID).

Name: Geneticin (G418 Sulfate)
Information: Geneticin (G418 Sulfate), an aminoglycoside antibiotic, is an elongation inhibitor of 80 S ribosomes that blocks polypeptide synthesis by inhibiting the elongation step in both prokaryotic and eukaryotic cells.

Name: Linagliptin
Information: Linagliptin is a highly potent, selective DPP-4 inhibitor with IC50 of 1 nM and exhibits a 10,000-fold higher selectivity for DPP-4 than for other dipeptidyl peptidases such as DPP-2, DPP-8, and DPP-9.

Name: Bindarit
Information: Bindarit exhibits selective inhibition against monocyte chemotactic proteins MCP-1/CCL2, MCP-3/CCL7 and MCP-2/CCL8.

Name: Vildagliptin (LAF-237)
Information: Vildagliptin (LAF-237) inhibits DPP?4 with IC50 of 2.3 nM.

Name: Daunorubicin HCl
Information: Daunorubicin HCl inhibits both DNA and RNA synthesis and inhibits DNA synthesis with Ki of 0.02 μM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Pravastatin sodium
Information: Pravastatin sodium is an HMG-CoA reductase inhibitor against sterol synthesis with IC50 of 5.6 μM.

Name: Bepotastine Besilate
Information: Bepotastine is a non-sedating, selective antagonist of histamine 1 (H1) receptor with pIC50 of 5.7.

Name: Fosaprepitant dimeglumine salt
Information: Fosaprepitant is a water-soluble phosphoryl prodrug for Aprepitant which is a NK1 antagonist.

Name: Rofecoxib
Information: Rofecoxib is a COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 18 nM.

Name: Cinepazide maleate
Information: Cinepazide maleate is a maleate salt form of cinepazide which is a vasodilator.

Name: Azilsartan
Information: Azilsartan is an angiotensin II type 1 (AT1) receptor antagonist with IC50 of 2.6 nM.

Name: Otilonium Bromide
Information: Otilonium bromide is an antimuscarinic.

Name: Solifenacin succinate
Information: Solifenacin succinate is a urinary antispasmodic of the antimuscarinic class.

Name: Palonosetron HCl
Information: Palonosetron HCl is a 5-HT3 antagonist used in the prevention and treatment of chemotherapy-induced nausea and vomiting.

Name: Bosentan Hydrate
Information: Bosentan is an endothelin (ET) receptor antagonist for ET-A and ET-B with Ki of 4.7 nM and 95 nM, respectively.

Name: Rupatadine Fumarate
Information: Rupatadine is an inhibitor of PAFR and histamine (H1) receptor with Ki of 550 nM and 102 nM, respectively.

Name: Azelnidipine
Information: Azelnidipine is a dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker.

Name: Alverine Citrate
Information: Alverine citrate is a drug used for functional gastrointestinal disorders.

Name: Besifloxacin HCl
Information: Besifloxacin HCl is a fourth-generation fluoroquinolone antibiotic.

Name: Miltefosine
Information: Miltefosine inhibits PI3K/Akt activity with ED50 of 17.2 μM and 8.1 μM in carcinoma cell lines A431 and HeLa, first oral drug for Visceral leishmaniasis, effective against both promastigotes and amastigotes.

Name: Azilsartan Medoxomil
Information: Azilsartan Medoxomil is a potent angiotensin II type 1 (AT1) receptor antagonist, inhibits the RAAS, with an IC50 of 2.6 nM, exhibits >10,000-fold selectivity over AT2.

Name: Danofloxacin Mesylate
Information: Danofloxacin is a fluoroquinolone antibacterial for veterinary use, with MIC90 of 0.28 μM.

Name: Enrofloxacin
Information: Enrofloxacin is a fluoroquinolone antibiotic.

Name: Medetomidine HCl
Information: Medetomidine is a selective α2-adrenoceptor agonist, with Ki of 1.08 nM, exhibts 1620-fold selectivity over α1-adrenoceptor.

Name: Epinephrine HCl
Information: Epinephrine HCl is a hormone and a neurotransmitter.

Name: Diclofenac Potassium
Information: Diclofenac potassium is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug taken to reduce inflammation and as an analgesic reducing pain in certain conditions.

Name: Diclofenac Diethylamine
Information: Diclofenac diethylamine is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug taken to reduce inflammation and as an analgesic reducing pain in certain conditions. Diclofenac exerts its action via inhibition of prostaglandin synthesis by inhibiting cyclooxygenase-1 (COX-1) and cyclooxygenase-2 (COX-2) with relative equipotency.

Name: Ambroxol HCl
Information: AmbroxolHCl is a potent inhibitor of the neuronal Na+ channels, inhibits TTX-resistant Na+ currents with IC50 of 35.2 μM and 22.5 μM for tonic and phasic block, inhibits TTX-sensitive Na+ currents with IC50 of 100 μM. Phase 3.

Name: Amikacin disulfate
Information: Amikacin sulfate binds to 16S rRNA (bacterial 30S ribosome), causing misreading of mRNA and supressing proteins synthesis.

Name: Naloxone HCl
Information: Naloxone HCl is an opioid inverse agonist drug used to counter the effects of opiate overdose.

Name: Chlorhexidine?2HCl
Information: Chlorhexidine hydrochloride is an antiseptic effective against a wide variety of gram-negative and gram-positive organisms.

Name: Piracetam
Information: Piracetam is a cyclic derivative of the neurotransmitter gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA), used in treatment of a wide range of cognitive disorders.

Name: Vanillin
Information: Vanillin, 4-hydroxy-3-methoxybenzaldehyde, is a food additive.

Name: (R)-baclofen
Information: (R)-baclofen is a derivative of gamma-aminobutyric acid primarily used to treat spasticity.

Name: Caspofungin Acetate
Information: Caspofungin acetate is an lipopeptide antifungal β-1,3-glucan synthase inhibitor.

Name: Chlorthalidone
Information: Chlortalidone is a diuretic drug widely used in antihypertensive therapy.

Name: Dexmedetomidine
Information: Dexmedetomidine is a sedative medication used by intensive care units and anesthetists.

Name: Foscarnet Sodium
Information: Foscarnet Sodium inhibits viral RNA polymerases, reverse transcriptase, and DNA polymerases through noncompetitive inhibition with dNTPs.

Name: Tazobactam
Information: Tazobactam is a β-lactamases Inhibitor with antibacterial activity. It also inhibits the class D oxacillinase OXA-2. It is used in combination with piperacillin and other β-lactam antibiotics to broaden their spectrum and enhance their effect.

Name: Beclomethasone dipropionate
Information: Beclomethasone dipropionate is a potent glucocorticoid steroid used for the treatment of rhinitis and sinusitis.

Name: Atovaquone
Information: Atovaquone is a medication used to treat or prevent for pneumocystis pneumonia, toxoplasmosis, malaria, and babesia.

Name: Etravirine (TMC125)
Information: Etravirine (TMC125) is a non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NNRTI) used for the treatment of HIV.

Name: Ulipristal
Information: Ulipristal is a selective SPRM for emergency contraception after an unprotected intercourse or contraceptive failure.

Name: Indacaterol Maleate
Information: Indacaterol is an ultra-long-acting β-adrenoceptor agonist with pKi of 7.36 for β1-adrenoceptor and pKi of 5.48 for β2-adrenoceptor.

Name: 2-Thiouracil
Information: 2-Thiouracil is a thiolated uracil derivative that is a known antihyperthyroid agent.

Name: Creatinine
Information: Creatinine is a break-down product of creatine phosphate in muscle, and is usually produced at a fairly constant rate by the body.

Name: Moguisteine
Information: Moguisteine is a novel peripheral non-narcotic antitussive drug.

Name: Nadifloxacin
Information: Nadifloxacin is a topical fluoroquinolone antibiotic for the treatment of acne vulgaris.

Name: Pidotimod
Information: Pidotimod is an immunostimulant.

Name: Pyridoxine HCl
Information: Pyridoxine HCl is a form of vitamin B6.

Name: Vitamin C
Information: Vitamin C is a water-soluble vitamin indicated for the prevention and treatment of scurvy.

Name: Sulfathiazole
Information: Sulfathiazole is an organosulfur compound that has been used as a short-acting sulfa drug.

Name: Oxybutynin chloride
Information: Oxybutynin is an anticholinergic medication used to relieve urinary and bladder difficulties.

Name: Doxepin HCl
Information: Doxepin is a tricyclic antidepressant formulated as a mixture of E-(trans) and Z-(cis) stereoisomers. It inhibits CYP2D6 activity in vivo.

Name: Ornidazole
Information: Ornidazole is a 5-nitroimidazole derivative with antiprotozoal and antibacterial properties against anaerobic bacteria.

Name: Amikacin hydrate
Information: Amikacin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic used to treat different types of bacterial infections.

Name: Dexamethasone Acetate
Information: Dexamethasone is a potent synthetic member of the glucocorticoid class of steroid drugs, and an interleukin receptor modulator that has anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressant effects.

Name: Trimethoprim
Information: Trimethoprim is a bacteriostatic antibiotic mainly used in the prophylaxis and treatment of urinary tract infections.

Name: Biotin (Vitamin B7)
Information: Biotin is a water-soluble B-vitamin and is necessary for cell growth, the production of fatty acids, and the metabolism of fats and amino acids.

Name: Sulfamerazine
Information: Sulfamerazine is a sulfonamide antibacterial.

Name: Sulfamethazine
Information: Sulfamethazine is a sulfonamide antibacterial.

Name: Sodium salicylate
Information: Sodium salicylate is used in medicine as an analgesic and antipyretic.

Name: Methylthiouracil
Information: Methylthiouracil is an antithyroid preparation.

Name: Methenamine
Information: Methenamine is an antibiotic used for the treatment of urinary tract infection.

Name: Milnacipran HCl
Information: Milnacipran inhibits both norepinephrine transporter (NET) and norepinephrine transporter (SERT) with IC50 of 77 nM and 420 nM, respectively.

Name: Darifenacin HBr
Information: Darifenacin is a selective M3 muscarinic receptor antagonist with pKi of 8.9.

Name: Tripelennamine HCl
Information: Tripelennamine is a widely used H1 antagonist, inhibiting PhIP glucuronidation with IC50 of 30 μM.

Name: Entacapone
Information: Entacapone inhibits catechol-O-methyltransferase(COMT) with IC50 of 151 nM.

Name: Ibandronate sodium
Information: Ibandronate is a highly potent nitrogen-containing bisphosphonate used for the treatment of osteoporosis.

Name: Estradiol valerate
Information: Estradiol is a synthetic ester used to treat menopausal symptoms and hormone deficiencies.

Name: Articaine HCl
Information: Articaine is a dental local anesthetic which contains an additional ester group that is metabolized by estearases in blood and tissue.

Name: Gliquidone
Information: Gliquidone is an ATP-sensitive K+ channel antagonist with IC50 of 27.2 nM.

Name: Butenafine HCl
Information: Butenafine HCl is a synthetic benzylamine antifungal, works by inhibiting the synthesis of sterols by inhibiting squalene epoxidase.

Name: Mepivacaine HCl
Information: Mepivacaine is a tertiary amine used as a local anesthetic.

Name: Ethynodiol diacetate
Information: Ethynodiol diacetate is one of the first synthetic progestogens used in contraceptive pills.

Name: Sertaconazole nitrate
Information: Sertaconazole nitrate is a topical broad-spectrum antifungal that is developed to provide an additional agent for the treatment of superficial cutaneous and mucosal infections.

Name: Tylosin tartrate
Information: Tylosin tartrate is a macrolide antibiotic approved for the control of mycoplasmosis in poultry.

Name: Benztropine mesylate
Information: Benztropine is a dopamine transporter (DAT) inhibitor with IC50 of 118 nM.

Name: Abacavir sulfate
Information: Abacavir is a commonly used nucleoside analogue with potent antiviral activity against HIV-1.

Name: Altrenogest
Information: Altrenogest is a progestogen structurally related to veterinary steroid trenbolone.

Name: Ampicillin sodium
Information: Ampicillin is a beta-lactam antibiotic that is part of the aminopenicillin family.

Name: Anagrelide HCl
Information: Anagrelide is a drug used for the treatment of essential thrombocytosis.

Name: Antipyrine
Information: Antipyrine is an analgesic and antipyretic agent selective COX-3 inhibitor.

Name: L-Arginine HCl (L-Arg)
Information: L-Arginine is the nitrogen donor for synthesis of nitric oxide, a potent vasodilator that is deficient during times of sickle cell crisis.

Name: Atomoxetine HCl
Information: Atomoxetine is a selective norepinephrine (NE) transporter inhibitor with Ki of 5 nM, with 15- and 290-fold lower affinity for human 5-HT and DA transporters.

Name: Betahistine 2HCl
Information: Betahistine is a histamine H3 receptor inhibitor with IC50 of 1.9 μM.

Name: Brinzolamide
Information: Brinzolamide is a potent carbonic anhydrase II inhibitor with IC50 of 3.19 nM.

Name: Carbenicillin disodium
Information: Carbenicillin is a semi-synthetic penicillin antibiotic which interferes with cell wall synthesis of gram-negative bacteria while displaying low toxicity.

Name: Eletriptan HBr
Information: Eletriptan is a selective 5-HT1B and 5-HT1D receptor agonist with Ki of 0.92 nM and 3.14 nM, respectively.

Name: Flumequine
Information: Flumequine is a synthetic chemotherapeutic antibiotic, inhibiting topoisomerase II with IC50 of 15 μM.

Name: Amitriptyline HCl
Information: Amitriptyline inhibits serotonin receptor, norepinephrine receptor, 5-HT4, 5-HT2 and sigma 1 receptor with IC50 of 3.45 nM, 13.3 nM, 7.31 nM, 235 nM and 287 nM, respectively.

Name: Adrenalone HCl
Information: Adrenalone is an adrenergic agonist used as a topical vasoconstrictor and hemostatic, mainly acts on alpha-1 adrenergic receptors.

Name: Azatadine dimaleate
Information: Azatadine is an histamine and cholinergic inhibitor with IC50 of 6.5 nM and 10 nM, respectively.

Name: (+,-)-Octopamine HCl
Information: Octopamine (OA), a biogenic monoamine structurally related to noradrenaline, acts as a neurohormone, a neuromodulator and a neurotransmitter in invertebrates.

Name: Ropinirole HCl
Information: Ropinirole a selective dopamine D2 receptors agonist with Ki of 29 nM.

Name: Ticarcillin sodium
Information: Ticarcillin is a semisynthetic antibiotic with a broad spectrum of bactericidal activity against many gram-positive and gram-negative aerobic and anaerobic bacteria.

Name: Azlocillin sodium salt
Information: Azlocillin is an acylampicillin with a broad spectrum against bacteria.

Name: Reboxetine mesylate
Information: Reboxetine is a norepinephrine reuptake inhibitor with Ki of 8.2 nM.

Name: Triflusal
Information: Triflusal irreversibly inhibits the production of thromboxane-B2 in platelets by acetylating cycloxygenase-1.

Name: Trifluoperazine 2HCl
Information: Trifluoperazine is a dopamine D2 receptor inhibitor with IC50 of 1.1 nM.

Name: Catharanthine
Information: Catharanthine inhibits nicotinic receptor mediated diaphragm contractions with IC50 of 59.6 μM.

Name: Meptazinol HCl
Information: Meptazinol is a unique centrally active opioid analgesic, which inhibits [3H]dihydromorphine binding with IC50 of 58 nM.

Name: Iopromide
Information: Iopromide is a low osmolar, non-ionic X-ray contrast agent for intravascular administration. It functions as a contrast agent by opacifying blood vessels in the path of flow of the contrast agent, permitting radiographic visualization of the internal structures until significant hemodilution occurs.

Name: Fexofenadine HCl
Information: Fexofenadine inhibits histamine H1 receptor with IC50 of 246 nM.

Name: Thiamine HCl (Vitamin B1)
Information: Thiamine or vitamin B1 is a water-soluble vitamin of the B complex, its phosphate derivatives are involved in many cellular processes.

Name: Moclobemide (Ro 111163)
Information: Moclobemide is a MAO-A (5-HT) inhibitor with IC50 of 6.1 μM.

Name: Schisandrin B (Sch B)
Information: Schisandrin B is the most abundant dibenzocyclooctadiene lignan present in the traditional Chinese medicinal herb Schisandra chinensis (Turcz.) Baill. It is a kind of ATR and P-gp inhibitor with high safety.

Name: Betulinic acid
Information: Betulinic acid, a pentacyclic triterpenoid from Syzigium claviflorum, is a inhibitor of HIV-1 with EC50 of 1.4 &mu M. Phase 1/2.

Name: Triptolide (PG490)
Information: Triptolide is a diterpene triepoxide, immunosuppresive agent extracted from the Chinese herb Tripterygium wilfordii. It functions as a NF-κB inhibitor with dual actions by disruption of p65/CBP interaction and by reduction of p65 protein.

Name: Borneol
Information: Borneol is a bicyclic monoterpenoid compound extracted from medicinal plants such as Blumea balsamifera, and Dryobalanops aromatica. It is a TRPM8 agonist that increases ocular surface wetness.

Name: Fangchinoline
Information: Fangchinoline, a bisbenzylisoquinoline alkaloid, is a novel HIV-1 inhibitor with pain-relieving, blood pressure-depressing, and antibiotic activities.

Name: Demethylzeylasteral (T-96)
Information: Demethylzeylasteral (T-96), the active component isolated from Tripterygium wilfordii Hook F., inhibits UDP-glucuronosyltransferase (UGT) isoforms UGT1A6 and UGT2B7 with immunosuppressive effects.

Name: Berbamine (dihydrochloride)
Information: Berbamine (BBM) is a natural bisbenzylisoquinoline product isolated from traditional Chinese herbal medicine Berberis amurensis. It is a novel inhibitor of bcr/abl fusion gene with potent anti-leukemia activity and also an inhibitor of NF-κB.

Name: Cordycepin
Information: Cordycepin is an adenosine analogue, which is readily phosphorylated to its mono-, di-, and triphosphate intracellularly. It has a very potent anti-cancer, anti-oxidant and anti-inflammatory activities.

Name: (+)-Fangchinoline
Information: Fangchinoline is a phytochemical that has been shown to elicit anti-cancer effects in prostate and breast cancer cell lines via inducing G1 cell cycle arrest. It has also been shown to possess neuroprotective activity.

Name: Rosmarinic acid
Information: Rosmarinic acid (RA) is a naturally occurring hydroxylated compound. It has the ability to block complement fixation, inhibit lipoxygenase and cyclooxygenase activity and inhibit the expression of CCL11 and CCR3 by suppressing the IKK-β activity in NF-κB activation signaling.

Name: Dehydrocostus Lactone
Information: Dehydrocostus lactone (DHE), a natural sesquiterpene lactone, inhibits IKKβ activity, IκBα phosphorylation and degradation, coactivators p300 recruitments and p50/p65 NF-κB nuclear translocation, and their DNA binding activity on COX-2 promoter. It has anti-inflammatory, anti-ulcer, immunomodulatory and anti-tumor properties.

Name: Asiaticoside
Information: Asiaticoside, the major active principle of Centella asiatica, prevents ultraviolet A-dependent photoaging by suppressing ultraviolet A-induced reactive oxygen species production. It also decreases DNA binding by MITF.

Name: Acetylspiramycin (ASPM)
Information: Acetylspiramycin (ASPM) is a macrolide antimicrobial agent.

Name: Citicoline sodium
Information: Citicoline is an essential intermediate in the synthesis of the major phospholipid of the cell membranes, phosphatidylcholine (PtdCho). It increases plasma adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH) levels and potentiates serum thyrotrophin (TSH) levels by activating the central cholinergic system.

Name: Pazufloxacin mesylate
Information: Pazufloxacin Mesylate, also known as Pazucross and T-3762, is a quinolone antibacterial agent used for the intravenous therapy of several infections.

Name: Diammonium Glycyrrhizinate
