Information: Valproic acid is a fatty acid with anticonvulsant properties used in the treatment of epilepsy. It is also a histone deacetylase inhibitor and is under investigation for treatment of HIV and various cancers.

Name: L-Cycloserine
Information: L-Cycloserine is a potent inhibitor of the sphingolipid pathway via inhibiting 3-ketodihydrosphingosine synthetase. It also inhibits HIV-1 cytopathic effects, replication, and infectivity.

Name: Mesterolone
Information: Mesterolone is a synthetic steroid with anabolic and androgenic activities.

Name: Spermine
Information: Spermine is a polyamine involved in cellular metabolism found in all eukaryotic cells. It is found in a wide variety of organisms and tissues and is an essential growth factor in some bacteria.

Name: Maltitol
Information: Maltitol is a sugar alcohol (polyol) used as a sugar substitute. It is especially useful in the production of sweets, including sugarless hard candies, chewing gum, chocolates.

Name: Tannic acid
Information: Tannic acid, a polyphenolic compound, is a CXCL12/CXCR4 inhibitor with antiangiogenic, anti-inflammatory and antitumor activity.

Name: L-Lysine hydrochloride
Information: L-Lysine hydrochloride is an essential amino acid. It is often added to animal feed used as a dietary supplement and plays a major role in calcium absorption, building muscle protein, recovering from surgery or sports injuries, and the body's production of hormones, enzymes, and antibodies.

Name: Gamma-Oryzanol
Information: Gamma-oryzanol (GO), a nutriactive phytochemical naturally occurring in crude rice bran oil, is an antioxidant compound used to treat hyperlipidemia, disorders of menopause and to increase the muscle mass.

Name: (+)-Borneol
Information: (+)-Borneol is one of enantiomers of borneol which is a valuable medical material, senior aromatic spice, and chemical material and has been used in food and also folk medicine.

Name: DL-Glutamine
Information: Glutamine is a non-essential amino acid present abundantly throughout the body and is involved in many metabolic processes.

Name: Vanillyl Butyl Ether
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Information: Vanillyl butyl ether, an ether of monohydroxybenzoic acid, is added to food products as a flavoring agent. It is also present in cosmetics and personal care products as a fragrance ingredient, oral care agent, hair conditioning agent, and warming or cooling agent.

Name: Nifuratel
Information: Local antiprotozoal and antifungal agent that may also be given orally.

Name: Flavone
Information: Flavone, a class of flavonoids, mainly found in spices and red or purple plant foods with antioxidant, anti-proliferative, anti-tumor, anti-microbial, estrogenic, acetyl cholinesterase, anti-inflammatory activities and are also used in cancer, cardiovascular disease, neurodegenerative disorders etc.

Name: Histamine
Information: Histamine, an organic nitrogenous compound, is involved in local immune responses regulating physiological function in the gut and acting as a neurotransmitter for the brain, spinal cord, and uterus. It is a potent H1 and H2 receptor agonist.

Name: Veratric acid
Information: Veratric acid, a simple benzoic acid derived from plants and fruits, has anti-oxidant, anti-inflammation, and blood pressure-lowering effects.

Name: Vindoline
Information: Vindoline is a chemical precursor to vinblastine and exhibits antimitotic activity by inhibiting microtubule assembly.

Name: Fusidine
Information: Fusidine, isolated from Fusidium coccineum, is a steroidal antibiotic that inhibits protein synthesis.

Name: Lobeline hydrochloride
Information: Lobeline hydrochloride is an alkaloid that acts on nicotinic cholinergic receptors but is less potent than nicotine. It is also a VMAT2 ligand and an antagonist of μ-opioid receptors.

Name: L-SelenoMethionine
Information: L-SelenoMethionine (SeMet), a naturally occurring amino acid, is a major food-form of selenium. It has been used as a supplement, and exhibits some important functions like cancer prevention and antioxidative defense.

Name: (+)-Catechin hydrate
Information: Catechins are a plant derived polyphenolic anti-oxidants with phytotoxic properties. (+)-Catechin hydrate is a frequent component of traditional herbal remedies, such as Uncaria rhynchophylla.

Name: Protocatechuic acid
Information: Protocatechuic acid (PCA), a dihydroxybenzoic acid, is a type of widely distributed naturally occurring phenolic acid.

Name: (-)-Borneol
Information: (-)-Borneol, one of enantiomers of borneol, has a camphoraceous and evident woody odor.

Name: Zinc Undecylenate
Information: Zinc Undecylenate is a natural or synthetic fungistatic fatty acid, antifungal Zinc Undecylenate is used topically in creams against fungal infections, eczemas, ringworm, and other cutaneous conditions.

Name: Pyridoxine
Information: Pyridoxine, also known as vitamin B6, is a form of vitamin B6 found commonly in food and used as dietary supplement. It is a cofactor for both glutamic acid decarboxylase and GABA transaminase.

Name: Batyl alcohol
Information: Batyl alcohol, isolated from shark liver oil, is also present in yellow bone marrow of animals and has been described as an inflammatory agent.

Name: Caryophyllene oxide
Information: Caryophyllene oxide, an oxygenated terpenoid existed in many plant essential oil, is well known as preservative in food, drugs and cosmetics with anti-inflammatory, anti-carcinogenic and skin penetration enhancing properties.

Name: Nordihydroguaiaretic acid (NDGA)
Information: Nordihydroguaiaretic acid (NDGA) is a phenolic antioxidant found in the leaves and twigs of the evergreen desert shrub, Larrea tridentata (Sesse and Moc. ex DC) Coville (creosote bush). It is a recognized inhibitor of lipoxygenase (LOX) and has antioxidant and free radical scavenging properties.

Name: Methyl 4-hydroxybenzoate
Information: Methyl 4-hydroxybenzoate is an anti-fungal agent often used in a variety of cosmetics, personal-care products and food preservatives.
Synonyms: Methylparaben, Methyl paraben, Methyl p-hydroxybenzoate, Nipagin, Methyl parahydroxybenzoate

Name: L(+)-Arabinose
Information: L-Arabinose (l-Ara) is a plant saccharide that is not found in animals. It is a component of cell wall and may be useful as a natural pharmaceutical.

Name: L-Tryptophan
Information: L-tryprophan is an essential amino acid that acts like a natural mood regulator that is necessary for normal growth in infants and for nitrogen balance in adults.

Name: D-(+)-Trehalose dihydrate
Information: Trehalose is a non-reducing sugar. It is thought to provide plants and animals with the ability to withstanding periods of dehydration.

Name: Guaiazulene
Information: Guaiazulene is a bicyclic sesquiterpene that is a constituent of some essential oils, mainly oil of guaiac and chamomile oil, which also serve as its commercial sources.

Name: Thioctic acid
Information: Thioctic acid (DL-α-Lipoic acid) is a cyclic disulfide antioxidant that interconverts with its reduced dithiol form.

Name: Oxaceprol
Information: Oxaceprol is an anti-inflammatory drug used in the treatment of osteoarthritis.

Name: (+)-α-Lipoic acid
Information: R(+)-α-lipoic acid, a physiological form of thioctic acid, is a strong antioxidant that relieves diabetic neuropathic symptoms. It shows superior antioxidative effects to its racemate.

Name: Pergolide Mesylate
Information: Pergolide Mesylate is an antiparkinsonian agent which functions as a dopaminergic agonist.

Name: Cabozantinib malate (XL184)
Information: Cabozantinib malate (XL184) is the malate of Cabozantinib, a potent VEGFR2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.035 nM and also inhibits c-Met, Ret, Kit, Flt-1/3/4, Tie2, and AXL with IC50 of 1.3 nM, 4 nM, 4.6 nM, 12 nM/11.3 nM/6 nM, 14.3 nM and 7 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Sitagliptin phosphate monohydrate
Information: Sitagliptin phosphate monohydrate is a potent inhibitor of DPP-IV with IC50 of 19 nM in Caco-2 cell extracts.

Name: Lithocholic acid
Information: Lithocholic acid is a toxic secondary bile acid, causes intrahepatic cholestasis, has tumor-promoting activity, its toxic effect can be protected after it activates the vitamin D receptor, PXR and FXR.

Name: Ethambutol 2HCl
Information: Ethambutol is a bacteriostatic antimycobacterial agent, which obstructs the formation of cell wall by inhibiting arabinosyl transferases.

Name: Pentamidine isethionate
Information: Pentamidine is an inhibitor of PRL Phosphatases and also inhibits synthesis of DNA, RNA and protein.

Name: Pemirolast potassium
Information: Pemirolast potassium (BMY 26517) is a histamine H1 antagonist and mast cell stabilizer that acts as an antiallergic agent.

Name: Mirabegron
Information: Mirabegron is a selective β3-adrenoceptor agonist with EC50 of 22.4 nM.

Name: Acebutolol HCl
Information: Acebutolol is a β-adrenergic receptors antagonist used in the treatment of hypertension, angina pectoris and cardiac arrhythmias.

Name: Ampiroxicam
Information: Ampiroxicam is a nonselective cyclooxygenase inhibitor uesd as anti-inflammatory drug.

Name: Desloratadine
Information: Desloratadine is a potent antagonist for human histamine H1 receptor with IC50 of 51 nM.

Name: Sodium Monofluorophosphate
Information: Sodium Monofluorophosphate is a competitive inhibitor of pyruvate kinase and alkaline phosphatase with Ki of 3.4 mM and 69 μM, respectively, which also irreversibly inhibits phosphorylase phosphatase with Ki of 0.5 mM.

Name: Hyoscyamine
Information: Hyoscyamine is an AChR inhibitor with IC50 of 7.5 nM.

Name: Ouabain
Information: Ouabain is a selective Na+/K+, -ATPase inhibitor, binds to α2 /α3 subunit with Ki of 41 nM/15 nM.

Name: Allylthiourea
Information: Allylthiourea is a metabolic inhibitor that selective inhibits ammonia oxidation.

Name: Sennoside B
Information: Sennoside B, a kind of irritant laxative isolated from rhei rhizome, inhibits PDGF-stimulated cell proliferation.

Name: Avanafil
Information: Avanafil is a highly selective PDE5 inhibitor with IC50 of 5.2 nM, >121-fold selectivity over other PDEs.

Name: Sodium Picosulfate
Information: Sodium Picosulfate inhibits absorption of water and electrolytes, and increases their secretion.

Name: Tolcapone
Information: Tolcapone is a selective, potent and reversible of catechol-O-methyl transferase (COMT) inhibitor with Ki of 30 nM.

Name: Probenecid
Information: Probenecid is a classical competitive inhibitor of organic anion transport, which is also a TRPV2 agonist and an inhibitor of TAS2R16.

Name: Procaine HCl
Information: Procaine is an inhibitor of sodium channel, NMDA receptor and nAChR with IC50 of 60 μM, 0.296 mM and 45.5 μM, which is also an inhibitor of 5-HT3 with KD of 1.7 μM.

Name: Homatropine Methylbromide
Information: Homatropine Methylbromide is muscarinic AChR antagonist, inhibits endothelial and smooth muscle muscarinic receptors of WKY-E and SHR-E with IC50 of 162.5 nM and 170.3 nM, respectively.

Name: Homatropine Bromide
Information: Homatropine Bromide is an muscarinic AChR antagonist, inhibits endothelial and smooth muscle muscarinic receptors of WKY-E and SHR-E with IC50 of 162.5 nM and 170.3 nM, respectively.

Name: Hydroxyzine 2HCl
Information: Hydroxyzine is a histamine H1-receptor antagonist, inhibits binding of [3H]pyrilamine/[3H]desloratadine to human histamine H1 receptor with IC50 of 10 nM/19 nM.

Name: Flavoxate HCl
Information: Flavoxate is a muscarinic AChR antagonist with IC50 of 12.2 μM.

Name: Dexamethasone Sodium Phosphate
Information: Dexamethasone is a potent synthetic member of the glucocorticoid class of steroid drugs, and an interleukin receptor modulator that has anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressant effects.

Name: Colistin Sulfate
Information: Colistin is a cyclic cationic decapeptide linked to a fatty acid side chain, it belongs to a group of similarly structured bacterial antimicrobial peptides.

Name: Gentamicin Sulfate
Information: Gentamycin Sulfate is a broad-spectrum, aminoglycoside antibiotic used for cell culture which inhibits protein synthesis in sensitive organisms.

Name: Aclidinium Bromide
Information: Aclidinium Bromide inhibits human muscarinic AChR M1, M2, M3, M4 and M5 with Ki of 0.1 nM, 0.14 nM, 0.14 nM, 0.21 nM and 0.16 nM, respectively.

Name: Sennoside A
Information: Sennoside A, a kind of irritant laxative isolated from rhei rhizome, causes purgative actions in the intestine.

Name: Diphemanil Methylsulfate
Information: Diphemanil Methylsulfate is a quaternary ammonium anticholinergic, it binds muscarinic acetycholine receptors (mAchR).

Name: Vitamin D2
Information: Vitamin D2 is a selective inhibitor of mammalian DNA polymerase A (pol A) with IC50 of 123 mM.

Name: Doxapram HCl
Information: Doxapram HCl inhibits TASK-1, TASK-3, TASK-1/TASK-3 heterodimeric channel function with EC50 of 410 nM, 37 μM, 9 μM, respectively.

Name: Dibucaine HCl
Information: Dibucaine HCl is a local anesthetics.

Name: Methazolamide
Information: Methazolamide is a carbonic anhydrase inhibitor with Ki of 50 nM, 14 nM and 36 nM for hCA I, hCA II and bCA IV isoforms, respectively.

Name: Norethindrone
Information: Norethindrone is a synthetic progestin, which mimic the actions of the endogenous ovarian hormone progesterone.

Name: Olsalazine Sodium
Information: Olsalazine Sodium is an anti-inflammatory prodrug, which consists of two 5-ASA moieties linked by an azo bond.

Name: Nafcillin Sodium
Information: Nafcillin sodium reversibly inhibits β-lactamase with Kd of 33 mM.

Name: Tetrahydrozoline HCl
Information: Tetrahydrozoline HCl is an imidazoline derivative with alpha receptor agonist activity.

Name: Toltrazuril
Information: Toltrazuril is an antiprotozoal agent that acts upon Coccidia parasites.

Name: Pheniramine Maleate
Information: Pheniramine Maleate is an antihistamine with anticholinergic properties used to treat allergic conditions such as hay fever or urticaria.

Name: Estradiol Cypionate
Information: Estradiol cypionate is the 17 β-cyclopentylpropinate ester of estradiol, which inhibits ET-1 synthesis via estrogen receptor.

Name: Bisacodyl
Information: Bisacodyl (INN) is a stimulant laxative drug that works directly on the colon to produce a bowel movement.

Name: Carbimazole
Information: Carbimazole is an imidazole antithyroid agent.

Name: Valdecoxib
Information: Valdecoxib is a potent and selective inhibitor of COX-2 with IC50 of 5 nM.

Name: Valganciclovir HCl
Information: Valganciclovir HCl is a prodrug for ganciclovir with antiviral activity used to treat cytomegalovirus infections.

Name: Nabumetone
Information: Nabumetone is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug and its active metabolite inhibits the COX.

Name: Netilmicin Sulfate
Information: Netilmicin Sulfate is a member of the aminoglycoside family of antibiotics.

Name: Sertraline HCl
Information: Sertraline HCl is a 5-HT antagonist with Ki of 13 nM.

Name: Spironolactone
Information: Spironolactone is a potent antagonist of the androgen receptor with IC50 of 77 nM.

Name: Retapamulin
Information: Retapamulin is a topical antibiotic, which binds to both E. coli and S. aureus ribosomes with similar potencies with Kd of 3 nM.

Name: Methyclothiazide
Information: Methyclothiazide is a substituted benzothiadiazide, used to treat high blood pressure and fluid retention caused by various conditions including heart disease.

Name: Ropivacaine HCl
Information: Ropivacaine HCl is an anaesthetic agent and blocks impulse conduction in nerve fibres through inhibiting sodium ion influx reversibly.

Name: Sodium Nitroprusside Dihydrate
Information: Sodium Nitroprusside Dihydrate is a potent vasodilator working through releasing NO spontaneously in blood.

Name: Erythromycin Ethylsuccinate
Information: Erythromycin Ethylsuccinate, an oral macrolide antibiotic produced by Streptomyces erythreus, reversibly binds to the 50S ribosome of bacteria, and inhibits protein synthesis.

Name: Levobupivacaine HCl
Information: Levobupivacaine HCl, the pure S(-)-enantiomer of bupivacaine, is a reversible neuronal sodium channel inhibitor, used as a long-acting local anesthetic.

Name: Ronidazole
Information: Ronidazole is an antiprotozoal agent.

Name: cholecalciferol (Vitamin D3)
Information: Vitamin D3 is a form of vitamin D, binds and activates a H305F/H397Y mutant vitamin D receptor (VDR) with EC50 of 300 nM.

Name: Escitalopram Oxalate
Information: Escitalopram Oxalate is a selective serotonin (5-HT) reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) with Ki of 0.89 nM.

Name: Guanabenz Acetate
Information: Guanabenz Acetate is an selective agonist of α2a-adrenergic receptor, α2b-adrenergic receptor and α2c-adrenergic receptor with pEC50 of 8.25, 7.01 and ~5, respectively.

Name: Deferiprone
Information: Deferiprone is a chelating agent with an affinity for ferric ion (iron III)，binds with ferric ions to form neutral 3:1 (deferiprone:iron) complexes that are stable over a wide range of pH values.

Name: Tinidazole
Information: Tinidazole is an anti-parasitic drug.

Name: Guanidine HCl
Information: Guanidine HCl, the crystalline compound of strong alkalinity formed by the oxidation of guanine, is a normal product of protein metabolism and a protein denaturant.

Name: Griseofulvin
Information: Griseofulvin, a production from some strains of the mold Penicillium griseofulvumam, is able to inhibit cell mitosis by interfering with microtubule function.

Name: Decamethonium Bromide
Information: Decamethonium Bromide is a nicotinic AChR partial agonist and neuromuscular blocking agent.

Name: Sodium Nitrite
Information: Sodium nitrite is a myeloperoxidase inhibitor with IC50 of 1.3 μM.

Name: Zinc Pyrithione
Information: Zinc pyrithione is an antifungal and antibacterial agent disrupting membrane transport by blocking the proton pump.

Name: Propranolol HCl
Information: Propranolol HCl is a competitive non-selective beta-adrenergic receptors inhibitor with IC50 of 12 nM.

Name: Mequinol
Information: Mequinol (4-Methoxyphenol) is a depigmentation agent.

Name: Mefenamic Acid
Information: Mefenamic Acid is a competitive inhibitor of COX-1 and COX-2.

Name: Ticagrelor
Information: Ticagrelor is the first reversibly binding oral P2Y12 receptor antagonist with Ki of 2 nM.

Name: Triamterene
Information: Triamterene blocks epithelial Na+ channel (ENaC) in a voltage-dependent manner with IC50 of 4.5 μM.

Name: Sulfacetamide Sodium
Information: Sulfacetamide Sodium is an anti-biotic.

Name: Spiramycin
Information: Spiramycin is a 16-membered ring macrolide (antibiotic).

Name: Vitamin A Acetate
Information: Vitamin A is a group of unsaturated nutritional hydrocarbons, that includes retinol, retinal, retinoic acid, and several provitamin A carotenoids, among which beta-carotene is the most important.

Name: Lomerizine 2HCl
Information: Lomerizine dihydrochloride is a relatively new L- and T-type calcium channel blocker used in the treatment of migraine.

Name: Levobetaxolol HCl
Information: Levobetaxolol exhibits a higher affinity at cloned human β1 and β2 receptors with Ki value of 0.76 nM and 32.6 nM, respectively.

Name: Loxapine Succinate
Information: Loxapine Succinate is a D2DR and D4DR inhibitor, serotonergic receptor antagonist and also a dibenzoxazepine anti-psychotic agent.

Name: Flumethasone
Information: Flumethasone is a glucocorticoid receptor agonist, this complex binds to the nucleus causing a variety of genetic activation and repressions.

Name: Halobetasol Propionate
Information: Halobetasol Propionate is an anti-inflammatory and a dermatologic agent commonly used to treat psoriasis.

Name: Fenspiride HCl
Information: Fenspiride is a bronchodilator with anti-inflammatory properties, inhibiting phosphodiesterase 4 and phosphodiesterase 3 activities with logIC50 values of 4.16 and 3.44, respectively, in human isolated bronchi.

Name: Ifenprodil Tartrate
Information: Ifenprodil is an atypical noncompetitive antagonist at the NMDA receptor, it interacts with high affinity at a homogeneous population of NMDA receptors in neonatal rat forebrain with IC50 of 0.3 μM.

Name: Pramoxine HCl
Information: Pramoxine is a topical local anesthetic that has been shown to have antipruritic properties.

Name: Bismuth Subcitrate Potassium
Information: Bismuth Subcitrate is an antibiotic used to treat stomach ulcers associated with Helicobacter pylori, a bacterial infection.

Name: Tetramisole HCl
Information: Tetramisole is a mixture of dextro- and levo isomers used as an anthelmintic.

Name: Difluprednate
Information: Difluprednate (difluoroprednisolone butyrate acetate, or DFBA) is a synthetic difluorinated prednisolone derivative, it is originally developed for dermatologic applications.

Name: Droperidol
Information: Droperidol is a potent antagonist of dopamine subtype 2 receptors in the limbic system.

Name: Halcinonide
Information: Halcinonide is a high potency corticosteroid used in topical preparations as an anti-inflammatory agent.

Name: Dexlansoprazole
Information: Dexlansoprazole, the dextrorotatory enantiomer of lansoprazole, is a proton pump inhibitor (PPI) formulated to have dual delayed-release properties.

Name: Esmolol HCl
Information: Esmolol is a cardioselective b-blocker, used to control rapid heartbeats or abnormal heart rhythms.

Name: Voglibose
Information: Voglibose is an N-substituted derivative of valiolamine, excellent inhibitory activity against α-glucosidases and its action against hyperglycemia and various disorders caused by hyperglycemia.

Name: Eprosartan Mesylate
Information: Eprosartan is a nonpeptide angiotensin II receptor antagonist, [3H]-eprosartan binds to the AT1 receptor with KD of 0.83 nM in rat vascular smooth muscle cells.

Name: Diminazene Aceturate
Information: Diminazene is a di-amidine also known as 4,4-(1-Triazene–1,3–diyl)bis(benzenecarboximidamide), used as an effective trypanocidal agent.

Name: Closantel Sodium
Information: Closantel is a gram positive antibacterial activity inhibitor, inhibiting the KinA/Spo0F system with IC50 of 3.8 μM.

Name: Closantel
Information: Closantel is a gram positive antibacterial activity inhibitor, inhibiting the KinA/Spo0F system with IC50 of 3.8 μM.

Name: Clofazimine
Information: Clofazimine is a rhimophenazine dye, originally developed for the treatment of tuberculosis, it has both antimicrobial and antiinflammatory activity, postulated mechanisms of action include intercalation of clofazimine with bacterial DNA and increasing levels of cellular phospholipase A2.

Name: Clodronate Disodium
Information: Clodronate Disodium, a bisphosphonate, is a potent antiosteolytic agent which inhibits bone resorption.

Name: Estradiol Benzoate
Information: Estradiol benzoate is an estradiol analog which binds to the human, murine and chicken ERα with IC50 of 22-28 nM.

Name: Dicloxacillin Sodium
Information: Dicloxacillin is a β-lactamase resistant penicillin similar to oxacillin and it has activity against gram-positive/negative aerobic and anaerobic bacteria.

Name: Desvenlafaxine Succinate
Information: Desvenlafaxine Succinate is a new serotonin (5-HT) transporter and norepinephrine (NE) transporter reuptake inhibitor with Ki of 40.2 nM and 558.4 nM respectively.

Name: Desvenlafaxine
Information: Desvenlafaxine is a serotonin (5-HT) and norepinephrine (NE) reuptake inhibitor with Ki of 40.2 nM and 558.4 nM, respectively.

Name: Triclabendazole
Information: Triclabendazole is a benzimidazole, it binds to tubulin impairing intracellular transport mechanisms and interferes with protein synthesis.

Name: Isovaleramide
Information: Isovaleramide is an anticonvulsant molecule isolated from Valeriana pavonii, it inhibits the liver alcohol dehydrogenases.

Name: Histamine Phosphate
Information: Histamine acts directly on the blood vessels to dilate arteries and capillaries mediated by both H 1- and H 2-receptors.

Name: Histamine 2HCl
Information: Histamine is an organic nitrogen compound, acts on target cells in mammalian brain via stimulation of Histamine 1/2.

Name: Pefloxacin Mesylate Dihydrate
Information: Pefloxacin Mesylate Dihydrate is the third generation of fluoroquinolone class of antibacterials, which inhibits Topoisomerase II activity and DNA replication.

Name: Sulconazole Nitrate
Information: Sulconazole Nitrate is an imidazole derivative with broad-spectrum antifungal activity.

Name: Succinylcholine Chloride Dihydrate
Information: Succinylcholine Chloride Dihydrate is a nicotinic AChR agonist and also acts as a depolarizing neuromuscular blocker.

Name: Tilmicosin
Information: Tilmicosin is a macrolide antibiotic.

Name: Timolol Maleate
Information: Timolol Maleate is a non-selective, beta-adrenergic receptor antagonist for β1/β2 with Ki of 1.97 nM/2.0 nM.

Name: Tolazoline HCl
Information: Tolazoline is a non-selective competitive α-adrenergic receptor antagonist.

Name: Sodium Phenylbutyrate
Information: Sodium phenylbutyrate is a histone deacetylase inhibitor, used to treat urea cycle disorders.

Name: Retinyl (Vitamin A) Palmitate
Information: Vitamin A palmitate is a more stable, synthetic version of the essential nutrient vitamin A joined to palmitic acid.

Name: Terbutaline Sulfate
Information: Terbutaline Sulfate is a selective β2-adrenergic receptor agonist with IC50 of 53 nM.

Name: Troxipide
Information: Troxipide is a novel systemic non-antisecretory gastric cytoprotective agent with anti-ulcer, anti-inflammatory and mucus secreting properties irrespective of pH of stomach or duodenum.

Name: Mildronate
Information: Mildronate is an inhibitor of biosynthesis of L-carnitine by gamma-butyrobetaine (GBB) hydroxylase and as a competitive inhibitor of renal carnitine reabsorption.

Name: Levodropropizine
Information: Levodropropizine possess anti-allergic and inhibits histamine receptor, reduces cough by interfering with stimulus activation of peripheral endings of sensory nerves and by modulation of neuropeptides involved in the cough reflex.

Name: Clorprenaline HCl
Information: Clorprenaline HCl is a β2-receptor agonist, it has a significant expansion of the bronchial effect.

Name: Carprofen
Information: Carprofen inhibits canine COX2 with IC50 of 30 nM.

Name: Eprazinone 2HCl
Information: Eprazinone is a mucolytic.

Name: Dropropizine
Information: Dropropizine is a racemic non-opiate antitussive agent, it is used as a cough suppressant.

Name: Cyclizine 2HCl
Information: Cyclizine 2HCl is a piperazine derivative with Histamine H1 receptor antagonist activity.

Name: Dinitolmide
Information: Dinitolmide is a broad-spectrum anticoccidial drug.

Name: Clopidol
Information: Clopidol is an antiprotozoal agent.

Name: Pentoxyverine Citrate
Information: Pentoxyverine Citrate is an antitussive (cough suppressant) commonly used for cough associated with illnesses like common cold.

Name: Amprolium HCl
Information: Amprolium chloride is a thiamin antagonist, which prevents carbohydrate synthesis by blocking thiamine uptake.

Name: Bacitracin
Information: Bacitracin is a mixture of related cyclic polypeptides produced by organisms of the licheniformis group of Bacillus subtilis var Tracy, which disrupts both gram positive and gram negative bacteria by interfering with cell wall and peptidoglycan synthesis.

Name: Azithromycin Dihydrate
Information: Azithromycin Dihydrate is an acid stable orally administered macrolide antimicrobial drug, structurally related to erythromycin.

Name: Ampicillin Trihydrate
Information: Ampicillin Trihydrate is a β-lactam antibiotic, which inhibits bacterial cell-wall synthesis (peptidoglycan cross-linking) by inactivating transpeptidases on the inner surface of the bacterial cell membrane.

Name: Amfenac Sodium Monohydrate
Information: Amfenac Sodium monohydrate is a non-steroidal analgesic anti-inflammatory drug with acetic acid moiety. The IC50 values for COX1 and COX2 is 250 nM and 150 nM, respectively.

Name: Penfluridol
Information: Penfluridol is a highly potent, first generation diphenylbutylpiperidine antipsychotic.

Name: Ethamsylate
Information: Ethamsylate is a haemostatic drug, which inhibits biosynthesis and action of prostaglandins, and increases capillary endothelial resistance as and platelet adhesion.

Name: D-Phenylalanine
Information: D-Phenylalanine, a carboxypeptidase A, endorphinase and enkephalinase inhibitor, enhances endorphin production and diminishes pain.

Name: Chlorzoxazone
Information: Chlorzoxazone is a muscle-relaxing drug,and a probe for human liver cytochrome P-450IIE1.

Name: Chlortetracycline HCl
Information: Chlortetracycline HCl is the first identified tetracycline antibiotic.

Name: Chloroquine Phosphate
Information: Chloroquine phosphate is a 4-aminoquinoline anti-malarial and anti-rheumatoid agent, also acting as an ATM activator.

Name: Ceftriaxone Sodium Trihydrate
Information: Ceftriaxone sodium trihydrate is a third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic.

Name: Bezafibrate
Information: Bezafibrate is the first clinically tested dual and pan-PPAR co-agonism.

Name: Penicillin G Sodium
Information: Penicillin G Sodium is a β-lactam antibiotic produced by Penicillin spp.

Name: Benzoic Acid
Information: Benzoic acid is a colorless crystalline solid and a simple aromatic carboxylic acid, used as a food preservative.

Name: Benzethonium Chloride
Information: Benzethonium chloride is a potent inhibitor of nAChRs, it inhibits α4β2 nAChRs and α7 nAChRs with IC50 of 49 nM and 122 nM, respectively.

Name: Doxycycline Hyclate
Information: Doxycycline is a member of the tetracycline antibiotics group, and is commonly used to treat a variety of infections. It is also an inhibitor of matrix metallo-proteinases (MMP).

Name: Doxofylline
Information: Doxofylline is a phosphodiesterase inhibitor and a xanthine derivative drug for asthma.

Name: Benzydamine HCl
Information: Benzydamine hydrochloride is a topical nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) with anti-inflammatory, analgesic, antipyretic and local anesthetic activity.

Name: Chlorpropamide
Information: Chlorpropamide is a sulfonylurea class drug for type 2 diabetes mellitus.

Name: Cyromazine
Information: Cyromazine is a triazine insect growth regulator used as an insecticide and an acaricide.

Name: Teriflunomide
Information: Teriflunomide is the active metabolite of leflunomide, inhibiting pyrimidine de novo synthesis by blocking the enzyme dihydroorotate dehydrogenase, used as an immunomodulatory agent.

Name: Coumarin
Information: Coumarin is a secondary phytochemical with hepatotoxic and carcinogenic properties.

Name: Choline Chloride
Information: Choline chloride is a quaternary ammonium salt used as an additive for animal feed. It is important as a precursor of acetylcholine, as a methyl donor in various metabolic processes, and in lipid metabolism.

Name: Cetylpyridinium Chloride
Information: Cetylpyridinium chloride is a cationic quaternary ammonium compound used as oropharyngeal antiseptic.

Name: 1-Hexadecanol
Information: 1-Hexadecanol is a fatty alcohol used to make other chemicals.

Name: Sodium Gluconate
Information: Sodium gluconate is the sodium salt of gluconic acid widely used in food and pharmaceutical industry.

Name: Sulfaguanidine
Information: Sulfaguanidine is a sulfonamide used as an anti-infective agent.

Name: Trometamol
Information: Trometamol is a proton acceptor used to treat acidemia. It inhibits both isoforms of cyclooxygenases (COX1 and COX2), thereby blocking the conversion of arachidonic acid to pro-inflammatory pro-prostaglandins.

Name: Uracil
Information: Uracil is one of the four nucleobases in the nucleic acid of RNA can be used for drug delivery and as a pharmaceutical.

Name: Climbazole
Information: Climbazole is a broad-spectrum imidazole antifungal agent that can provide anti-dandruff benefits.

Name: Mezlocillin Sodium
Information: Mezlocillin sodium is a penicillin beta-lactam antibiotic used in the treatment of bacterial infections caused by susceptible, usually gram-positive, organisms.

Name: Nefopam HCl
Information: Nefopam HCl is a centrally-acting but non-opioid analgesic drug by blocking voltage-gated sodium channel and inhibition of serotonin, dopamine and noradrenaline reuptake.

Name: Nicardipine HCl
Information: Nicardipine is a dihydropyridine calcium-channel blocking agent used for the treatment of vascular disorders.

Name: Nifuroxazide
Information: Nifuroxazide is a cell-permeable and orally available nitrofuran-based antidiarrheal agent that effectively suppresses the activation of cellular STAT1/3/5 transcription activity with IC50 of 3 μM against IL-6-induced STAT3 activation in U3A cells.

Name: Paromomycin Sulfate
Information: Paromomycin Sulfate is an aminoglycoside antibiotics inhibiting protein synthesis in non-resistant cells by binding to 16S ribosomal RNA.

Name: Penciclovir
Information: Penciclovir is a purine acyclic nucleoside analogue with potent antiviral activity.

Name: Tiratricol
Information: Tiratricol (also known as TRIAC or triiodothyroacetic acid) is a thyroid hormone analogue.

Name: Domiphen Bromide
Information: Domiphen bromide is a quaternary ammonium antiseptic with actions as a cationic surfactant.

Name: Salicylanilide
Information: Salicylanilides are a group of compounds with a wide range of biological activities including antiviral potency, antibacterial (including antimycobacterial) and antifungal activities.

Name: Sasapyrine
Information: Sasapyrine (salsalate) is a nonsteroidal oral anti-inflammatory agent.

Name: Cyclandelate
Information: Cyclandelate is an effective inhibitor of rat hepatic acycloenzyme A: cholesterol acyltransferase (ACAT) with IC50 of 80 μM.

Name: Betamipron
Information: Betamipron is a chemical compound which is used together with panipenem to inhibit panipenem uptake into the renal tubule and prevent nephrotoxicity.

Name: Chlorquinaldol
Information: Chlorquinaldol is an antimicrobial agent used for local antisepsy.

Name: Broxyquinoline
Information: Broxyquinoline is an antiprotozoal agent and able to release oxygen free radicals from the water in mucous membranes.

Name: Ethacridine lactate monohydrate
Information: Ethacridine lactate monohydrate is an aromatic organic compound based on acridine used as an antiseptic agent.

Name: Bemegride
Information: Bemegride is a central nervous system stimulant and antidote for barbiturate poisoning.

Name: Tolperisone HCl
Information: Tolperisone HCl is an ion channel blocker and centrally-acting muscle relaxant.

Name: Florfenicol
Information: Florfenicol is a fluorinated synthetic analog of thiamphenicol with broad-spectrum, primarily bacteriostatic activity.

Name: Verapamil HCl
Information: Verapamil HCl is an L-type calcium channel blocker that is a class IV anti-arrhythmia agent.

Name: Furaltadone HCl
Information: Furaltadone HCl is an antibacterial and has distinct curative effect in the treatment of coccidiosis.

Name: Isosorbide
Information: Isosorbide is a heterocyclic compound that is derived from glucose, used as a diuretic.

Name: Cysteamine HCl
Information: Cysteamine is an agent for the treatment of nephropathic cystinosis and an antioxidant.

Name: Clofibric Acid
Information: Clofibric acid is a PPARα agonist and hypolipidemic agent.

Name: Chromocarb
Information: Chromocarb is a vasoprotectant.

Name: Chlorocresol
Information: Chlorocresol is an activator of ryanodine receptor.

Name: Benzocaine
Information: Benzocaine is the ethyl ester of p-aminobenzoic acid (PABA), it is a local anesthetic commonly used as a topical pain reliever or in cough drops.

Name: Montelukast Sodium
Information: Montelukast selectively antagonizes leukotriene D 4 (LTD4) by binding to it so that block the action of leukotriene D4 on the cysteinyl leukotriene receptor CysLT1.

Name: Tenatoprazole
Information: Tenatoprazole is a prodrug of the proton pump inhibitor (PPI) class, which inhibits proton transport with IC50 of 3.2 μM.

Name: Dirithromycin
Information: Dirithromycin is a macrolide glycopeptide antibiotic by binding to the 50S subunit of the 70S bacterial ribosome to inhibit the translocation of peptides.

Name: Sucralose
Information: Sucralose is an artificial and noncaloric sweetener, not broken down by the body.

Name: Ribostamycin Sulfate
Information: Ribostamycin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, containing a neutral sugar moiety, and is produced by Streptomyces ribosidi?cus.

Name: Valnemulin HCl
Information: Valnemulin HCl is a broad-spectrum bacteriostatic agent inhibiting protein synthesis in bacteria by binding to the peptidyl transferase component of the 50S subunit of ribosomes.

Name: Liothyronine Sodium
Information: Liothyronine Sodium is the most potent form of thyroid hormone acting on the body to increase the basal metabolic rate, affect protein synthesis.

Name: Amoxapine
Information: Amoxapine is a tricyclic dibenzoxazepine (an N-aryl piperazine) which acts similarly to several other tricyclic antidepressants, amoxapine inhibits GLYT2a transport activity with IC50 of 92 μM.

Name: Azaperone
Information: Azaperone crosses the blood-brain barrier and binds to both DI and D2 receptors, being an antagonist of Dopamine receptors with sedative and antiemetic effects, which is used mainly as a tranquilizer in veterinary medicine.

Name: Benzbromarone
Information: Benzbromarone is a CYP2C9 inhibitor, it binds to CYP2C9 with Ki value of 19.3 nM.

Name: Piperacillin Sodium
Information: Piperacillin is a semisynthetic, broad-spectrum, ampicillin derived ureidopenicillin antibiotic proposed for pseudomonas infections.

Name: Mevastatin
Information: Mevastatin is a competitive inhibitor of HMG-Coenzyme A (HMG-CoA) reductase with a binding affinity 10,000 times greater than the HMG-CoA substrate itself.

Name: Erythritol
Information: Erythritol is a sugar alcohol used as low-calorie sweetener.

Name: Mexiletine HCl
Information: Mexiletine HCl belongs to Class IB anti-arrhythmic group of medicines, inhibits sodium channels to reduce the inward sodium current.

Name: Minocycline HCl
Information: Minocycline HCl is the most lipid soluble and most active tetracycline antibiotic, binds to the 30S ribosomal subunit, preventing the binding of tRNA to the mRNA-ribosome complex and interfering with protein synthesis.

Name: Fidaxomicin
Information: Fidaxomicin is a narrow spectrum macrocyclic antibiotic that inhibits RNA polymerase sigma subunit.

Name: Fluorometholone Acetate
Information: Fluorometholone Acetate is a synthetic corticosteroid, used in the treatment of steroid responsive inflammatory conditions of the eye.

Name: Oxybuprocaine HCl
Information: Oxybuprocaine HCl is a local anesthetic, which is used especially in ophthalmology and otolaryngology. Oxybuprocaine binds to sodium channel and reversibly stabilizes the neuronal membrane which decreases its permeability to sodium ions

Name: Oxaprozin
Information: Oxaprozin is a non-narcotic, non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) used to relieve the inflammation, swelling, stiffness, and joint pain associated with osteoarthritis and rheumatoid arthritis.

Name: Pilocarpine HCl
Information: Pilocarpine HCl is a nonselective muscarinic acetylcholine receptor agonist used to produce an experimental model of epilepsy.

Name: Capreomycin Sulfate
Information: Capreomycin Sulfate is a cyclic peptide antibiotic and thought to inhibit protein synthesis by binding to the 70S ribosomal unit.

Name: Phenazopyridine HCl
Information: Phenazopyridine HCl is a local analgesic that has been used in urinary tract disorders. It is an inhibitor of sodium channel protein type 1 subunit alpha.

Name: Proflavine Hemisulfate
Information: Proflavine Hemisulfate is a topical antiseptic by interchelating DNA, thereby disrupting DNA synthesis and leading to high levels of mutation in the copied DNA strands.

Name: Primaquine Diphosphate
Information: Primaquine Diphosphate is a transmission-blocking anti-malarial clinically available, displaying a marked activity against gametocytes of all species of human malaria.

Name: Cepharanthine
Information: Cepharanthine is a biscoclaurine alkaloid inhibiting tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-α-mediated NFκB stimulation, plasma membrane lipid peroxidation and platelet aggregation and suppressing cytokine production.

Name: Bergapten
Information: Bergapten is a psoralen that can be photoactivated and is capable of crossing-linking DNA, covalently modifying proteins and lipids, and consequently inhibiting cell replication.

Name: Doxylamine Succinate
Information: Doxylamine succinate competitively inhibits histamine at H1 receptors with substantial sedative and anticholinergic effects.

Name: Cetrimonium Bromide (CTAB)
Information: Cetrimonium Bromide is a known component of the broad-spectrum antiseptic cetrimide, which is a mixture of different quaternary ammonium salts.

Name: Deoxycorticosterone acetate
Information: Deoxycorticosterone acetate is a steroid hormone used for intramuscular injection for replacement therapy of the adrenocortical steroid.

Name: Serotonin HCl
Information: Serotonin HCl is a monoamine neurotransmitter and Endogenous 5-HT receptor agonist.

Name: Sodium ascorbate
Information: Sodium Ascorbate is a more bioavailable form of vitamin C that is an alternative to taking ascorbic acid as a supplement.

Name: Tranylcypromine (2-PCPA) HCl
Information: Tranylcypromine is a monoamine oxidase inhibitor, which inhibits CYP2A6 with Ki of 0.08 μM and 0.2 μM in cDNA-expressing microsomes and Human Liver Microsomes, respectively.

Name: Prucalopride Succinate
Information: Prucalopride is a selective, high affinity 5-HT4 receptor agonist. The Ki values of prucalopride for human 5-HT(4a) and 5-HT(4b) receptor are 2.5 nM and 8 nM, respectively.

Name: Bromfenac Sodium
Information: Bromfenac Sodium is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID), which has anti-inflammatory activity and may block prostaglandin synthesis by inhibiting cyclooxygenase 1 and 2.

Name: Flopropione
Information: Flopropione is a spasmolytic or antispasmodic agent, and acts as a 5-HT1A receptor antagonist.

Name: Sulfamethoxypyridazine
Information: Sulfamethoxypyridazine is a long-acting sulfonamide for treatment of Dermatitis herpetiformis.

Name: Mechlorethamine HCl
Information: Mechlorethamine is the prototype of alkylating agents, it works by binding to DNA, crosslinking two strands and preventing cell duplication.

Name: Epinastine HCl
Information: Epinastine is an antihistamine and mast cell stabilizer that is used in eye drops to treat allergic conjunctivitis.

Name: Apramycin Sulfate
Information: Apramycin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, which binds to the deep groove of the RNA.

Name: Quinacrine 2HCl
Information: Quinacrine 2HCl is a lipophilic cationic drug with multiple actions that is commonly used as an anti-protozoal agent. Quinacrine is an effective phospholipase A2 inhibitor.

Name: Buspirone HCl
Information: Buspirone is a serotonergic (5HT(1A) receptor agonist) anxiolytic drug with some D(2) dopaminergic effect, used for anxiety disorders.

Name: Alizapride HCl
Information: Alizapride HCl is a dopamine receptor antagonist used for the theropy of nausea and vomiting.

Name: Luliconazole
Information: Luliconazole is a broad-spectrum antifungal drug.

Name: Vilazodone HCl
Information: Vilazodone HCl is a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) and a partial agonist of 5-HT1A receptors, used for the treatment of major depressive disorder.

Name: Tamibarotene
Information: Tamibarotene is a synthetic retinoic acid receptor (RAR) agonist with high specificity for RARα and RARβ over RARγ.

Name: EUK 134
Information: EUK 134, a synthetic superoxide dismutase (SOD)/catalase mimetic, exhibits potent antioxidant activities, and inhibits the formation of β-amyloid and related amyloid fibril.

Name: Ebastine
Information: Ebastine is a potent H1-histamine receptor antagonist, used for allergic disorders.

Name: Efaproxiral Sodium
Information: Efaproxiral Sodium is a synthetic allosteric modifier of hemoglobin, used for brain metastases originating from breast cancer.

Name: Etofibrate
Information: Etofibrate is a combination of clofibrate and niacin, used to treat hyperlipemia.

Name: Nicaraven
Information: Nicaraven is a hydroxyl radical scavenger with antivasospastic and neuroprotective effects.

Name: Brimonidine Tartrate
Information: Brimonidine Tartrate is a highly selective α-adrenergic receptor agonist with EC50 of 0.45 nM for the α2A adrenoreceptor, and used to treat open-angle glaucoma or ocular hypertension.

Name: Diacerein
Information: Diacerein is an inhibitor of pro-inflammatory cytokine Interleukin-1B (IL-1B) production, prescribed for osteoarthritis and chronic inflammatory arthritis.

Name: Flufenamic acid
Information: Flufenamic Acid is an anti-inflammatory agent, and also acts as an ion channel modulator.

Name: Vinorelbine Tartrate
Information: Vinorelbine Tartrate is a semi-synthetic vinca alkaloid, and inhibits mitosis through interaction with tubulin.

Name: Oxiracetam
Information: Oxiracetam, a cyclic derivative of gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA), is used as a nootropic drug to improve memory and learning.

Name: Isepamicin Sulphate
Information: Isepamicin Sulphate is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, which inhibits bacterial protein synthesis by targeting the bacterial 30S ribosomal subunit.

Name: Rotigotine
Information: Rotigotine is a dopamine receptor agonist, used in the treatment of Parkinson's disease and restless legs syndrome.

Name: Bambuterol HCl
Information: Bambuterol HCl is a potent β-adrenoceptor agonist, used in the treatment of asthma.

Name: Carteolol HCl
Information: Carteolol HCl is a β-adrenoceptor antagonist, used for the treatment of glaucoma.

Name: Demeclocycline HCl
Information: Demeclocycline HCl is a tetracycline antibiotic via inhibition of protein synthesis by bacteria, used for the treatment of bacterial infections.

Name: Meclofenoxate (Centrophenoxine) HCl
Information: Meclofenoxate (Centrophenoxine) HCl is an anti-aging drug used to treat the symptoms of senile dementia and Alzheimer's disease, and also inhibits the activity of cholinephosphotransferase.

Name: Tasimelteon
Information: Tasimelteon is a melatonin MT1 and MT2 receptor agonist.

Name: Nelfinavir Mesylate
Information: Nelfinavir Mesylate is a potent HIV protease inhibitor with Ki of 2 nM.

Name: Cyclobenzaprine HCl
Information: Cyclobenzaprine HCl is a muscle relaxant by blocking pain sensations, used for the treatment of muscle spasms A 5-HT2 receptor antagonist.

Name: Chloroprocaine HCl
Information: Chloroprocaine HCl is a local anesthetic during surgical procedures.

Name: Ospemifene
Information: Ospemifene is a non-hormonal selective estrogen receptor modulator (SERM), used for the treatment of dyspareunia.

Name: Anidulafungin (LY303366)
Information: Anidulafungin (LY303366), an echinocandin derivative, inhibits glucan synthase activity, used as an antifungal drug.

Name: Micafungin Sodium
Information: Micafungin Sodium is an inhibitor of 1, 3-beta-D-glucan synthesis, used as an antifungal drug.

Name: Chloroambucil
Information: Chlorambucil is a nitrogen mustard alkylating agent, used in the treatment of chronic lymphocytic leukemia.

Name: Metoclopramide HCl
Information: Metoclopramide HCl is a selective dopamine D2 receptor antagonist, used for the treatment of nausea and vomiting.

Name: Digoxin
Information: Digoxin is a classical Na,K-ATPase inhibitor, with selectivity for the α2β3 isoform over the common α1β1 isoform, used in the treatment of atrial fibrillation and heart failure.

Name: Labetalol HCl
Information: Labetalol HCl is a dual antagonist for both selective alpha1-adrenergic and nonselective beta-adrenergic receptors, used in the treatment of high blood pressure.

Name: Diphenidol HCl
Information: Diphenidol HCl is a potent antagonist of muscarinic M2 and M3 receptor with pKb of 6.72 and 7.02, respectively, used in the treatment of vomiting and vertigo.

Name: Promethazine HCl
Information: Promethazine HCl is a potent histamine H1 receptor antagonist, used as a sedative and antiallergic medication.

Name: Procainamide HCl
Information: Procainamide HCl is a sodium channel blocker, and also a DNA methyltransferase inhibitor, used in the treatment of cardiac arrhythmias.

Name: Meclofenamate Sodium
Information: Meclofenamate Sodium is a dual COX-1/COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 40 nM and 50 nM, respectively, used in the treatment of joint, muscular pain, arthritis and dysmenorrhea.

Name: Salmeterol Xinafoate
Information: Salmeterol Xinafoate is a long-acting β2-adrenergic receptor agonist with anti-inflammatory effects, used in the treatment of asthma symptoms and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) symptoms.

Name: Mupirocin
Information: Mupirocin is an isoleucyl t-RNA synthetase inhibitor, used in the treatment of bacterial skin infections.

Name: Amifostine
Information: Amifostine is the first approved radioprotective drug, used to decrease the risk of kidney problems caused by treatment with cisplatin.

Name: Dicoumarol
Information: Dicoumarol is a competitive NADPH quinone oxidoreductase (NQO1) inhibitor,and used as an anticoagulant by interfering with the metabolism of vitamin K.

Name: (R)-(+)-Atenolol HCl
Information: (R)-(+)-Atenolol binds to but does not activate beta-adrenergic receptors thereby blocking the actions of endogenous or exogenous beta-adrenergic agonists.

Name: 9-Aminoacridine
Information: Anisotropine Methylbromide is a quaternary ammonium compound, used as treatment adjunct in peptic ulcer.

Name: Anisindione
Information: Anisindione is a synthetic anticoagulant and an indanedione derivative.

Name: Anisotropine Methylbromide
Information: Anisotropine Methylbromide is a quaternary ammonium compound, used as treatment adjunct in peptic ulcer.

Name: Benzthiazide
Information: Benzthiazide is a thiazide diuretic, promoting water loss from the body.

Name: Bromocriptine Mesylate
Information: Bromocriptine, an ergoline derivative, is a dopamine agonist that is used in the treatment of pituitary tumors, Parkinson's disease (PD), hyperprolactinaemia, neuroleptic malignant syndrome, and type 2 diabetes.

Name: Calcium Gluceptate
Information: Calcium gluceptate is a calcium salt used in the treatment and prophylaxis of hypocalcemia and as an electrolyte replenisher.

Name: Carbadox
Information: Carbadox is an anti-inflammatory drug used in the treatment of Inflammatory Bowel Disease.

Name: Ceftazidime Pentahydrate
Information: Ceftazidime is a β-lactam antibacterial agent which has demonstrated a broad spectrum of activity against Gram-positive and Gram-negative aerobic bacteria.

Name: Clorgyline HCl
Information: Clorgiline is an irreversible and selective inhibitor of monoamine oxidase A (MAO-A).

Name: Disopyramide Phosphate
Information: Disopyramide (DISO) is a widely used Class 1a antiarrhythmic agent that is employed in the treatment of ventricular and supraventricular arrhythmias.

Name: Ethoxzolamide
Information: Ethoxzolamide is an inhibitor of the metalloenzyme carbonic anhydrase, which inhibits hCA I, hCA II, hCA IV, hCA VI and hCA VII with Ki of 25 nM, 8 nM, 93 nM, 43 nM and 0.8 nM, respectively.

Name: Guanethidine Sulfate
Information: Guanethidine is an antihypertensive drug that reduces the release of catecholamines, such as norepinephrine.

Name: Isoetharine Mesylate
Information: Isoetharine is a selective beta2-adrenergic receptor agonist, which gives quick relief for bronchospasm and asthma.

Name: Meclocycline Sulfosalicylate
Information: Meclocycline is a tetracycline antibiotic. Meclocycline sulfosalicylate prevents bacterial protein synthesis through 30S ribosome-mediated chain elongation and blocks amino-acyl tRNA A-site binding.

Name: Methoxamine HCl
Information: Methoxamine is an α1-adrenergic receptor agonist, it induces vasoconstriction of skin and splanchnic blood vessels.

Name: Nalmefene HCl
Information: Nalmefene is an opioid receptor antagonist, it is used primarily in the management of alcohol dependence.

Name: Oxethazaine
Information: Oxethazaine is a strong local anaesthetic, which acts in a number of ways to numb the walls of the stomach and relieve the pain associated with hyperacidic conditions.

Name: Oxprenolol HCl
Information: Oxprenolol is a non-selective beta blocker with some intrinsic sympathomimetic activity.

Name: Pentoxifylline
Information: Pentoxifylline is a competitive nonselective phosphodiesterase inhibitor which raises intracellular cAMP, activates PKA, inhibits TNF and leukotriene synthesis, and reduces inflammation and innate immunity.

Name: Piromidic Acid
Information: Piromidic acid is a quinolone antibiotic.

Name: Procyclidine HCl
Information: Procyclidine HCl blocks the effects of certain chemicals in the brain, and thus is used to treat Parkinson's disease or extrapyramidal side-effects caused by other medicines.

Name: Ractopamine HCl
Information: Ractopamine HCl (RAC), a beta-agonist with established nutrient partitioning capabilities, promotes skeletal muscle accretion at the expense of fat deposition.

Name: Terfenadine
Information: Terfenadine is an antihistamine, generally completely metabolizes to the active form fexofenadine in the liver by the enzyme cytochrome P450 CYP3A4 isoform.

Name: Thiostrepton
Information: Thiostrepton is a natural cyclic oligopeptide antibiotic, derived from several strains of strepromycetes.

Name: Tacrine HCl
Information: Tacrine is a centrally acting anticholinesterase and indirect cholinergic agonist.

Name: Pimozide
Information: Pimozide is an antipsychotic drug of the diphenylbutylpiperidine class, which is a strong inhibitor of CYP2D6.

Name: Carbachol
Information: Carbachol is a cholinomimetic drug that binds and activates the acetylcholine receptor.

Name: Tolmetin Sodium
Information: Tolmetin is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug of the arylalkanoic acids.

Name: Cinoxacin
Information: Cinoxacin is a chemotherapeutic agent that inhibits bacterial DNA synthesis.

Name: Glafenine HCl
Information: Glafenine is an anthranilic acid derivative with analgesic properties, which has been used previously in the treatment of pain.

Name: Phthalylsulfacetamide
Information: Phthalylsulfacetamide is a sulfonamide with a high solubility and suited for systemic use for diseases of the eye.

Name: Pinacidil
Information: Pinacidil is known to augment a time-independent outward current in cardiac tissues by activating the ATP-regulated potassium channels.

Name: Suxibuzone
Information: Suxibuzone is a prodrug of the non steroidal anti inflammatory drug phenylbutazone, and is commonly used in horses.

Name: Carbenoxolone Sodium
Information: Carbenoxolone, a synthetic derivative of glycyrrhetinic acid, is also used as a blocker of the enzyme 11β-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase (11β-HSD), of pannexon membrane channels (comprising 6 subunits of pannexin) and the related innexon channels.

Name: Nicotine Ditartrate
Information: Nicotine is a potent parasympathomimetic alkaloid found in the nightshade family of plants (Solanaceae), and also a nicotinic acetylcholine receptor agonist.

Name: Dicyclomine HCl
Information: Dicyclomine is an anticholinergic drug, a chemical released from nerves that stimulates muscles, by blocking the receptors for acetylcholine on smooth muscle (a type of muscle).

Name: Mepenzolate Bromide
Information: Mepenzolate is a post-ganglionic parasympathetic inhibitor, it decreases gastric acid and pepsin secretion and suppresses spontaneous contractions of the colon.

Name: Aceclidine HCl
Information: Aceclidine is a parasympathomimetic miotic agent used to decreases intraocular pressure.

Name: Imipramine HCl
Information: Imipramine is a tricyclic antidepressant (TCA) of the dibenzazepine group, mainly used in the treatment of major depression and enuresis (inability to control urination).

Name: Proadifen HCl
Information: Proadifen is an inhibitor of cytochrome P450 enzymes, preventing some types of drug metabolism.

Name: Pyrilamine Maleate
Information: Pyrilamine is a histamine H1 receptor inverse agonist, it binds to a G protein-coupled form of the receptor and promotes a G protein-coupled inactive state of the H1 receptor that interferes with the Gq/11-mediated signaling.

Name: Fosfomycin Tromethamine
Information: Fosfomycin tromethamine is a phosphonic acid bactericidal agent with in vitro activity against most urinary tract pathogens.

Name: Mefloquine HCl
Information: Mefloquine HCl is a blood schizonticide by inhibiting hemozoin formation, used as an antimalarial drug.

Name: Hydroxychloroquine Sulfate
Information: Hydroxychloroquine Sulfate is an antimalarial agent used for the treatment of systemic lupus erythematosus, rheumatoid arthritis and other autoimmune, inflammatory and dermatologic conditions. Also acts as an inhibitor of autophagy and toll-like receptor (TLR) 7/9.

Name: Eltrombopag
Information: Eltrombopag, a member of the biarylhydrazone class, is a nonpeptide agonist of the thrombopoietin receptor (TpoR), used to treat chronic hepatitis C-associated thrombocytopenia and chronic immune (idiopathic) thrombocytopenia (ITP).

Name: 6-Mercaptopurine (6-MP) Monohydrate
Information: 6-Mercaptopurine Monohydrate is a widely used antileukemic agent and immunosuppressive drug that inhibits de novo purine synthesis through incorporation of thiopurine methyltransferase metabolites into DNA and RNA.

Name: Vinblastine sulfate
Information: Vinblastine sulfate inhibits microtubule formation and suppresses nAChR activity with IC50 of 8.9 μM in a cell-free assay, used to treat certain kinds of cancer.

Name: Acetazolamide
Information: Acetazolamide, a potent carbonic anhydrase (CA) inhibitor, is commonly used in clinical practice as an immediate and readily available option for acute reduction of intraocular pressure(IOP).

Name: 17-Hydroxyprogesterone
Information: 17-Hydroxyprogesterone?(17-OHP) is an?endogenous?progestogen?as well as?chemical intermediate?in the?biosynthesis?of other?steroid hormones, including the?corticosteroids?and the?androgens?and the estrogens.

Name: 4-Aminoantipyrine
Information: 4-Aminoantipyrine(Ampyrone) is a metabolite of aminopyrine with analgesic, anti-inflammatory, and antipyretic properties. It is used as a reagent for biochemical reactions producing peroxides or phenols.
Synonyms: Ampyrone, NSC 60242, Metapirazone, Solnapyrin-A, Solvapyrin-A, Minoazophene, Aminoazophene, Aminoantipyrin

Name: 4-Aminobenzoic acid
Information: 4-Aminobenzoic acid is an intermediate in the synthesis of tetrahydrofolic acid in many non-mammalian organisms, including bacteria and fungi.

Name: Aceglutamide
Information: Aceglutamide is a psychostimulant, nootropic agent which functions as a prodrug to glutamine with improved potency and stability.

Name: Acetylleucine
Information: Acetylleucine is a drug used in the treatment of vertigo.

Name: Ademetionine disulfate tosylate
Information: Ademetionine Disulfate Tosylate is the disulfate-tosylate mixed salt of a mixture of diastereoisomers of the ademetionine ions. Ademetionine possesses anti-inflammatory activity and has been used in treatment of chronic liver disease.

Name: (+)-Camphor
Information: Camphor is a waxy, flammable, white or transparent solid with a strong aroma, often used to relieve pain, reduce itching and treat fungal infections. It can activate TRPV1 and TRPV3.

Name: Cefotaxime sodium
Information: Cefotaxime sodium salt is a third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic broad-spectrum antibiotic with activity against numerous Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria.

Name: Chloroxylenol
Information: Chloroxylenol is a broad-spectrum antimicrobial chemical compound used to control bacteria, algae, fungi and virus.

Name: Citric acid trilithium salt tetrahydrate
Information: Citric acid trilithium salt tetrahydrate is a pharmaceutical and construction material. It is commonly used in HPLC gradient elution for quantification of amino acids.
Synonyms: Trilithium citrate tetrahydrate, Lithium citrate tribasic tetrahydrate

Name: 2-Aminoheptane

Information: 2-Aminoheptane is a nasal decongestant drug which is a sympathomimetic stimulant and vasoconstrictor.

Name: DEET
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Information: DEET is a commen active ingredient insect repellent.

Name: Dihydrostreptomycin sulfate
Information: Dihydrostreptomycin sulfate is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, used to treat bacterial diseases in cattle, pigs and sheep. Dihydrostreptomycin is a derivative of streptomycin.

Name: Ethylparaben
Information: Ethylparaben is the ethyl ester of p-hydroxybenzoic acid, used as an antifungal preservative and food additive. It is a standardized chemical allergen. The physiologic effect of ethylparaben is by means of Increased Histamine Release, and Cell-mediated Immunity.

Name: Fenbufen
Information: Fenbufen is an orally active phenylalkanoic derivative with anti-inflammatory, analgesic and antipyretic activity. It is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug.

Name: Fenofibric acid
Information: Fenofibric acid is a fibrate that acts as a lipid-lowering agent, decreasing low-density lipoprotein cholesterol and triglycerides.

Name: Furazolidone
Information: Furazolidone is a synthetic nitrofuran derivative with bactericidal or bacteriostatic activity when used against Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria.

Name: Iopamidol
