Information: Isatin is an endogenous MAO inhibitor with an IC50 of 15 μM and more active against MAO-B than MAO-A.

Name: Acetylcholine iodide
Information: Acetylcholine iodide is a neurotransmitter found at neuromuscular junctions, autonomic ganglia, parasympathetic effector junctions, a subset of sympathetic effector junctions, and at many sites in the central nervous system.

Name: Kynurenic acid
Information: Kynurenic acid, a natural metabolite of tryptophan via the kynurenine pathway, is a broad-spectrum excitatory amino acid antagonist It proved to be an antagonist at NMDA, kainate and AMPA receptors.

Name: L-Glutamic acid monosodium salt
Information: L-Glutamic acid monosodium salt is the sodium salt of glutamic acid, found naturally in tomatoes, cheese and other foods.

Name: (+)-Catechin
Information: Cianidanol is an antioxidant flavonoid, occurring especially in woody plants as both (+)-catechin and (-)-epicatechin (cis) forms.

Name: (-)Epicatechin
Information: (?)Epicatechin is a flavonoid present in cocoa, green tea and red wine. It is a strong antioxidant, has insulin mimic action and improves heart health.

Name: Benzenesulfonamide
Information: Benzenesulfonamide ia an inhibitor of carbonic anhydrases.
Synonyms: Benzenesulphonamide, Benzosulfonamide, Phenyl sulfonamide, Benzene sulfonamide

Name: Lauric Acid
Information: Lauric Acid is a saturated medium-chain fatty acid with a 12-carbon backbone. Lauric acid is found naturally in various plant and animal fats and oils, and is a major component of coconut oil and palm kernel oil.
Synonyms: dodecanoic acid, N-Dodecanoic acid, Dodecylic acid

Name: Cinnarizine
Information: Cinnarizine is a medication derivative of piperazine, and characterized as an antihistamine and a calcium channel blocker.

Name: 3,3'-Diindolylmethane
Information: 3,3'-Diindolylmethane(DIM) is a major digestive product of indole-3-carbinol, a potential anticancer component of cruciferous vegetables.

Name: Tamsulosin hydrochloride
Information: Tamsulosin is a potent and selective α1a adrenergic receptor antagonist with Ki values of 0.13 nM, 1.92 nM and 0.18 nM for α1a-AR, α1b-AR and α1d-AR.

Name: Perphenazine
Information: Perphenazine is a phenothiazine derivative and a dopamine antagonist with antiemetic and antipsychotic properties.

Name: Retigabine
Information: Retigabine(free base) is a novel anticonvulsant with activity in a broad range of seizure models. The mechanism of action involves opening of neuronal K(V)7.2-7.5 (formerly KCNQ2-5) voltage-activated K(+) channels.

Name: Retigabine 2HCl
Information: Retigabine is a novel anticonvulsant with activity in a broad range of seizure models. The mechanism of action involves opening of neuronal K(V)7.2-7.5 (formerly KCNQ2-5) voltage-activated K(+) channels.

Name: Salvianolic acid B
Information: Salvianolic acid B (Sal B), an antioxidant and free radical scavenging compound, is the most abundant bioactive compound extracted from the root of Salvia miltiorrhiza Bunge.

Name: Trapidil
Information: Trapidil is a PDGF antagonist that can inhibit the proliferation of the PDGF-producing glioma cells.

Name: Psoralen
Information: Psoralen is a naturally occurring furocoumarin that intercalates with DNA, inhibiting DNA synthesis and cell division.

Name: Sodium ferulate
Information: Sodium ferulate (SF), the sodium salt of ferulic acid, is a drug used in traditional Chinese medicine for treatment of cardiovascular and cerebrovascular diseases and to prevent thrombosis.

Name: Danshensu
Information: Danshensu, a herbal preparation used in traditional Chinese medicine, possesses potential antitumor and anti?angiogenesis effects.

Name: Wogonin
Information: Wogonin, a natural and biologically-active flavonoid found in plants, is an inhibitor of CDK9 and does not inhibit CDK2, CDK4 and CDK6 at doses that inhibit CDK9 activity Also inhibits N-acetyltransferase.

Name: Ondansetron Hydrochloride Dihydrate
Information: Ondansetron is a highly specific and selective serotonin 5-HT3 receptor antagonist (Ki=6.16 nM), with low affinity for dopamine receptors.

Name: Citalopram HBr
Information: Citalopram HBr, an antidepressant, is an orally administered selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) with IC50 of 1.8 nM.
Synonyms: Nitalapram HBr, Prepram HBr, Bonitrile HBr, Lu 10-171 HBr

Name: Sulfacetamide sodium salt hydrate
Information: Sulfacetamide is a sulfonamide antibiotic that blocks the synthesis of dihydrofolic acid by inhibiting the enzyme dihydropteroate synthase(DHPS) with IC50 of 9.5 μM. Sulfacetamide is a competitive inhibitor of bacterial para-aminobenzoic acid (PABA), which is required for bacterial synthesis of folic acid.

Name: Cisapride hydrate
Information: Cisapride acts directly as a selective serotonin 5-HT4 receptor agonist with IC50 of 0.483 μM. And It also acts indirectly as a parasympathomimetic.

Name: Corticosterone
Information: Corticosterone, the major stress hormone, is an adrenocortical steroid that has modest but significant activities as a mineralocorticoid and a glucocorticoid.

Name: Betulin
Information: Betulin (BE), also known as betulinol, betuline, or betulinic alcohol, is a pentacyclic lupane-type triterpenoid naturally distributed in many plants and displays a broad spectrum of biological and pharmacological properties such as anticancer and chemopreventive activity.

Name: Dihydrotestosterone(DHT)
Information: Dihydrotestosterone is an endogenous androgen sex steroid and hormone and a potent agonist of the androgen receptor with 2-3-fold greater androgen receptor affinity than testosterone and 10-fold higher potency of inducing androgen receptor signaling.

Name: p-Coumaric Acid
Information: p-Coumaric acid is a hydroxy derivative of cinnamic acid found in a variety of edible plants and is reported to have antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial activity.
Synonyms: 4-Hydroxycinnamic acid, P-Hydroxycinnamic acid, 4-Coumaric acid, Trans-p-Coumaric acid, para-Coumaric Acid

Name: Melibiose
Information: Melibiose is a nondigestible disaccharide that consists of one galactose and one glucose moiety in an alpha (1-6) glycosidic linkage.

Name: L-5-Hydroxytryptophan
Information: 5-Hydroxytryptophan (5-HTP), also known as oxitriptan, is a naturally occurring amino acid and chemical precursor as well as a metabolic intermediate in the biosynthesis of the neurotransmitter serotonin.

Name: Creatine phosphate disodium salt
Information: Phosphocreatine, also known as creatine phosphate (CP) or PCr (Pcr), is a phosphorylated creatine molecule that serves as a rapidly mobilizable reserve of high-energy phosphates in skeletal muscle and the brain to recycle adenosine triphosphate, the energy currency of the cell.

Name: Harmaline
Information: Harmaline, a natural occurrence β-carboline alkaloid, is a central nervous system stimulant and an acetylcholinesterase (AChR) inhibitor also inhibits histamine N-methyltransferase.

Name: Plumbagin
Information: Plumbagin, a quinoid constituent isolated from the root of the medicinal plant Plumbago zeylanica L, exerts anticancer and antiproliferative activities in animal models and in cell culture.

Name: Menadiol Diacetate
Information: Menadiol Diacetate (Vitamin K4) is a synthetic hydrophilic menadione compound, which is clinically used as hemostasis medicine. It induces caspase-3-related apoptosis pathway via mitochondrial dysfunction and DNA fragmentation.

Name: Benzyl isothiocyanate
Information: Benzyl isothiocyanate (BITC) is an isothiocyanate originally found in cruciferous vegetables that exhibits immunomodulatory, anti-parasitic, antibiotic, antioxidative, anti-atherosclerotic, anti-angiogenic, anti-metastatic, anticancer chemotherapeutic, and chemopreventive activities.
Synonyms: Benzyl isothiocyanate, Benzoylthiocarbimide, Isothiocyanic Acid Benzoyl Ester

Name: N-Acetylneuraminic acid
Information: N-Acetylneuraminic acid (Neu5Ac or NANA) is the predominant sialic acid found in mammalian cells. Sialic acids are negatively charged monosaccharides attached to the end of sugar chains, giving rise to a wide variety of glycoproteins and glycolipids in biological fluids and cell membranes.
Synonyms: Neu5Ac, NeuAc, Acido aceneuramico, Acide aceneuramique, Acidium aceneuramicum, Sialic acid

Name: Drostanolone Propionate
Information: Drostanolone Propionate is an anabolic androgenic steroid with strong anti-estrogenic properties.

Name: Trenbolone acetate
Information: Trenbolone acetate, a synthetic anabolic steroid, is an androgen ester and a long-acting prodrug of trenbolone.

Name: Methandrostenolone
Information: Methandrostenolone is a synthetic steroid with anabolic properties that are more pronounced than its androgenic effects.
Synonyms: Dianabol, Metanabol, Methandienone, Methandrolone, Dehydromethyltestosterone, Perabol

Name: Nicergoline
Information: Nicergoline is an ergot derivative used to treat senile dementia and other disorders with vascular origins. It has a selective alpha-1A adrenergic receptor blocking property and also other additional mechanisms of actions.

Name: Daminozide
Information: Daminozide, a plant growth regulator, selectively inhibits the KDM2/7 JmjC subfamily with IC50 of 1.5±0.7 μM for KDM2A. It is at least 100-fold selective as an inhibitor of the KDM2/7 subfamily over the other demethylase subfamily members tested, with IC50s of 2 μM or less against KDM2A, PHF8, and KIAA1718 and IC50s of 127 μM for KDM3A or greater (mM range) against other demethylases.

Name: Thymidine
Information: Thymidine is a pyrimidine nucleoside that is composed of the pyrimidine base thymine attached to the sugar deoxyribose. As a constituent of DNA, thymidine pairs with adenine in the DNA double helix.

Name: Glycylglycine
Information: Glycylglycine, the simplest peptide made of two glycine molecules, is usually used in the synthesis of more complicated peptides.

Name: VitaMin U
Information: Vitamin U (Methylmethionine chloride) is a vitamin found in green vegetables. It is used in the treatment of peptic ulcers, colitis, and gastritis and has an effect on secretory, acid-forming, and enzymatic functions of the intestinal tract.

Name: Ceftizoxime
Information: Ceftizoxime is a semisynthetic cephalosporin antibiotic which can be administered intravenously or by suppository. It is highly resistant to a broad spectrum of beta-lactamases and is active against a wide range of both aerobic and anaerobic gram-positive and gram-negative organisms.

Name: Cefuroxime axetil
Information: Cefuroxime axetil, a prodrug of the cephalosporin cefuroxime, is a second generation oral cephalosporin antibiotic with in vitro antibacterial activity against several gram-positive and gram-negative organisms.

Name: L-Cysteine HCl
Information: L-cysteine Hydrochloride, also known as L-CYSTEINE or Cysteine HCL (anhydrous), is classified as a cysteine or a cysteine derivative that increases glutathione levels and is important for lung and brain function and liver detoxification.

Name: Diatrizoate sodium
Information: Diatrizoate sodium is an iodinated radiopaque X-ray contrast medium that is used as a diagnostic aid in angiography, urography and radiography.

Name: Atenolol
Information: Atenolol is a selective β1 receptor antagonist with log Kd values of ?6.66±0.05, ?5.99±0.14, ?4.11±0.07 for binding to the human β1-, β2- and β3-adrenoceptors.

Name: Saccharin
Information: Saccharin is an artificial sweetener with effectively no food energy.
Synonyms: Benzoic sulfimide, O-Sulfobenzimide, O-Benzoic sulfimide, Saccharimide

Name: Diastase
Information: Diastase, a natural enzyme, catalyses the breakdown of starch into maltose.

Name: Glycine
Information: Glycine is a non-essential, non-polar, non-optical, glucogenic amino acid that is primarily found in gelatin and silk fibroin. It is involved in the body's production of DNA, phospholipids and collagen, and in release of energy.

Name: Aluminium hydroxide
Information: Aluminium hydroxide, found in nature as the mineral gibbsite, is amphoteric (i.e., it has both basic and acidic properties). It is used to treat symptoms of increased stomach acid, such as heartburn, upset stomach, sour stomach, or acid indigestion also reduce phosphate levels in people with certain kidney conditions.
Synonyms: Aluminic hydroxide, Aluminum trihydroxide, Aluminium(III) hydroxide

Name: Manganese chloride
Information: Manganese chloride occurs in nature as the mineral. It is used as a precursor for other manganese compounds.

Name: Sodium carbonate
Information: Sodium Carbonate is the disodium salt of carbonic acid with alkalinizing property.
Synonyms: Disodium carbonate, Soda Ash, Carbonic acid disodium salt

Name: Maltose
Information: Maltose, an non-essential nutrient that provides energy, is an intermediate in the intestinal digestion of glycogen and starch, and is found in germinating grains (and other plants and vegetables).

Name: Piperonyl butoxide
Information: Piperonyl butoxide (PBO) is a man-made pesticide synergist, working with insect killers to increase their effectiveness.

Name: Tolmetin
Information: Tolmetin is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug of the heterocyclic acetic acid derivative class and also exhibits analgesic and antipyretic activity.

Name: Cefoxitin sodium
Information: Cefoxitin Sodium is the sodium salt form of cefoxitin, a beta-lactam, second-generation cephalosporin antibiotic with bactericidal activity.

Name: Aceclofenac
Information: Aceclofenac is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) with anti-inflammatory and analgesic properties.

Name: Nilutamide
Information: Nilutamide is a nonsteroidal antiandrogen (NSAA) with affinity for androgen receptors (but not for progestogen, estrogen, or glucocorticoid receptors). It is used in the treatment of prostate cancer.

Name: Ibudilast
Information: Ibudilast is a relatively non-selective phosphodiesterase inhibitor with anti-inflammatory and neuroprotective activities.

Name: Acotiamide hydrochloride
Information: Acotiamide Hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt form of acotiamide, a prokinetic agent with gastrointestinal (GI) motility-enhancing activity. It is a new orally active selective acetylcholinesterase inhibitor.

Name: Mosapride
Information: Mosapride is a gastroprokinetic agent that acts as a selective 5HT4 agonist.

Name: Laurocapram
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Information: Laurocapram is a skin penetration enhancer that facilitates absorption of cutaneously applied substances.
Synonyms: N-Dodecylcaprolactam, Azone, N-0252, N-Lauryl caprolactam, Tranzone

Name: Potassium acetate
Information: Potassium acetate is the potassium salt of acetic acid, which is a synthetic carboxylic acid with antibacterial and antifungal properties.

Name: Cefcapene Pivoxil Hydrochloride
Information: Cefcapene Pivoxil is the pivalate ester prodrug form of cefcapene, a semi-synthetic third-generation cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: Rabeprazole
Information: Rabeprazole is an oral inhibitor of proton pump and blocks the production of acid by the stomach.

Name: Meropenem Trihydrate
Information: Meropenem is a broad-spectrum antibacterial agent of the carbapenem family with a broad spectrum of in vitro activity against Gram-positive and Gram-negative pathogens.

Name: Faropenem Sodium
Information: Faropenem sodium is an orally active beta-lactam antibiotic that has been used in trials studying the treatment of Tuberculosis, Pulmonary Tuberculosis, and Community Acquired Pneumonia.

Name: Dalbavancin
Information: Dalbavancin is a lipoglycopeptide antibiotic that has bactericidal activity against Gram-positive bacteria including various staphylococci.

Name: Levocetirizine Dihydrochloride
Information: Levocetirizine is the active R-enantiomer of cetirizine and represents a new second-generation histamine H1 antagonist.

Name: Flucloxacillin sodium
Information: Flucloxacillin sodium is the sodium salt of flucloxacillin, a penicillin antibiotic used to treat bacterial infections.

Name: Tafluprost
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Information: Tafluprost is a novel prostaglandin analog with a high affinity for the fluoroprostaglandin (FP) receptor PGF2α. A prostanoid selective FP receptor agonist.

Name: Gadopentetate Dimeglumine
Information: Gadopentetate Dimeglumine, a complex of gadolinium with a chelating agent, diethylenetriamine penta-acetic acid, is an extracellular intravenous contrast agent used in magnetic resonance imaging.
Synonyms: Gadopentetic acid dimeglumine, Gd-DTPA, Meglumine gadopentetate

Name: Ecabet sodium
Information: Ecabet sodium is a widely employed mucoprotective agent for the treatment of gastric ulcers.

Name: Bedaquiline fumarate
Information: Bedaquiline fumarate, an oral diarylquinoline, is a bactericidal antimycobacterial drug. It is a proton-translocating ATP synthetase inhibitor.

Name: Iproniazid
Information: Iproniazid is a non-selective, irreversible monoamine oxidase (MAO) inhibitor (MAOI) that is used as an antidepressive agent.

Name: TriacetonaMine
Information: TriacetonaMine, a member of the class of compounds known as piperidinones, is an extremely weak acidic compound found in green vegetables and tea.

Name: Indole-3-carboxylic acid
Information: Indole-3-carboxylic acid is a normal urinary indolic tryptophan metabolite which belongs to a class of organic compounds known as indolecarboxylic acids and derivatives.

Name: Squalene
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Information: Squalene, a naturally occurring substance found in plants, animals and humans, is a component of some adjuvants that is added to vaccines to enhance the immune response.

Name: Cefetamet pivoxil hydrochloride
Information: Cefetamet pivoxil hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt form of cefetamet pivoxil, which is an oral third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic.

Name: Nicarbazin
Information: Nicarbazin, an effective anticoccidial, is also a wide-spectrum anti-parasitic drug.

Name: Propacetamol hydrochloride
Information: Propacetamol hydrochloride (PRO) is a water-soluble prodrug of paracetamol (PA) which can be parenterally administered as analgesic for the treatment of postoperative pain, acute trauma, and gastric and/or intestinal disorders.

Name: Xanthinol Nicotinate
Information: Xanthinol Nicotinate is a potent vasodilator that can easily pass through the cell membrane and once inside the cell it causes an increase in glucose metabolism resulting in an increased energy.

Name: Sulfamethoxazole sodium
Information: Sulfamethoxazole sodium is an antibiotic used for bacterial infections.

Name: Cefodizime Sodium
Information: Cefodizime Sodium, a third generation cephalosporin antibiotic, has broad-spectrum activity and is stable to most beta-lactamases.

Name: Pyridoxal 5-phosphate monohydrate
Information: Pyridoxal 5-phosphate monohydrate is an active vitamin B6 metabolite, which is a cofactor in many reactions of amino acid metabolism.

Name: Titanium tetrafluoride
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Information: Titanium tetrafluoride is an inorganic compound that is an effective but instable caries preventive agent.

Name: Cefazedone
Information: Cefazedone is a semisynthetic first-generation cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: Cephapirin Benzathine
Information: Cephapirin Benzathine is the benzathine salt form of cephapirin, which is a semisynthetic, broad-spectrum, first-generation cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: Robenidine Hydrochoride
Information: Robenidine hydrochloride is an anticoccidial agent mainly for poultry.

Name: Eperisone hydrochloride
Information: Eperisone hydrochloride is muscle relaxant agent with antispasmodic effects. It is widely used in the treatment of patients with muscular contractures, low back pain or spasticity.

Name: Neticonazole Hydrochloride
Information: Neticonazole is an imidazole antifungal for the treatment of fungal skin infections.

Name: Cefathiamidine
Information: Cefathiamidine is the first generation of cephalosporin antibacterial used for the treatment of respiratory, liver, five senses, urinary tract infections, endocarditis and sepsis.

Name: Calcium Dobesilate
Information: Calcium dobesilate is a small molecule that has been widely used for treating diabetic retinopathy and chronic venous insufficiency.

Name: Lynestrenol
Information: Lynestrenol is a synthetic progestational hormone, an agonist of the progesterone receptor and has weak androgenic and estrogenic activity.

Name: Taurolidine
Information: Taurolidine is a synthetic broad-spectrum antibiotic with antibacterial, anticoagulant and potential antiangiogenic activities.

Name: Menbutone
Information: Menbutone, or genabilic acid, is a derivative of oxybutyric acid which acts as a choleretic stimulating secretion, a trypsinogen and a pepsinogen.

Name: Nikethamide
Information: Nikethamide is a respiratory stimulant that acts directly in the respiratory centres of brain.

Name: Perospirone hydrochloride
Information: Perospirone is an atypical or second-generation antipsychotic of the azapirone family that antagonizes serotonin 5HT2A receptors and dopamine D2 receptors. It also displays affinity towards 5HT1A receptors as a partial agonist.

Name: Bifendate
Information: Bifendate, a synthetic intermediate of schisandrin C, is an anti-HBV drug used in Chinese medicine for the treatment of chronic hepatitis B.

Name: Cytosine
Information: Cytosine is one of the four main bases found in DNA and RNA used in storing and transporting genetic information within a cell.

Name: Elagolix Sodium
Information: Elagolix Soidum is a potent, selective, orally active, non-peptide antagonist of the gonadotropin-releasing hormone receptor (GnRHR) with Kd value of 54 pM. Concentration at 10 μM shows no significant activity on ion channels, enzymes, and transporters (inhibition <50%).

Name: Sulfogaiacol
Information: Sulfogaiacol is a antitussive agent that is used for acute respiratory tract infections, cough and other conditions.

Name: SN-38
Information: SN-38 is an active metabolite of CPT-11, inhibits DNA topoisomerase I, DNA synthesis and causes frequent DNA single-strand breaks.

Name: (R)-Nepicastat HCl
Information: (R)-Nepicastat HCl, the R-enantiomer of Nepicastat HCl, is a potent and selective inhibitor with IC50 of 25.1 nM and 18.3 nM for bovine and human dopamine-β-hydroxylase, with negligible affinity for twelve other enzymes and thirteen neurotransmitter receptors.

Name: Cetilistat
Information: Cetilistat is a novel highly lipophilic benzoxazinone that inhibits gastrointestinal and pancreatic lipases. It shows a good safety and tolerability profile in vivo

Name: Propiverine hydrochloride
Information: Propiverine is an anticholinergic drug used for the treatment of overactive bladder and urinary incontinence.

Name: Proxyphylline
Information: Proxyphylline is a derivative of theophylline which is used as a bronchodilator and for its cardiovascular properties. It selectively antagonizes A1 adenosine receptors (Ki = 82 nM for bovine brain) versus A2 adenosine receptors (Ki = 850 ?M for platelets).

Name: Lithium carbonate
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Information: Used in treatment of manic depression.

Name: Asunaprevir
Information: Asunaprevir is an orally bioavailable inhibitor of the hepatitis C virus enzyme serine protease NS3 that is necessary for protein processing required for viral replication.

Name: cis-Aconitic acid
Information: Cis-Aconitic acid is an intermediate in the tricarboxylic acid cycle produced by the dehydration of citric acid.
Synonyms: cis-aconitate, Achilleic acid, Citridinic acid, Equisetic acid, Pyrocitric acid

Name: Maltol
Information: Maltol is a naturally occurring organic compound that is flavour enhancer and flavouring agent.

Name: Nonanoic acid
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Information: Nonanoic acid is a naturally occurring fatty acid found in both vegetable and animal fats.

Name: L(+)-Asparagine monohydrate
Information: L-asparagine is a non-essential amino acid that is involved in the metabolic control of cell functions in nerve and brain tissue, being used for a variety of pharmaceutical applications.

Name: L-Threonine
Information: L-Threonine is an essential amino acid which is in its active form. It is important for the formation of collagen, elastin, and tooth enamel, and aids liver and lipotropic function when combined with aspartic acid and methionine.

Name: Fumaric acid
Information: Fumaric acid is an intermediate in the citric acid cycle used by cells to produce energy in the form of adenosine triphosphate (ATP) from food also a product of the urea cycle.
Synonyms: 2-Butenedioic acid, Trans-Butenedioic acid, Allomaleic acid, Boletic acid, Donitic acid, Lichenic acid, Fumarate

Name: Usnic acid
Information: Usnic acid is a furandione found uniquely in lichen that is used widely in cosmetics, deodorants, toothpaste and medicinal creams as well as some herbal products. It exhibits antiviral, antiprotozoal, antiproliferative, anti-inflammatory and analgesic activity.

Name: Linalool
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Information: Linalool, a monoterpene compound commonly found as major component of essential oils of several aromatic species, is a competitive antagonist of NMDA receptors.

Name: Glycocholic acid
Information: Glycocholic acid is a natural secondary bile acid involved in the emulsification of fats.

Name: Agmatine sulfate
Information: Agmatine sulfate is a bioactive metabolite of the arginine amino acid. It has been shown to increase nitric oxide, reduce blood sugar levels and even increase growth hormone levels.

Name: Lactobionic acid
Information: Lactobionic acid, an α-hydroxyacid (AHA) with antioxidation activity, is used in the development of cosmeceuticals for skin.

Name: Buparvaquone
Information: Buparvaquone is a second-generation hydroxynaphthoquinone related to parvaquone, with novel features that make it a promising compound for the therapy and prophylaxis of all forms of theileriosis.

Name: Choline Glycerophosphate
Information: Choline Glycerophosphate is a choline derivative and one of the two major forms of choline storage (along with phosphocholine) in the cytosol.

Name: Iminostilbene
Information: Iminostilbene (Dibenzazepine) is a chemical precursor of carbamazepine which is used primarily in the treatment of epilepsy and neuropathic pain.

Name: Fimasartan
Information: Fimasartan is a non-peptide angiotensin II receptor antagonist (ARB) with noncompetitive, insurmountable binding with the AT1 receptor. It is used for the treatment of hypertension and heart failure.

Name: Sulfalene(SMPZ)
Information: Sulfalene（SMPZ）is a cyclic organic chemical used as a versatile synthetic intermediate.

Name: Efonidipine
Information: Efonidipine is an L- and T-type calcium channel blocker leading to vasodilation and decreased automaticity of the heart. It also suppresses aldosterone secretion from the adrenal.

Name: Azathramycin
Information: Azathramycin (Azaerythromycin) is a macrolide antibiotic containing cladinose.

Name: Anamorelin
Information: Anamorelin (ONO-7643, RC-1291, ST-1291) is an orally active, high-affinity, selective agonist of the ghrelin receptor with an EC50 value of 0.74 nM in the HEK293/GRLN FLIPR assay.

Name: Sorbic acid
Information: Sorbic acid is a naturally occurring compound that originated from the unripe berries of the Rowan Tree. It inhibits various bacteria, including sporeformers, at various stages of their life cycle (germination, outgrowth and cell division).

Name: Latamoxef sodium
Information: Latamoxef sodium is an antibiotic compound more effective against Escherichia coli and Pseudomonas aeruginosathan cephalosporins

Name: Tiamulin fumarate
Information: Tiamulin fumarate is a semisynthetic pleuromutilin antibiotic that binds to the ribosomal peptidyl transferase centre and inhibits protein synthesis.

Name: Valpromide
Information: Valpromide is an antiepileptic drug, derivative of Valproic acid (VPA), used as a mood-stabilizer in bipolar disorder.

Name: Timonacic
Information: Timonacic is a cyclic sulfur amino acid derivative with potential antineoplastic and antioxidant activities.

Name: Methylcobalamin
Information: Methylcobalamin is one active form of vitamin B12 which can directly participate in homocysteine metabolism. It is used to treat some nutritional diseases and other diseases in clinic, such as Alzheimer's disease and rheumatoid arthritis.

Name: Tavaborole (AN-2690)
Information: Tavaborole (AN-2690) is a boron-containing small molecule with broad spectrum antifungal activity.

Name: Avermectin B1
Information: Avermectin B1 (Abamectin) is a widely used insecticide and anthelmintic.

Name: Tofacitinib (CP-690550) Citrate
Information: Tofacitinib citrate (CP-690550 citrate) is a novel inhibitor of JAK with IC50 of 1 nM, 20 nM and 112 nM against JAK3, JAK2, and JAK1, respectively.

Name: Fingolimod (FTY720) HCl
Information: Fingolimod (FTY720) HCl is a S1P antagonist with IC50 of 0.033 nM in K562, and NK cells.

Name: Tacrolimus (FK506)
Information: Tacrolimus (FK506) is a 23-membered macrolide lactone, it reduces peptidyl-prolyl isomerase activity in T cells by binding to the immunophilin FKBP12 (FK506 binding protein) creating a new complex.

Name: Pimecrolimus
Information: Pimecrolimus is an immunophilin ligand, which binds specifically to the cytosolic receptor, immunophilin macrophilin-12 (FKBP-12) a calcineurin inhibitor.

Name: Cefotiam hydrochloride
Information: Cefotiam hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt form of cefotiam and has a broad spectrum of activity against both gram-positive and gram-negative microorganisms.

Name: Teprenone
Information: Teprenone, an acylic polyisoprenoid, that is known as tetraprenylacetone or geranylgeranylacetone, is an anti-ulcer drug, clinically used for gastritis.

Name: Delamanid
Information: Delamanid is a new anti-tuberculosis drug with an excellent intracellular bactericidal activity and a high accumulation rate.

Name: Brivudine
Information: Brivudine is a uridine derivative and nucleoside analog with pro-apoptotic and chemosensitizing properties. It is incorporated into the viral DNA and blocks the action of DNA polymerases, thus inhibiting viral replication.

Name: Indometacin Sodium
Information: Indometacin is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) used most commonly for the treatment of inflammation and pain resulting from rheumatic disease (arthritis), and less commonly in postoperative pain management. When taken for chronic pain conditions, indometacin has been associated with a high incidence of adverse events. The benefits and harms of orally-administered indometacin for postoperative pain are not clear.

Name: Disodium Phosphate

Name: Octenidine Dihydrochloride

It has a medium inhibitory concentration (IC50) <13 nM for all HCV NS3/4A enzymes(genotypes 1a, 1b, 2, 4, 5, and 6), but has an IC50 value of 37 nM for genotype 3.

Information: Mebhydrolin Napadisylate is classified as an antihistamine drug classes used to treat allergies.

Name: Indobufen

Name: Tilorone dihydrochloride
Information: Tilorone dihydrochloride is a broad-spectrum, orally active antiviral agent that activates interferon production. It has antitumor, anti-inflammatory properties.

Name: Nadolol
Information: Nadolol is a non-selective beta-adrenergic antagonist with antihypertensive and antiarrhythmic activities.

Name: Efinaconazole
Information: Efinaconazole is an inhibitor of 14 alpha-demethylase which is involved in the biosynthesis of ergosterol, a constituent of fungal cell membranes.

Name: Mebeverine Hydrochloride
Information: Mebeverine, a 3-phenylethylamine derivative of methoxybenzamine, acts as a musculotropic antispasmodic agent.
Synonyms: Duspatalin Hydrochloride, Duspatal Hydrochloride, Colofac Hydrochloride

Name: 4-Aminopyridine
Information: 4-Aminopyridine (4-AP) is a potent and non-selective inhibitor of voltage gated potassium channels (Kv) with IC50 values of 170 μM and 230 μM for Kv1.1 and Kv1.2 in CHO cells, respectively.

Name: Etofylline
Information: Etofylline is a N-7 substituted theophylline derivative used as a bronchodilator.

Name: Dihydralazine sulphate
Information: Dihydralazine sulphate is a dihydralazine-l,4-phthalazine derivative and used as an antihypertensive drug.

Name: Sulfaquinoxaline sodium
Information: Sulfaquinoxaline sodium (N'1-quinoxalin-2-ylsulphanilamide sodium, SQ-Na) is the sodium salt of sulfaquinoxaline, which is often used as a drug to prevent coccidiosis in poultry, swine, and sheep by inhibiting the synthesis of nucleic acids and proteins in microorganisms.

Name: Mephenesin
Information: Mephenesin is centrally acting muscle relaxant, a topical analgesic and may be an NMDA receptor antagonist.

Name: Terconazole
Information: Terconazole is a new, broad-spectrum, triazole antifungal agent which is primarily used to treat vaginal fungal infections.

Name: Melitracen hydrochloride
Information: Melitracen hydrochloride is a potential dopamine D1/2 receptor antagonist which has antidepressant properties.

Name: 6-Aminopenicillanic acid
Information: 6-Aminopenicillanic acid (6-APA) is the central component of penicillin β-lactam antibiotics which are generated by Penicillium. It is used as precursor for antibiotic compounds ampicillin and amoxicillin.

Name: Nisin
Information: Nisin is a ribosomally synthesized peptide that has broad-spectrum antibacterial activity, including activity against many bacteria that are food-spoilage pathogens.

Name: Phenazine methosulfate
Information: Phenazine methosulfate is widely used as an intermediate electron carrier for coupling the production of NADH or NADPH to the reduction of tetrazolium salts to coloured formazans.

Name: Valethamate Bromide
Information: Valethamate bromide is an alkylbenzene which is useful for facilitating cervical ripening, dilatation and thereby decreasing the duration of labor.

Name: Actarit
Information: Actarit is an orally active immunomodulator used in the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis.

Name: Tiamulin
Information: Tiamulin is a semisynthetic pleuromutilin antibiotic that binds to the ribosomal peptidyl transferase centre and inhibits protein synthesis.

Name: Difloxacin hydrochloride
Information: Difloxacin is a second-generation, synthetic fluoroquinolone antimicrobial antibiotic used in veterinary medicine.

Name: Bevantolol hydrochloride
Information: Bevantolol hydrochloride is a cardioselective, beta adrenoceptor antagonist, devoid of intrinsic β sympathomimetic activity and with weak membrane-stabilizing and local anesthetic properties.

Name: Benorylate
Information: Benorylate is the esterification product of paracetamol and acetylsalicylic acid with anti-inflammatory, analgesic and antipyretic properties.

Name: Clonixin
Information: Clonixin is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug with analgesic, antipyretic, and platelet-inhibitory actions.

Name: Fosfomycin Disodium
Information: Fosfomycin is a bactericidal, low-molecular weight, broad-spectrum antibiotic, with putative activity against several bacteria, including multidrug-resistant Gram-negative bacteria, by irreversibly inhibiting an early stage in cell wall synthesis.

Name: Thiocolchicoside
Information: Thiocolchicoside is a natural occuring glycoside originated from the flower seeds of superba gloriosa with anti-inflammatory and analgesic properties as well as pronounced convulsant activity. It is also an antagonist of GABAA receptor.

Name: Pipemidic acid
Information: Pipemidic acid is a pyridopyrimidine antibiotic derivative of piromidic acid with activity against gram-negative and some gram-positive bacteria.

Name: Granisetron

Name: Rifamycin sodium salt

Name: Milbemycin Oxime
Information: Milbemycin Oxime is a broad spectrum anti-parasitic drug that is active against worms (anthelmintic) and mites (miticide).

Name: Dinoprost tromethamine

Name: Revaprazan Hydrochloride

Name: Pixantrone Maleate

Name: Metadoxine
Information: Metadoxine, also known as pyridoxine-pyrrolidone carboxylate, is a drug used to treat chronic and acute alcohol intoxication.

Name: Daclatasvir Digydrochloride
Information: Daclatasvir is an orally available antiviral agent that inhibits the NS5A region of the hepatitis C virus (HCV) used for the treatment of chronic HCV genotype 1 and 3 infection.

Name: Trelagliptin succinate
Information: Trelagliptin succinate is a dipeptidyl peptidase IV (DPP-4) inhibitor which is used as a new long-acting drug for once-weekly treatment of type 2 diabetes mellitus (DM).

Name: Losartan
Information: Losartan D4 is the deuterium labeled Losartan. Losartan is an angiotensin II receptor antagonist, competing with the binding of angiotensin II to AT1 receptors with IC50 of 20 nM.

Name: Dabrafenib Mesylate
Information: Dabrafenib Mesylate is the mesylate salt form of dabrafenib, an orally bioavailable inhibitor of B-raf (BRAF) protein with IC50s of 0.8 nM, 3.2 nM and 5 nM for B-Raf (V600E), B-Raf (WT) and C-Raf, respectively.

Name: Mupirocin calcium

Name: Androsterone
Information: Androsterone is a steroid metabolite derived from sex hormones, which displays weak androgenic properties.

Name: EPZ005687
Information: EPZ005687 is a potent and selective inhibitor of EZH2 with Ki of 24 nM in a cell-free assay, 50-fold selectivity against EZH1 and 500-fold selectivity against 15 other protein methyltransferases.

Name: Binimetinib (MEK162, ARRY-162, ARRY-438162)
Information: Binimetinib (MEK162, ARRY-162, ARRY-438162) is a potent inhibitor of MEK1/2 with IC50 of 12 nM in a cell-free assay. Phase 3.

Name: LCL161
Information: LCL-161, a small molecule second mitochondrial activator of caspase (SMAC) mimetic, potently binds to and inhibits multiple IAPs (i.e. XIAP, c-IAP).

Name: GDC-0152
Information: GDC-0152 is a potent antagonist of XIAP-BIR3, ML-IAP-BIR3, cIAP1-BIR3 and cIAP2-BIR3 with Ki of 28 nM, 14 nM, 17 nM and 43 nM in cell-free assays, respectively less affinity shown to cIAP1-BIR2 and cIAP2-BIR2. Phase 1.

Name: Merestinib (LY2801653)
Information: LY2801653 is a type-II ATP competitive, slow-off inhibitor of MET tyrosine kinase with a dissociation constant (Ki) of 2 nM, a pharmacodynamic residence time (Koff) of 0.00132 min(-1) and t1/2 of 525 min.

Name: Birinapant
Information: Birinapant is a SMAC mimetic antagonist, mostly to cIAP1 with Kd of <1 nM in a cell-free assay, less potent to XIAP. Phase 2.

Name: VS-5584 (SB2343)
Information: VS-5584 (SB2343) is a potent and selective dual PI3K/mTOR inhibitor for mTOR, PI3Kα/β/δ/γ with IC50 of 3.4 nM and 2.6-21 nM, respectively. Phase 1.

Name: Embelin
Information: Embelin, a quinone isolated from the Japanese Ardisia herb, is an inhibitor of X-linked inhibitor of apoptosis (XIAP) with IC50 of 4.1 μM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Duvelisib (IPI-145, INK1197)
Information: Duvelisib (IPI-145, INK1197) is a novel and selective PI3K δ/γ inhibitor with Ki and IC50 of 23 pM/243 pM and 1 nM/50 nM in cell-free assays, highly selective for PI3K δ/γ than other protein kinases. Phase 3.

Name: AZD2461
Information: AZD2461 is a novel PARP inhibitor with low affinity for Pgp than Olaparib. Phase 1.

Name: RG-7112
Information: RG7112 (RO5045337) is an orally bioavailable and selective p53-MDM2 inhibitor with HTRF IC50 of 18 nM.

Name: XL388
Information: XL388 is a highly potent, selective, ATP-competitive inhibitor of mTOR with IC50 of 9.9 nM, 1000-fold selectivity over the closely related PI3K kinases.

Name: XL019
Information: XL019 is a potent and selective JAK2 inhibitor with IC50 of 2.2 nM, exhibiting >50-fold selectivity over JAK1, JAK3 and TYK2. Phase 1.

Name: PD168393
Information: PD168393 is an irreversible EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 0.70 nM, irreversibly alkylate Cys-773 inactive against insulin, PDGFR, FGFR and PKC.

Name: AZD3514
Information: AZD3514 is a potent and oral androgen receptor downregulator with Ki of 2.2 μM and has ability of reducing AR protein expression.Phase 1.

Name: CX-6258 HCl
Information: CX-6258 HCl is a potent, orally efficacious pan-Pim kinase inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM, 25 nM and 16 nM for Pim1, Pim2, and Pim3, respectively.

Name: Brefeldin A
Information: Brefeldin A is a lactone antibiotic and ATPase inhibitor for protein transport with IC50 of 0.2 μM in HCT 116 cells, induces cancer cell differentiation and apoptosis.

Name: Oprozomib (ONX 0912)
Information: Oprozomib (ONX 0912) is an orally bioavailable inhibitor for CT-L activity of 20S proteasome β5/LMP7 with IC50 of 36 nM/82 nM. Phase 1/2.

Name: LY2874455
Information: LY2874455 is a pan-FGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 2.8 nM, 2.6 nM, 6.4 nM, and 6 nM for FGFR1, FGFR2, FGFR3, and FGFR4, respectively, and also inhibits VEGFR2 activity with IC50 of 7 nM. Phase 1.

Name: Tezacaftor?(VX-661)
Information: Tezacaftor?(VX-661) is a second F508del CFTR corrector and is believed to help CFTR protein reach the cell surface. Phase 2.

Name: LY2090314
Information: LY2090314 is a potent GSK-3 inhibitor for GSK-3α/β with IC50 of 1.5 nM/0.9 nM may improve the efficacy of platinum-based chemotherapy regimens. LY2090314 is highly selective towards GSK3 as demonstrated by its fold selectivity relative to a large panel of kinases.

Name: Tepotinib (EMD 1214063)
Information: Tepotinib (EMD 1214063) is a potent and selective c-Met inhibitor with IC50 of 4 nM, >200-fold selective for c-Met than IRAK4, TrkA, Axl, IRAK1, and Mer. Phase 1.

Name: T0901317
Information: T0901317 is a potent and selective agonist for both LXR and FXR, with EC50 of ~50 nM and 5 μM, respectively.

Name: Cilengitide?trifluoroacetate
Information: Cilengitide is a potent integrin inhibitor for αvβ3 receptor and αvβ5 receptor with IC50 of 4.1 nM and 79 nM in cell-free assays, respectively ~10-fold selectivity against gpIIbIIIa. Phase 2.

Name: Ceritinib (LDK378)
Information: Ceritinib (LDK378) is potent inhibitor against ALK with IC50 of 0.2 nM in cell-free assays, shows 40- and 35-fold selectivity against IGF-1R and InsR, respectively. Phase 3.

Name: GSK923295
Information: GSK923295 is a first-in-class, specific allosteric inhibitor of CENP-E kinesin motor ATPase with Ki of 3.2 nM, and less potent to mutant I182 and T183. Phase 1.

Name: Zotarolimus(ABT-578)
Information: Zotarolimus (ABT-578) is an analogue of rapamycin, and inhibits FKBP-12 binding with IC50 of 2.8 nM.

Name: PF-3758309
Information: PF-03758309 is a potent, ATP-competitive, pyrrolopyrazole inhibitor of PAK4 with IC50 of 1.3 nM.

Name: HSP990 (NVP-HSP990)
Information: NVP-HSP990 (HSP990) is a novel, potent and selective HSP90 inhibitor for HSP90α/β with IC50 of 0.6 nM/0.8 nM.

Name: PD123319
Information: PD 123319 is a potent, selective AT2 angiotensin II receptor antagonist with IC50 of 34 nM.

Name: Taselisib (GDC 0032)
Information: Taselisib (GDC 0032) is a potent, next-generation β isoform-sparing PI3K inhibitor targeting PI3Kα/δ/γ with Ki of 0.29 nM/0.12 nM/0.97nM, >10 fold selective over PI3Kβ.

Name: AZD1208
Information: AZD1208 is a potent, and orally available Pim kinase inhibitor with IC50 of 0.4 nM, 5 nM, and 1.9 nM for Pim1, Pim2, and Pim3 in cell-free assays, respectively. Phase 1.

Name: NLG919
Information: NLG919 is a potent IDO (indoleamine-(2,3)-dioxygenase) pathway inhibitor with Ki/EC50 of 7 nM/75 nM in cell-free assays. Phase 1.

Name: Zebularine
Information: Zebularine is a DNA methylation inhibitor that forms a covalent complex with DNA methyltransferases, also inhibits cytidinedeaminase with Ki of 2 μM in a cell-free assay.

Name: NU6027
Information: NU6027 is a potent ATR/CDK inhibitor, inhibits CDK1/2, ATR and DNA-PK with Ki of 2.5 μM/1.3 μM, 0.4 μM and 2.2 μM, enter cells more readily than the 6-aminopurine-based inhibitors.

Name: AMG-517
Information: AMG 517 is a potent and selective TRPV1 antagonist, and antagonizes capsaicin, proton, and heat activation of TRPV1 with IC50 of 0.76 nM, 0.62 nM and 1.3 nM， respectively.

Name: Go6976
Information: Go6976 is a potent PKC inhibitor with IC50 of 7.9 nM, 2.3 nM, and 6.2 nM for PKC (Rat brain), PKCα, and PKCβ1, respectively. Also a potent inhibitor of JAK2 and Flt3.

Name: MLN2480
Information: MLN2480 is an oral, selective pan-Raf kinase inhibitor in chinical trials.

Name: XL888
Information: XL888 is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of HSP90 with IC50 of 24 nM. Phase 1.

Name: KPT-185
Information: KPT-185 is a selective CRM1 inhibitor that induces growth inhibition and apoptosis in a panel of NHL cell lines with a median IC50 ~25 nM.

Name: Tazemetostat (EPZ-6438)
Information: Tazemetostat (EPZ-6438) is a potent, and selective EZH2 inhibitor with Ki and IC50 of 2.5 nM and 11 nM in cell-free assays, exhibiting a 35-fold selectivity versus EZH1 and >4,500-fold selectivity relative to 14 other HMTs.

Name: P5091 (P005091)
Information: P5091(P005091) is a selective and potent inhibitor of ubiquitin-specific protease 7 (USP7) with EC50 of 4.2 μM and the closely related USP47.

Name: BMS-833923
Information: BMS-833923 is an orally bioavailable Smoothened antagonist. Phase 2.

Name: LGK-974
Information: LGK-974 is a potent and specific PORCN inhibitor, and inhibits Wnt signaling with IC50 of 0.4 nM in TM3 cells. Phase 1.

Name: BMS-911543
Information: BMS-911543 is a potent and selective inhibitor of JAK2 with IC50 of 1.1?nM, ~350-, 75- and 65-fold selective to JAK1, JAK3 and TYK2, respectively. Phase 1/2.

Name: AZD1080
Information: AZD1080 is a selective, orally active, brain permeable GSK3 inhibitor, inhibits human GSK3α and GSK3β with Ki of 6.9 nM and 31 nM, respectively, shows >14-fold selectivity against CDK2, CDK5, CDK1 and Erk2.

Name: Batimastat (BB-94)
Information: Batimastat (BB-94) is a potent, broad spectrum matrix metalloprotease (MMP) inhibitor for MMP-1, MMP-2, MMP-9, MMP-7 and MMP-3 with IC50 of 3 nM, 4 nM, 4 nM, 6 nM and 20 nM, respectively. Also inhibits the activitity of other metalloproteases, such as ADAM17.

Name: Marimastat (BB-2516)
Information: Marimastat (BB-2516) is a broad spectrum matrix metalloprotease (MMP) inhibitor for MMP-9, MMP-1, MMP-2, MMP-14 and MMP-7 with IC50 of 3 nM, 5 nM, 6 nM, 9 nM and 13 nM, respectively. Phase 3.

Name: Ilomastat (GM6001, Galardin)
Information: Ilomastat (GM6001, Galardin) is a broad spectrum matrix metalloprotease (MMP) inhibitor for MMP-1, MMP-2, MMP-3, MMP-7, MMP-8, MMP-9, MMP-12, MMP-14, and MMP-26 with Ki of 0.4 nM, 0.5 nM, 27 nM, 3.7 nM, 0.1 nM, 0.2 nM, 3.6 nM, 13.4 nM, 0.36 nM, respectively.

Name: abemaciclib (LY2835219)
Information: abemaciclib (LY2835219) is a potent and selective inhibitor of CDK4 and CDK6 with IC50 of 2 nM and 10 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. Phase 3.

Name: Glasdegib (PF-04449913)
Information: Glasdegib (PF-04449913) is a potent, and orally bioavailable Smoothened (Smo) inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM. Phase 2.

Name: Motolimod (VTX-2337)
Information: Motolimod (VTX-2337) is a selective and potent Toll-like receptor (TLR) 8 agonist with EC50 of 100 nM, > 50-fold selectivity over TLR7. Phase 2.

Name: Crenigacestat (LY3039478)
Information: Crenigacestat (LY3039478) is an oral Notch inhibitor with an IC50 of 0.41 nM.

Name: RO5126766 (CH5126766)
Information: RO5126766 (CH5126766) is a dual RAF/MEK inhibitor with IC50 of 8.2 nM,19 nM, 56 nM, and 160 nM for BRAF V600E, BRAF, CRAF, and MEK1, respectively. Phase 1.

Name: GKT137831
Information: GKT137831 is a potent, dual NADPH oxidase NOX1/NOX4 inhibitor with Ki of 110 nM and 140 nM, respectivelyl ~10-fold selectivity towards NOX1, 4 and 5 over NOX2, does not inhibit XO or scavange ROS/RNS.

Name: Spebrutinib (CC-292, AVL-292)
Information: Spebrutinib (CC-292, AVL-292) is a covalent, orally active, and highly selective BTK inhibitor with IC50 of <0.5 nM, displaying at least 1400-fold selectivity over the other kinases assayed. Phase 1.

Name: Opaganib (ABC294640)
Information: Opaganib (ABC294640) is an orally bioavailable and selective sphingosine kinase-2 (SphK2) inhibitor with IC50 of approximately 60 μM. Phase 1/2.

Name: BAF312 (Siponimod)
Information: BAF312 (Siponimod) is a next-generation S1P receptor modulator, selective for S1P1 and S1P5 receptors with EC50 of 0.39 nM and 0.98 nM, exhibits >1000-fold selectivity over S1P2, S1P3 and S1P4 receptors. Phase 3.

Name: I-BET-762
Information: I-BET-762 is an inhibitor for BET proteins with IC50 of ~35 nM in a cell-free assay, suppresses the production of proinflammatory proteins by macrophages and blocks acute inflammation, highly selective over other bromodomain-containing proteins.

Name: PF-04620110
Information: PF-04620110 is an orally active, selective and potent diglyceride acyltransferase-1 (DGAT1) inhibitor with IC50 of 19 nM.

Name: GZD824 Dimesylate
Information: GZD824 Dimesylate is a novel orally bioavailable Bcr-Abl inhibitor for Bcr-Abl(WT) and Bcr-Abl(T315I) with IC50 of 0.34 nM and 0.68 nM, respectively.

Name: Fosbretabulin (Combretastatin A4 Phosphate (CA4P)) Disodium
Information: Fosbretabulin (Combretastatin A4 Phosphate (CA4P)) Disodium is the water-soluble prodrug of Combretastatin A4 (CA4), which is a microtubule-targeting agent that binds β-tubulin with Kd of 0.4 μM in a cell-free assay. Fosbretabulin Disodium inhibits the polymerization of tubulin with IC50 of 2.4 μM, and also disrupts tumor vasculature. Phase 3.

Name: Idasanutlin (RG-7388)
Information: Idasanutlin (RG-7388) is a potent and selective p53-MDM2 inhibitor with IC50 of 6 nM showing improved in vitro binding as well as cellular potency/selectivity.

Name: PF-04418948
Information: PF-04418948 is a potent and selective prostaglandin EP? receptor antagonist with IC50 of 16 nM. Phase 1.

Name: Losmapimod (GW856553X)
Information: Losmapimod (GW856553X) is a selective, potent, and orally active p38 MAPK inhibitor with pKi of 8.1 and 7.6 for p38α and p38β, respectively. Phase 3.

Name: Alvelestat (AZD9668)
Information: Alvelestat (AZD9668) is an oral, highly selective inhibitor of neutrophil elastase (NE) with IC50 and Ki of 12 nM and 9.4 nM, at least 600-fold more selective over other serine proteases. Phase 2.

Name: GS-9620
Information: GS-9620 is a potent and selective orally active small molecule agonist of Toll-like receptor 7.

Name: Erastin
Information: Erastin is a ferroptosis activator by acting on mitochondrial VDAC, exhibiting selectivity for tumor cells bearing oncogenic RAS.

Name: Selinexor (KPT-330)
Information: Selinexor (KPT-330) is an orally bioavailable selective CRM1 inhibitor. Phase 2.

Name: AZD2858
Information: AZD2858 is a selective GSK-3 inhibitor with an IC50 of 68 nM, activating Wnt signaling, increases bone mass in rats.

Name: NMS-P937 (NMS1286937)
Information: NMS-P937 (NMS1286937) is an orally available, selective Polo-like Kinase 1 (PLK1) inhibitor with IC50 of 2 nM, 5000-fold selectivity over PLK2/PLK3. Phase 1.

Name: Beta-Lapachone
Information: Beta-Lapachone is a selective DNA topoisomerase I inhibitor, exhibiting no inhibitory activities against DNA topoisomerase II or ligase. Phase 2.

Name: Vidofludimus
Information: Vidofludimus is an orally active and potent dihydroorotate dehydrogenase (DHODH) inhibitor with IC50 of 134 nM for human DHODH. Phase 2.

Name: AZD1981
Information: AZD1981 is a potent, selective CRTh2 (DP2) receptor antagonist with IC50 of 4 nM, showing >1000-fold selectivity over more than 340 other enzymes and receptors, including DP1. Phase 2.

Name: PD173955
Information: PD173955 is a potent Bcr-Abl inhibitor with IC50 of 1-2 nM, also inhibiting Src activity with IC50 of 22 nM.

Name: SC75741
Information: SC75741 is a potent NF-κB inhibitor with EC50 of 200 nM.

Name: Edoxaban
Information: Edoxaban is a selective factor Xa inhibitor with Ki of 0.561 nM, >10 000-fold selectivity over thrombin and FIXa, and is also an orally bioavailable anticoagulant drug.

Name: NMS-E973
Information: NMS-E973 is a potent and selective Hsp90 inhibitor with DC50 of <10 nM for Hsp90 binding, no activiy against a panel of 52 diverse protein kinases.

Name: Rociletinib (CO-1686, AVL-301)
Information: Rociletinib (CO-1686, AVL-301) is an irreversible, mutant-selective EGFR inhibitor with Ki of 21.5 nM and 303.3 nM for EGFRL858R/T790M and EGFRWT in cell-free assays, respectively. Phase 2.

Name: TAK-632
Information: TAK-632 is a potent pan-Raf inhibitor with IC50 of 8.3 nM and 1.4 nM for B-Raf(wt) and C-Raf in cell-free assays, respectively, showing less or no inhibition against other tested kinases.

Name: RG2833 (RGFP109)
Information: RG2833 (RGFP109) is a brain-penetrant HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 60 nM and 50 nM for HDAC1 and HDAC3 in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Apabetalone (RVX-208)
Information: Apabetalone (RVX-208) is a potent BET bromodomain inhibitor with IC50 of 0.510 μM for BD2 in a cell-free assay, about 170-fold selectivity over BD1. Phase 2.

Name: Osimertinib (AZD9291)
Information: Osimertinib (AZD9291) is an oral, irreversible, and mutant-selective EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 12.92, 11.44 and 493.8 nM for Exon 19 deletion EGFR, L858R/T790M EGFR, and WT EGFR in LoVo cells, respectively. Phase 3.

Name: Rilpivirine
Information: Rilpivirine is a non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NNRTI), and used to treat HIV-1 infection.

Name: CPI-203
Information: CPI-203 is a potent BET bromodomain inhibitor with IC50 of 37 nM for BRD4.

Name: BAY 87-2243
Information: BAY 87-2243 is a potent and selective hypoxia-inducible factor-1 (HIF-1) inhibitor. Phase 1.

Name: CHF 5074
Information: CHF5074 is a gamma-secretase modulator that reduces Aβ42 and Aβ40 secretion. The IC50s of CHF5074 for inhibition of COX-1 and COX-2 is above 100 μmol/L.

Name: Tasisulam
Information: Tasisulam is an antitumor agent and an apoptosis inducer via the intrinsic pathway. Phase 3.

Name: IOWH032
Information: IOWH032 is a synthetic CFTR inhibitor with IC50 of 1.01 μM in CHO-CFTR cell based assays. Phase 2.

Name: CW069
Information: CW069 is an allosteric, and selective inhibitor of microtubule motor protein HSET with IC50 of 75 μM, significant selectivity over KSP.

Name: AZD3965
Information: AZD3965 is a potent, selective and orally available monocarboxylate transporter 1 (MCT1) inhibitor with a binding affinity of 1.6 nM, 6-fold selective over MCT2. Phase 1.

Name: ARQ 621
Information: ARQ 621 is an allosteric, and selective Eg5 mitotic motor protein inhibitor. Phase 1.

Name: PF-562271 HCl
Information: PF-562271 HCl is the hydrochloride salt of PF-562271, which is a potent, ATP-competitive, reversible inhibitor of FAK with IC50 of 1.5 nM, ~10-fold less potent for Pyk2 than FAK and >100-fold selectivity against other protein kinases, except for some CDKs. Phase 1.

Name: Poziotinib (HM781-36B)
Information: Poziotinib (HM781-36B) is an irreversible pan-HER inhibitor with IC50 of 3.2 nM, 5.3 nM and 23.5 nM for HER1, HER2, and HER4, respectively. Phase 2.

Name: OTX015
Information: OTX015 is a potent BET bromodomain inhibitor with EC50 ranging from 10 to 19 nM for BRD2, BRD3, and BRD4 in cell-free assays. Phase 1.

Name: 4EGI-1
Information: 4EGI-1 is a competitive eIF4E/eIF4G interaction inhibitor by binding to eIF4E with KD of 25 μM.

Name: Aprotinin
Information: Aprotinin is a small protein serine protease inhibitor (Kd=0.06 pM for bovine β-trypsin), used to reduce perioperative blood loss and transfusion.

Name: E-64
Information: E-64 is an irreversible and selective cysteine protease inhibitor, and also inhibits papain, calpain, and cathepsins B and H, but not serine proteases or aspartic proteases. The IC50 for papain is 9 nM.

Name: Pepstatin A
Information: Pepstatin A is a potent aspartic protease inhibitor, and also inhibits HIV replication.

Name: Aloxistatin
Information: Aloxistatin is an irreversible and membrane-permeable cysteine protease inhibitor with blood platelet aggregation inhibiting activity.

Name: Calpeptin
Information: Calpeptin is a potent, cell-permeable calpain inhibitor with ID50 of 52 nM, 34 nM, 138 nM, and 40 nM for Calpain I (porcine erythrocytes), Calpain II (porcine kidney), Papainb, and Calpain I (human platelets), respectively.

Name: Sorafenib
Information: Sorafenib is a multikinase inhibitor of Raf-1, B-Raf and VEGFR-2 with IC50 of 6 nM, 22 nM and 90 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Ascomycin (FK520)
Information: Ascomycin (FK520), an FK-506 analog, is a neutral macrolide immunosuppressant, which prevents rejection after an organ transplant. Phase 3.

Name: Puromycin 2HCl
Information: Puromycin 2HCl is an aminonucleoside antibiotic, which acts as a protein synthesis inhibitor.

Name: AR-A014418
Information: AR-A014418 is an ATP-competitive, and selective GSK3β inhibitor with IC50 and Ki of 104 nM and 38 nM in cell-free assays, without significant inhibition on 26 other kinases tested.

Name: Ribociclib (LEE011)
Information: Ribociclib (LEE011) is an orally available, and highly specific CDK4/6 inhibitor. Phase 3.

Name: E3330
Information: E3330 is a potent and selective APE1(Ref-1) inhibitor, which suppressed NF-kappa B DNA-binding activity.

Name: Osilodrostat (LCI699)
Information: LCI699(Osilodrostat) is a potent inhibitor of 11β-hydroxylase, an enzyme catalyzing the final step of cortisol synthesis.

Name: VER-49009
Information: VER-49009 is a potent HSP90 inhibitor with IC50 of 47 nM for HSP90β.

Name: FTI 277 HCl
Information: FTI 277 HCl is the methyl ester of FTI 277, which is a potent and selective farnesyltransferase (FTase) inhibitor with IC50 of 500 pM, about 100-fold selectivity over the closely related GGTase I.

Name: GGTI 298 TFA salt
Information: GGTI 298 is a geranylgeranyltransferase I inhibitor with ability to arrest human tumor cells in the G1 phase of the cell cycle and induce apoptosis.

Name: Triapine
Information: Triapine is a potent ribonucleotide reductase inhibitor with broad spectrum antitumor activity by inhibiting DNA synthesis. Phase 2.

Name: EHT 1864 2HCl
Information: EHT 1864 2HCl is a potent Rac family GTPase inhibitor with Kd of 40 nM, 50 nM, 60 nM and 250 nM for Rac1, Rac1b, Rac2 and Rac3, respectively.

Name: MPI-0479605
Information: MPI-0479605 is an ATP competitive and selective inhibitor of mitotic kinase Mps1 with IC50 of 1.8 nM, >40-fold selectivity over other kinases.

Name: Uprosertib (GSK2141795)
Information: Uprosertib (GSK2141795) is a selective, ATP-competitive, and orally bioavailable Akt inhibitor with IC50 of 180 nM, 328 nM, and 38 nM for Akt 1, 2 and 3, respectively. Phase 2.

Name: (S)-crizotinib
Information: (S)-crizotinib, the (S)-enantiomer of crizotinib, is a potent MTH1 (NUDT1) inhibitor with IC50 of 72 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Trelagliptin
Information: Trelagliptin is a highly selective, long-acting DPP-4 inhibitor. Phase 3.

Name: VGX-1027
Information: VGX-1027 is an orally active immunomodulator. Phase 1.

Name: AZD7545
Information: AZD7545 is a potent PDHK inhibitor with IC50 of 36.8 nM and 6.4 nM for PDHK1 and PDHK2, respectively. It failed to inhibit PDHK4 at higher concentrations(>10 nM), AZD7545 stimulates PDHK4 activity.

Name: Voreloxin (SNS-595) hydrochloride
Information: Voreloxin is a potent Topoisomerase II inhibitor with broad-spectrum anti-tumor activity. Phase 2.

Name: Darapladib (SB-480848)
Information: Darapladib (SB-480848) is a reversible lipoprotein-associated phospholipase A2 (Lp-PLA2) inhibitor with IC50 of 0.25 nM. Phase 3.

Name: Afuresertib (GSK2110183)
Information: Afuresertib (GSK2110183) is a potent, orally bioavailable Akt inhibitor with Ki of 0.08 nM, 2 nM, and 2.6 nM for Akt1, Akt2, and Akt3, respectively. Phase 2.

Name: Entospletinib (GS-9973)
Information: Entospletinib (GS-9973) is an orally bioavailable, selective Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 7.7 nM in a cell-free assay and showed 13- to >1000-fold cellular selectivity for Syk over other kinases(including Jak2, ckit, Flt3, Ret, KDR) as assessed by target protein phosphorylation or functional response.

Name: Vactosertib ?(TEW-7197)
Information: Vactosertib ?(TEW-7197) is a highly potent, selective, and orally bioavailable TGF-β receptor ALK4/ALK5 inhibitor with IC50 of 13 nM and 11 nM, respectively. Phase 1.

Name: Lorlatinib?(PF-6463922)
Information: PF-06463922 is a potent, dual ALK/ROS1 inhibitor with Ki of <0.02 nM, <0.07 nM, and 0.7 nM for ROS1, ALK (WT), and ALK (L1196M), respectively. Phase 1.

Name: LB-100
Information: LB-100 is a water soluble protein phosphatase 2A (PP2A) inhibitor with IC50s of 0.85 μM and 3.87 μM in BxPc-3 and Panc-1 cells.

Name: SB273005
Information: SB273005 is a potent integrin inhibitor with Ki of 1.2 nM and 0.3 nM for αvβ3 receptor and αvβ5 receptor, respectively.

Name: Decernotinib (VX-509)
Information: Decernotinib (VX-509) is a potent and selective JAK3 inhibitor with Ki of 2.5 nM, >4-fold selectivity over JAK1, JAK2, and TYK2, respectively. Phase 2/3.

Name: Pritelivir (BAY 57-1293)
Information: Pritelivir (BAY 57-1293) is a potent helicase primase inhibitor, exhibiting antiviral effect on herpes simplex virus (HSV) with IC50 of 20 nM for both HSV-1 and HSV-2.

Name: XL413 (BMS-863233)
Information: XL413 (BMS-863233) is a potent and selective cell division cycle 7 homolog (CDC7) kinase inhibitor with IC50 of 3.4 nM, showing 63-, 12- and 35-fold selectivity over CK2, Pim-1 and pMCM2, respectively. Phase 1/2.

Name: Rilmenidine Phosphate
Information: Rilmenidine Phosphate is a selective I(1) imidazoline receptor agonist, used for the treatment of hypertension.

Name: THZ1 2HCl
Information: THZ1 is a covalent CDK7 inhibitor which has the unprecedented ability to target a remote cysteine residue located outside of the canonical kinase domain, providing an unanticipated means of achieving selectivity for CDK7.

Name: Erythromycin Cyclocarbonate
Information: Erythromycin Cyclocarbonate, derivative of Erythromycin, inhibits protein synthesis of bacteria by binding to the 50S ribosome.

Name: GDC-0623
Information: GDC-0623 is a potent and ATP-uncompetitive MEK1 inhibitor with Ki of 0.13 nM. Phase 1.

Name: 4SC-202
Information: 4SC-202 is a selective class I HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 1.20 μM, 1.12 μM, and 0.57 μM for HDAC1, HDAC2, and HDAC3, respectively. Also displays inhibitory activity against Lysine specific demethylase 1 (LSD1). Phase 1.

Name: CL-387785 (EKI-785)
Information: CL-387785 (EKI-785) is an irreversible, and selective EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 370 pM.

Name: Darolutamide (ODM-201)
Information: Darolutamide (ODM-201) is a novel androgen receptor (AR) antagonist that blocks AR nuclear translocation with Ki of 11 nM. Phase 3.

Name: AT13148
Information: AT13148 is an oral, ATP-competitive, multi-AGC kinase inhibitor with IC50 of 38 nM/402 nM/50 nM, 8 nM, 3 nM, and 6 nM/4 nM for Akt1/2/3, p70S6K, PKA, and ROCKI/II, respectively. Phase 1.

Name: SAR125844
Information: SAR125844 is a potent intravenously active and highly selective MET kinase inhibitor, displaying nanomolar activity against the wild-type kinase (IC50 value of 4.2 nmol/L) and H1094Y, Y1235D, M1250T, L1195V, and D1228H kinase domain mutants (IC50 values of 0.22, 1.7, 6.5, 65, and 81 nmol/L, respectively).

Name: Ledipasvir (GS5885)
Information: Ledipasvir (GS5885) is a HCV NS5A polymerase inhibitor, used for the treatment of hepatitis C virus infection.

Name: Anacardic Acid
Information: Anacardic Acid is a potent inhibitor of p300 and p300/CBP-associated factor histone acetyltranferases, which also has antibacterial activity, antimicrobial activity, prostaglandin synthase inhibition, and tyrosinase and lipoxygenase inhibition.

Name: SB-334867
Information: SB-334867 is a selective orexin-1 (OX1) receptor antagonist.

Name: N6022
Information: N6022 is a selective, and reversible inhibitor of S-nitrosoglutathione reductase (GSNOR) with IC50 of 8 nM and Ki of 2.5 nM. Phase 1/2.

Name: Abscisic Acid (Dormin）
Information: Abscisic Acid is a plant hormone, which is involved in many plant developmental processes, modulates ion homeostasis and metabolism, and inhibits germination and seedling growth.

Name: Filgotinib (GLPG0634)
Information: Filgotinib (GLPG0634) is a selective JAK1 inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM, 28 nM, 810 nM, and 116 nM for JAK1, JAK2, JAK3, and TYK2, respectively. Phase 2.

Name: UM171
Information: UM171 is a potent agonist of human hematopoietic stem cell renewal, independently of AhR suppression.

Name: PX-478 2HCl
Information: PX-478 2HCl is an orally active, and selective hypoxia-inducible factor-1α (HIF-1α) inhibitor. Phase 1.

Name: CPI-169
Information: CPI-169 is a potent, and selective EZH2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.24 nM, 0.51 nM, and 6.1 nM for EZH2 WT, EZH2 Y641N, and EZH1, respectively.

Name: Tasquinimod
Information: Tasquinimod is an orally active antiangiogenic agent by allosterically inhibiting HDAC4 signalling. Phase 3.

Name: MI-2 (Menin-MLL Inhibitor)
Information: MI-2 (Menin-MLL Inhibitor) is a potent menin-MLL interaction inhibitor with IC50 of 446 nM.

Name: SD-208
Information: SD-208 is a selective TGF-βRI (ALK5) inhibitor with IC50 of 48 nM, >100-fold selectivity over TGF-βRII.

Name: Niraparib (MK-4827) tosylate
Information: Niraparib (MK-4827) tosylate is a selective inhibitor of PARP1/PARP2 with IC50 of 3.8 nM/2.1 nM.

Name: Lomitapide Mesylate
Information: Lomitapide Mesylate is a potent microsomal triglyceride transfer protein (MTP) inhibitor, used in the treatment of familial hypercholesterolemia.

Name: Cerdulatinib (PRT062070, PRT2070)
Information: Cerdulatinib (PRT-062070) is an oral active, multi-targeted tyrosine kinase inhibitor with IC50 of 12 nM/6 nM/8 nM/0.5 nM and 32 nM for JAK1/JAK2/JAK3/TYK2 and Syk, respectively. Also inhibits 19 other tested kinases with IC50 less than 200 nM.

Name: Lomitapide
Information: Lomitapide is a potent microsomal triglyceride transfer protein (MTP) inhibitor, used in the treatment of familial hypercholesterolemia.

Name: SU9516
Information: SU 9516 is a 3-substituted indolinone CDK inhibitor with IC50 of 22 nM, 40 nM, and 200 nM for CDK2, CDK1, and CDK4, respectively.

Name: DTP3
Information: DTP3 is a selective GADD45β/MKK7 inhibitor, which inhibits cancer-selective NF-κB survival pathway.

Name: 3PO
Information: 3PO is a small-molecule inhibitor of PFKFB3 with an IC50 of 22.9 μM for recombinant human PFKFB3 protein and does not inhibit PFK-1 activity. It suppresses glucose uptake, and decreases the intracellular concentration of Fru-2,6-BP, lactate, ATP, NAD+, and NADH.

Name: Pilaralisib (XL147)
Information: Pilaralisib (XL147) is a selective and reversible class I PI3K inhibitor for PI3Kα/δ/γ with IC50 of 39 nM/36 nM/23 nM in cell-free assays, less potent to PI3Kβ. Phase 1/2.

Name: Voxtalisib (XL765, SAR245409)
Information: Voxtalisib (SAR245409, XL765) is a dual inhibitor of mTOR/PI3K, mostly for p110γ with IC50 of 9 nM also inhibits DNA-PK and mTOR. Phase 1/2.

Name: OTS964
Information: OTS964 is a potent TOPK inhibitor with high affinity and selectivity and IC50 value is 28 nM.

Name: MI-773 (SAR405838)
Information: MI-773 (SAR405838) is an orally available MDM2 antagonist with Ki of 0.88 nM. Phase 1.

Name: Peficitinib (ASP015K, JNJ-54781532)
Information: Peficitinib (ASP015K, JNJ-54781532) is an orally bioavailable JAK inhibitor. Phase 3.

Name: SB225002
Information: SB225002 is a potent, and selective CXCR2 antagonist with IC50 of 22 nM for inhibiting interleukin IL-8 binding to CXCR2, > 150-fold selectivity over the other 7-TMRs tested.

Name: OTS514 hydrochloride
Information: OTS514 is a highly potent TOPK(T-LAK cell-originated protein kinase) inhibitor with an IC50 value of 2.6 nM.

Name: PND-1186 (VS-4718)
Information: PND-1186 (VS-4718) is a reversible and selective FAK inhibitor with IC50 of 1.5 nM. Phase 1.

Name: Defactinib (VS-6063, PF-04554878)
Information: Defactinib (VS-6063, PF-04554878) is a selective, and orally active FAK inhibitor. Phase 2.

Name: CB-839
Information: CB-839 is a potent, selective, and orally bioavailable glutaminase inhibitor with IC50 of 24 nM for recombinant human GAC. Phase 1.

Name: CPI-360
Information: CPI-360 is a potent, selective,and SAM-competitive EZH1 inhibitor with IC50 of 102.3 nM, >100-fold selectivity over other methyltransferases.

Name: Obeticholic Acid
Information: Obeticholic Acid is a potent and selective farnesoid X receptor (FXR) agonist with EC50 of 99 nM. Phase 3.

Name: Ruboxistaurin (LY333531 HCl)
Information: LY333531 is a β-specific protein kinase C inhibitor. It competitively and reversibly inhibits PKCβ1 and PKCβ2 with IC50 values of 4.7 and 5.9 nM respectively.

Name: CH5183284 (Debio-1347)
Information: CH5183284 is a selective and orally available FGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 9.3 nM, 7.6 nM, 22 nM, and 290 nM for FGFR1, FGFR2, FGFR3, and FGFR4, respectively. Phase 1.

Name: SU5402
Information: SU5402 is a potent multi-targeted receptor tyrosine kinase inhibitor with IC50 of 20 nM, 30 nM, and 510 nM for VEGFR2, FGFR1, and PDGF-Rβ, respectively.

Name: Picropodophyllin (PPP)
Information: Picropodophyllin (PPP) is a IGF-1R inhibitor with IC50 of 1 nM. It displays selectivity for IGF-1R and does not coinhibit tyrosine phosphorylation the IR, or of a selected panel of receptors less related to IGF-IR(FGF-R, PDGF-R, OR EGF-R).

Name: Omaveloxolone (RTA-408)
Information: Omaveloxolone (RTA-408) is a synthetic triterpenoid that activates the cytoprotective transcription factor Nrf2 and inhibits NF-κB signaling. Phase 2.

Name: Savolitinib(AZD6094, HMPL-504)
Information: Savolitinib (volitinib, AZD6094, HMPL-504) is a novel, potent, and selective MET inhibitor currently in clinical development in various indications, including PRCC. The IC50 values of this compound for c-Met and p-Met are 5 nM and 3 nM, respectively. It shows exquisite selectivity for c-Met over 274 kinase.

Name: Sacubitril/valsartan (LCZ696)
Information: Sacubitril/valsartan (LCZ696), consisting of valsartan and sacubitril in 1:1 molar ratio, is an orally bioavailable, dual-acting angiotensin receptor-neprilysin inhibitor (ARNi) for hypertension and heart failure. Phase 3.

Name: Salirasib
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is fat, and can be dissolved in any proportion in DMSO
Information: Salirasib is a potent competitive prenylated protein methyltransferase (PPMTase) inhibitor with Ki of 2.6 μM, which inhibits Ras methylation. Phase 2.

Name: ML141
Information: ML141 (CID-2950007), is demonstrated to be a potent, selective and reversible non-competitive inhibitor of Cdc42 GTPase suitable for in vitro assays, with IC50 of 200 nM and selectivity against other members of the Rho family of GTPases (Rac1, Rab2, Rab7).

Name: PS-1145
Information: PS-1145 is a specific IKK inhibitor with IC50 of 88 nM.

Name: AZD6738
Information: AZD6738 is an orally active, and selective ATR kinase inhibitor with IC50 of 1 nM. Phase 1/2.

Name: AZD8186
Information: AZD8186 is a potent and selective inhibitor of PI3Kβ and PI3Kδ with IC50 of 4 nM and 12 nM, respectively. Phase 1.

Name: LY2584702
Information: LY2584702 is a selective, ATP-competitive p70S6K inhibitor with IC50 of 4 nM. Phase 1.

Name: LY2584702 Tosylate
Information: LY2584702 Tosylate is a selective, ATP-competitive <B>p70S6K inhibitor with IC50 of 4 nM. Phase 1.

Name: Verdinexor (KPT-335)
Information: Verdinexor (KPT-335) is an orally bioavailable, selective XPO1/CRM1 inhibitor.

Name: Monomethyl auristatin E (MMAE)
Information: Monomethyl auristatin E (MMAE) is a synthetic antineoplastic agent, which is linked to a monoclonal antibody (MAB). It is also a microtubule-disrupting agent .

Name: PRIMA-1
Information: PRIMA-1 is a mutant p53 reactivator. It induces apoptosis and inhibits growth of human tumors with mutant p53.

Name: APR-246 (PRIMA-1MET)
Information: APR-246, also known as PRIMA-1MET, is a small organic molecule that has been shown to restore tumour-suppressor function primarily to mutant p53 and also to induce cell death in various cancer types.

Name: BLZ945
Information: BLZ945 is an orally active, potent and selective CSF-1R inhibitor with IC50 of 1 nM, >1000-fold selective against its closest receptor tyrosine kinase homologs.

Name: NU1025
Information: NU1025 is a potent PARP inhibitor with IC50 of 400 nM.

Name: AZD3839
Information: AZD3839 is a potent and selective BACE1 inhibitor with Ki of 26.1 nM, about 14-fold selectivity over BACE2. Phase 1.

Name: LFM-A13
Information: LFM-A13 is a specific Bruton's tyrosine kinase (BTK) inhibitor with IC50 of 2.5 μM, >100-fold selectivity over other protein kinases including JAK1, JAK2, HCK, EGFR,and IRK.

Name: PRT-060318 2HCl
Information: PRT-060318 (PRT318) is a novel selective inhibitor of the Syk tyrosine kinase with an IC50 of 4 nM, as an approach to HIT treatment.

Name: SB239063
Information: SB239063 is a potent and selective p38 MAPKα/β inhibitor with IC50 of 44 nM, showing no activity against the γ- and δ-kinase isoforms.

Name: EPZ015666(GSK3235025)
Information: EPZ015666(GSK3235025) is a potent, selective and orally bioavailable PRMT5 inhibitor with Ki of 5 nM, >20,000-fold selectivity over other PMTs.

Name: KNK437
Information: KNK437 is a pan-HSP inhibitor, which inhibits the synthesis of inducible HSPs, including HSP105, HSP72, and HSP40.

Name: Gilteritinib (ASP2215)
Information: Gilteritinib(ASP2215) is a small-molecule FLT3/AXL inhibitor with IC50 values of 0.29 nM and 0.73 nM for FLT3 and AXL, respectively. It inhibits FLT3 at an IC50 value that was approximately 800-fold more potent than the concentration required to inhibit c-KIT (230 nM).

Name: Indoximod (NLG-8189）
Information: Indoximod (NLG-8189), a methylated tryptophan, acts as an IDO (indoleamine-(2,3)-dioxygenase) pathway inhibitor, and reverses IDO-mediated immune suppression. Phase 2.

Name: 6-Thio-dG
Information: 6-thio-dG is a nucleoside analog and telomerase substrate.

Name: TRx0237 (LMTX) mesylate
Information: TRx 0237 (LMTX?) mesylate is a second-generation tau protein aggregation inhibitor for the treatment of Alzheimer's disease (AD) and frontotemporal dementia.

Name: Dovitinib (TKI258) Lactate
Information: Dovitinib (TKI258) Lactate is the Lactate of Dovitinib, which is a multitargeted RTK inhibitor, mostly for class III (FLT3/c-Kit) with IC50 of 1 nM/2 nM, also potent to class IV (FGFR1/3) and class V (VEGFR1-4) RTKs with IC50 of 8-13 nM, less potent to InsR, EGFR, c-Met, EphA2, Tie2, IGFR1 and HER2. Phase 4.

Name: Cabotegravir (GSK744, GSK1265744)
Information: Cabotegravir (GSK744, GSK1265744) is a long-acting HIV integrase inhibitor against a broad range of HIV subtypes, and inhibits the HIV-1 integrase catalyzed strand transfer reaction with IC50 of 3.0 nM. Phase 2.

Name: Elacridar (GF120918)
Information: Elacridar (GF120918) is a potent P-gp (MDR-1) and BCRP inhibitor.

Name: Emricasan
Information: Emricasan is a potent irreversible pan-caspase inhibitor.

Name: Coelenterazine
Information: Coelenterazine is a luminescent enzyme substrate, used for monitoring reporter genes in BRET, ELISA and HTS techniques.

Name: Sunitinib
Information: Sunitinib is a multi-targeted RTK inhibitor targeting VEGFR2 (Flk-1) and PDGFRβ with IC50 of 80 nM and 2 nM, and also inhibits c-Kit.

Name: Dasatinib Monohydrate
Information: Dasatinib Monohydrate is a novel, potent and multi-targeted inhibitor that targets Abl, Src and c-Kit, with IC50 of <1 nM, 0.8 nM and 79 nM, respectively.

Name: Combretastatin A4
Information: Combretastatin A4 is a microtubule-targeting agent that binds β-tubulin with Kd of 0.4 μM.Phase 3.

Name: Fumagillin
Information: Fumagillin is a selective and potent irreversible inhibitor of Methionine aminopeptidase 2 (MetAP2), used as an antibiotic to treat microsporidiosis.

Name: Pemetrexed Disodium Hydrate
Information: Pemetrexed Disodium Hydrate is a novel antifolate and antimetabolite for TS, DHFR and GARFT with Ki of 1.3 nM, 7.2 nM and 65 nM, respectively.

Name: Erlotinib
Information: Erlotinib is an EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 2 nM, >1000-fold more sensitive for EGFR than human c-Src or v-Abl.

Name: Docetaxel Trihydrate
Information: Docetaxel, an analog of paclitaxel, is an inhibitor of depolymerisation of microtubules by binding to stabilized microtubules.

Name: SRT2104 (GSK2245840)
Information: SRT2104 (GSK2245840) is a selective SIRT1 activator involved in the regulation of energy homeostasis. Phase 2.

Name: ORY-1001 (RG-6016) 2HCl
Information: ORY-1001 (RG-6016) 2HCl is an orally active and selective lysine-specific demethylase LSD1/KDM1A inhibitor with IC50 of <20 nM, with high selectivity against related FAD dependent aminoxidases. Phase 1.

Name: GSK2879552 2HCl
Information: GSK2879552 2HCl is a potent, selective, orally bioavailable, irreversible LSD1 inhibitor with Kiapp of 1.7 μM. Phase 1.

Name: Pexmetinib (ARRY-614)
Information: Pexmetinib (ARRY-614) is a potent, orally bioavailable, dual p38 MAPK/Tie-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 4 nM/18 nM in a HEK-293 cell line. Phase 1.

Name: AT7519 HCl
Information: AT7519 HCl is a multi-CDK inhibitor for CDK1, 2, 4, 6 and 9 with IC50 of 10-210 nM in cell-free assays. It is less potent to CDK3 and little active to CDK7. Phase 2.

Name: Afatinib (BIBW2992) Dimaleate
Information: Afatinib (BIBW2992) Dimaleate irreversibly inhibits EGFR/HER2 including EGFR(wt), EGFR(L858R), EGFR(L858R/T790M) and HER2 with IC50 of 0.5 nM, 0.4 nM, 10 nM and 14 nM, respectively 100-fold more active against Gefitinib-resistant L858R-T790M EGFR mutant.

Name: Itacitinib (INCB39110)
Information: Itacitinib(INCB39110) is an orally bioavailable inhibitor of Janus-associated kinase 1 (JAK1) with potential antineoplastic activity.

Name: AMG319
Information: AMG319 is a potent and selective PI3Kδ inhibitor with IC50 of 18 nM, >47-fold selectivity over other PI3Ks. Phase 2.

Name: MI-463
Information: MI-463 is a potent inhibitor of Menin-MLL interaction with an IC50 value of 15.3 nM.

Name: Pexidartinib (PLX3397)
Information: Pexidartinib (PLX3397) is an oral, potent mutil-targeted receptor tyrosine kinase inhibitor of CSF-1R, Kit, and Flt3 with IC50 of 20 nM, 10 nM and 160 nM, respectively. Phase 3.

Name: BLU9931
Information: BLU9931 is a potent, selective, and irreversible FGFR4 inhibitor with IC50 of 3 nM, about 297-, 184-, and 50-fold selectivity over FGFR1/2/3, respectively.

Name: EPZ020411 2HCl
Information: EPZ020411 is a potent and selective small molecule PRMT6 inhibitor with an IC50 of 10 nM.

Name: Nazartinib (EGF816, NVS-816)
Information: Nazartinib (EGF816, NVS-816) is a covalent, irreversible, mutant-selective EGFR inhibitor that has nanomolar inhibitory potency against activating mt (L858R, ex19del) and T790M mt, with up to 60-fold selectivity over wild type (wt) EGFR in vitro.

Name: 4-Hydroxytamoxifen
Information: 4-Hydroxytamoxifen is the active metabolite of tamoxifen and a selective estrogen receptor (ER) modulator that is widely used in the therapeutic and chemopreventive treatment of breast cancer.

Name: Licochalcone A
Information: Licochalcone A is an estrogenic flavanoid extracted from licorice root, showing antimalarial, anticancer, antibacterial and antiviral activities. Phase 3.

Name: CB1954
Information: CB1954(Tretazicar) is a anticancer prodrug that is converted in the presence of the enzyme NQO2 and co-substrate caricotamide ( EP-0152R) (EP) into a potent cytotoxic bifunctional alkylating agent. It can be activated by NAD(P)H quinone oxidoreductase 2.

Name: Cyclo (-RGDfK)
